title: punch
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve in a large punch bowl.
Add ice.
Serves 30 people.

title: sweet potatoes and cranberries
directions: In a medium covered saucepan, cook cranberries in water until berries pop (about 10 minutes).
Add sugar and cook 15 minutes more.
Chill for later use in recipe.
Cook, peel and slice sweet potatoes lengthwise.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Place sweet potato slices in greased 2-quart casserole.

title: weight watchers nightmare
directions: Pour coffee in a large saucepan.
Add marshmallows; stir over low heat until it's a syrup.
Cool.
Whip cream; fold into syrup. Line an 8 x 8 x 3-inch dish with graham crackers, then a layer of banana slices.
Pour half of syrup mixture, then layer graham crackers, sliced bananas and other half of mixture.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Refrigerate.

title: bran muffins
directions: Put soda in water and pour over cereal; leave until soft.
Mix in other ingredients.
Fill muffin tins 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: nacho beef dip
directions: In a medium skillet, brown meat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: texas chili(makes 6 servings)
directions: In large saucepan over medium-high heat, brown steak in batches in butter.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add tomatoes with liquid, steak sauce and chili powder.
Heat to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour and 15 minutes to 1 hour and 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sandwich spread relish
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients to measure.
Mix all vegetables and add salt.
Mix salt through and let stand for 30 minutes.
Drain well by squeezing vegetables by hand and put into another pan. Then add sugar and vinegar and boil for 25 minutes.
Mix flour with some water to make a thickening agent.
Add to boiling mixture during the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Stir to thicken.
Remove from heat and cool by letting stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Add prepared mayonnaise and prepared mustard.
Put still warm mixture into sterilized jars and seal with hot lids and rings.
Yields 12 pints.

title: grammy's strawberry glazed pie
directions: Put aside 8 small whole berries for garnish.
Take a handful of berries and squeeze enough into a small saucepan to make 1/2 cup. Leave the rest of berries whole or halved.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, and water with crushed berries.
Bring to boil over medium heat and cook while stirring over low heat for 3 minutes, or until clear and thickened.
Add a drop of red food coloring and butter.
Stir and let cool.
Place berries into cooked pie shell and cover with cooled sauce.
Top with real whipped cream and garnish with a few small whole berries.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: sharps and flats
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in saucepan; heat, stirring, until butter is melted.
Place remaining ingredients in roasting pan.
Pour butter mixture over cereal mixture; toss to mix well. Bake in preheated 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour until fine.
Add water, lemon juice or vinegar and egg yolk.
Mix together until blended. Refrigerate until chilled.
Roll out.
Makes two 9-inch shells.

title: wasper cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Cook until thick.
Pour in cake mix and mix together well by hand.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Then sprinkle with butterscotch chips.
Then bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with water to egg mixture.
Stir in sauerkraut.
Bake in two greased and floured 8-inch square or round pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: bud's mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Bake in a greased and mealed skillet.

title: potato casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish and put in sliced potatoes. Mix the soup and water together and pour over the potatoes. Pour onions on top of this. Slice your stick of butter all over the top of soup. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.

title: oatmeal cookies(hand me downs)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, oatmeal, pecans and raisins.
Add sifted flour, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Mix well. Roll into small balls (approximately 1 teaspoon dough) and roll in sugar.
Cover glass with cheesecloth on bottom and dampen and press cookies down in pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes (moderate oven).
Remove immediately from baking sheets.

title: butterscotch pudding
directions: Boil the first 6 ingredients until taffy.
After you have boiled the first ingredients, add the boiling water (or real hot water) and add the remaining ingredients (which have been mixed well) until it comes to a boil.
If it's too thick, add more water.

title: cauliflower au gratin
directions: Place cauliflower upside down in a 2-quart microproof casserole dish.
Add water.
Cover with lid and cook on High for 4 minutes; turn cauliflower over.
Cover and cook on High for 4 to 5 minutes or until tender; drain and reserve liquid.
Mix liquid with cheese and bread crumbs.
Pat mixture gently onto cauliflower.
Cover and cook on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese begins to melt. Let stand, still covered, 3 minutes before serving.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and mix well.
Add potato chips, pecans and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: rolled round steak roast(servings:  8)
directions: On waxed paper or cutting board, lay round steak flat.
Layer bread crumbs, onion, pepper, mushrooms, eggs and bacon strips in order given.
Dash with salt and pepper.
Carefully roll up so ingredients mostly remain inside; tie with kite twine.
Carefully place into roasting pan and pour soup and water over roast. Roast, covered, 4 or 5 hours in 300° oven.

title: mexican chicken
directions: You will also need 1 large casserole dish or 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: celery seed dressing(for salad)
directions: Combine sugar, salt, paprika, onion juice and catsup in mixing bowl.
Beating at second speed, add oil slowly and alternately with vinegar.
Add celery seed.

title: homemade vegetable beef soup
directions: Add
meat to water; let cook until meat is tender.
Add mixed vegetables,
tomato
sauce,
ketchup,
onions
(chopped fine), sugar, chili powder and Accent.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Cook
over
a
slow
fire
until other ingredients are tender. When
other
ingredients
are tender, mix all-purpose flour
with water which will form a thick mixture.
Add flour mixture to soup.
The purpose of the flour mixture is to keep the soup
from being
too watery.
Makes close to a gallon of soup.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: chow chow
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt.
Cover and let stand overnight in refrigerator.
Next day, rinse vegetables well. Combine vinegar, water, sugar and spices in pot and let these come to a boil, then add chopped vegetables.
Let boil and simmer 30 minutes.
Seal in clean jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta per box instructions, drain and cool.
Prepare salad dressing per package directions.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Before serving sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage crescent bites
directions: Line bottom of 2 pans, each 13 x 9-inches, with dough from packages of rolls.
In a skillet, brown the sausage; drain.
Mix eggs with sausage and spread over dough in the two pans; reserve 1 to 2 tablespoons of egg.
Sprinkle cheese and seasoning over sausage mixture.
Cover with a layer of roll from remaining packages.
Brush with reserved egg.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares or bars.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat cranberries, sugar and water to boiling, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat to low and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove from heat, stir in remaining ingredients; cover and refrigerate.

title: texas casserole
directions: Line 13 x 9-inch pan with Fritos or Doritos.
Brown together beef, onion and pepper.
Pour this over chips in pan.
Layer on top of meat the soup, beans and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Melt cheese on top before serving.

title: old fashioned peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine cake mix, pie filling, eggs, 1/2 teaspoon extract and nuts.
Blend at low speed until completely moistened, about 1 minute.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Spread batter in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients with pastry blender for topping. Mixture will be crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans; mix beans and mushroom soup in casserole bowl. Cook in oven at 300° for 30 minutes.
Put canned onion rings on top of casserole.
Put back in oven for 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown on top.

title: sun pickles
directions: Pack pickles in jars.
Heat solution to boiling and pour over pickles.
Add pinch of alum and seal can.
Add dill.
Set in sun 3 to 4 days.

title: potato soup
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a large kettle.
Cook about 4 hours. Add 1/3 cup butter and evaporated milk when ready to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, baking powder, cinnamon, pecans, salt and dates and set aside. Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl; add sugar, oil and vanilla. Beat until creamy; stir in the zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: milky way candy bar cake
directions: Melt candy bars and 1 stick margarine; set aside.
Cream sugar and 1 stick margarine.
Add beaten eggs.
Blend with buttermilk; add melted candy and margarine mixture.
Add pecans.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 70 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: In a saucepan, boil vinegar and sugar.
Add peppers.
Boil again, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in fruit pectin and food coloring.
Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal. This makes 6 cups.

title: hot rolls
directions: Put yeast in hot water.
Mix shortening and sugar.
Then add the cold water and flour.
Mix well.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour, then work dough down and squeeze out in two little balls in each muffin pan.
Let rise and bake.

title: turkey supreme
directions: Melt butter in 1-quart saucepan. Stir in 2 tablespoons flour. Stir in all at once 1 cup milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring until thickened and smooth. Blend in mushroom soup, parsley, sherry, salt and pepper. Add turkey, mushrooms and peas. Heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over hot buttered wide noodles.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican pie
directions: Brown beef, salt, pepper, garlic, chili powder and onion together.
Pour through strainer to make sure all grease is removed.
Make pie crust with crescent rolls.
Flatten them to fit in pie dish.
Pour beef mixture into pie crust.
Layer tomatoes and cheese.
Blend sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spread on top of pie.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and salt; pour over vegetables. Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: quick chicken pot pie
directions: Cover chicken with water in pot; add onion, salt and pepper and cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to cool.
Pull into small pieces.
Add soup and slices of potatoes and cook until potatoes are tender.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup cold water until smooth.
Pour into hot mixture to thicken.
Add chicken (without bones) and peas to the potatoes.
Spray deep dish with Pam.
Pour mixture into dish.
Open cans of biscuits; place on top of hot chicken and potato mixture.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are brown.

title: noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients with a fork until dough forms.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise for 15 minutes.
On a floured board, roll out as thin as possible.
Allow rolled out dough to dry enough that it will not be sticky, but not too dry or it will be brittle.
Roll up tightly in jelly roll fashion.
With a sharp knife, cut the noodles for soup or to desired widths. Noodle may also be cut into 1/4-inch squares.
Let noodles dry by spreading out noodles on a clean cloth and tossing gently, occasionally, until completely dry.
Store in plastic bags.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Moisten chicken with water; shake off excess.
Mix in bowl Bisquick, cracker meal and seasonings.
Coat chicken completely with mix.
Place chicken on foil-lined baking sheets sprayed with Pam.
Bake chicken 1/2 hour on one side and 1/2 hour on other side.

title: meringue crust - lemon cloud pie
directions: Crust: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg white and cream of tartar in medium bowl to soft peaks.

Gradually beat in sugar, beating to stiff peaks. Spoon mixture into ungreased 9-inch glass pie pan, spreading bottom and up sides to form a bowl shape. Bake 40 minutes or until firm to touch and lightly browned.
Cool on wire rack.

title: zucchini bread(good)
directions: Add oil and sugar and beat, then add eggs, zucchini and vanilla and beat together.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans.
Pour in two greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: lo-fat macaroni salad
directions: Bring water to a rolling boil.
Add macaroni; cover.
Let stand for 7 to 8 minutes.
Drain macaroni and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients into mixing bowl and mix well.
Salt to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: roast beef hash
directions: Cook roast until done and make gravy from drippings. Chop roast into fine shreds. Chop potato into fine pieces. Mix together the roast and potato pieces and moisten with the gravy. Place in casserole dish. Dot with butter. Bake at 375° for 45-60 minutes.

title: chicken-chestnut casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion with 1/2 of butter until onion is clear.
Mix the chicken, rice, soup, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Melt rest of butter; mix with corn flakes.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, or until hot and fluffy. Serves 8 to 10.

title: turkey lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain. Meanwhile, cook turkey, onion and garlic powder until meat is browned.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato juice, tomato sauce, basil and oregano.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes.
If using mushrooms, drain and stir them in.
Stir together Ricotta, parsley, Parmesan, milk and pepper.
Arrange half the noodles in bottom of 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Spread with half the meat mixture.
Layer remaining noodles, all the Ricotta mixture and remaining meat mixture.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella.
May be baked now or cover dish and freeze whole or freeze 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until nearly firm.
Remove from freezer and cut into 6 portions. Transfer each piece to a freezer bag or a lightly greased individual casserole.
Seal, label and freeze.

title: black raspberry delight
directions: Blend well with medium speed of electric mixer.
Great with cookies or animal crackers.

title: apple cake
directions: Slice and cube apples.
Combine sugar and apples.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Add oil and eggs.
Stir until mixed.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 50 minutes.
Let cool 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in microwave and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add rice and stir.
In microwave bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Microwave until smooth and pour over broccoli and rice.
Mix together.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: instant onion soup
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Store in a container with a tight fitting lid.
Shake well before each use.
Will keep for about 6 months.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Layer, cover and refrigerate 8 to 12 hours.

title: aunt lori's mystery potatoes
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
While hash browns are still frozen, layer on bottom of baking dish.
In a large bowl, mix soup, onion, sour cream, cheese, salt and pepper.
Melt butter in pan and saute corn flakes.
Spread soup mix on top of potatoes. Coat with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: minty spiced chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl stir together mint, lime zest, sugar, salt, garlic, turmeric, coriander, cardamom and red pepper flakes.
Prick chicken all over with fork.
Brush chicken with lime juice.
Rub mint mixture over all sides of chicken pieces.
Place pieces on rack set in roasting pan.
Roast until juices run clear when pierced with fork, about 1 hour.
Serve hot or let cool in pan on rack 30 minutes.
Wrap and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 4.

title: near east meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, milk and salt.
Shape into 18 meatballs.
Brown meatballs in shortening.
Pour in soup and water; bring to a boil.
Stir in rice and cover.
Simmer 30 minutes or until rice is tender.
Stir often.
Garnish with parsley.

title: baked sea bass with black olive sauce
directions: Combine garlic, olives, oregano, basil and parsley in small bowl.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Heat oil in 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish at 425° for 1 minute.
Spread olive mixture evenly over bottom of baking dish.
Arrange sea bass, skin side up, on top.
Pour vegetable stock around fillets.
Bake, basting occasionally with juices, 15 minutes or until done.
To serve, arrange fillets and olive mixture on heated serving plate.

title: chiuch's 4# pound cake
directions: With butter at room temperature beat eggs, vanilla and sugar in a large bowl.
In a small bowl mix the flour and salt.
Blend together in large bowl.
Put in a Bundt pan.
Bake at 325 for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: chicken stuffed with cheese
directions: You will also need wooden toothpicks.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients and pour into greased sheet cake pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans over the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut bars
directions: Mix ingredients with hands; roll into oblong shape rolls (approximately 2 rolls, each 7 inches long).
Smooth and flatten the top of each roll with your hands, keeping the sides and ends of rolls more round.
Place each roll on a piece of wax paper; fold around dough.
Place rolls in refrigerator until next day. (Can also be frozen until ready to use.)
Cut into thin strips; bake in moderate 350° oven until golden.
Yields 5 dozen.
Cut each bar into 1/2-inch slices and bake for 13 to 15 minutes, until golden.

title: swiss and crab quiche
directions: Arrange cheese evenly over bottom of pastry shell.
Top with crab meat; sprinkle with green onions.
Combine eggs, cream, salt, lemon peel and dry mustard; pour evenly over crab meat.
Top with almonds.
Bake in a slow 325° oven for about 45 minutes, or until set.
Remove from oven; let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: pot roast
directions: Place mushrooms, carrots and potatoes in the bottom of a Dutch oven or roasting pan.
Place roast on top of vegetables; spread mushroom soup over roast and sprinkle with dry onion soup mix. Cover and cook in a 300° oven for 2 to 3 hours or until it forks tender.

title: crunchy celery skillet
directions: Cook and stir celery, water chestnuts, instant bouillon, salt and celery salt in oil over medium heat, turning vegetables constantly with pancake turner, until celery is crisp-tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in pimiento and heat thoroughly.
Makes 5 servings.

title: dog head(bread sodes)
directions: Fresh corn with leaves (blades).
Save shucks after you remove from corn.
Grate corn and put in a little hot water or corn juice; add a little soda and make into balls.
Put corn in shucks and tie or use toothpicks to hold shut.
Drop in boiling water and cook about 20 minutes or until done.
(Tender.)

title: pie meringue
directions: Beat egg whites with water in a bowl until fluffy.
Add cream of tartar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spread over pie, sealing edge. Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with a fork.
Beat vigorously 1 minute. Bake until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 45 to 55 minutes at 350°.
Cool 5 minutes.
Run knife around sides and remove from pan.
Grease bottom of pan.
Makes 1 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Put hot water, yeast and sugar in mixing bowl; set aside.
Mix sifted flour, salt, powdered milk together. Add to yeast mixture. Add melted butter as you mix together; let rise.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Place on greased pan or muffin cups.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: chocolate chip zucchini cake
directions: Cream butter, oil and sugar. Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Beat with mixer. Mix all dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture and blend well. Stir in zucchini. Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: eclair cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients together to make your crust.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 55 minutes at 350°. Remove and cool.
Cut cake in half (it will be very thin; use a serrated knife to cut).
Scoop out the dough to make room for the filling.
Okay if falls apart a little.
Set aside.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350° and continue baking for 45 minutes.
Serve warm generously sprinkled with powdered sugar.

title: saucepan cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and mix.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat. Add flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add nuts and chips.
Grease pan and flour.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.

title: corny macaroni and cheese
directions: In a large bowl, combine macaroni, milk, cottage cheese, corn (or Veg-All), egg product and 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese.
Spoon into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. In a small bowl, toss crackers with 1/4 cup cheese.
Sprinkle over macaroni mixture; return to oven and bake 30 minutes.
Can be served hot or at room temperature.

title: mocha mousse
directions: In a small saucepan, heat milk and gelatin to boiling point, stirring to dissolve gelatin.
Pour into blender with the exception of the heavy cream.
Process until smooth.
Add heavy cream; process at a low speed until well blended.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart mold.
Chill until firm.
Serve with coffee brand whipped cream or regular whipped cream.

title: mom's buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add 2 cups sugar.
Mix flour and 1 cup sugar into butter, then mix all together and pour into pie shells.
Bake in 450° oven for 10 minutes, then in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until top is browned.
Yum!
Yum!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients including sugar into bowl.
Make a well in dry ingredients and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix together until smooth.
Divide batter into 3 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.
Cool, then wrap in foil or plastic.
Keep one day before slicing.

title: black walnut chocolate pound cake
directions: Melt chocolate; set aside.
Cream together the margarine, shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and cocoa.
(Coat chopped walnuts with a bit of this.)
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring, chocolate and nuts.
Put into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and about 45 minutes.
Turn out on rack to cool.
This freezes well.

title: beef brisket
directions: Mix soup, vinegar, soy sauce, liquid smoke and garlic together in baking pan.
Marinate brisket in mixture overnight fat side up.
Bake at 250 degrees for 5 to 6 hours.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Saute onion, celery and pepper in butter until tender. Combine with chicken and other ingredients except cheese and onion rings.
Put into greased casserole and bake about 25 minutes at 350° or until thoroughly heated.
Remove from oven; cover with cheese and top with onion rings.
Return to oven and heat until cheese is melted, being careful not to burn onion rings.

title: low fat orange dream cheesecake(calories per serving: 100)
directions: Sprinkle crumbs onto bottom of 8 or 9 inch spring form pan or 9 inch pie plate sprayed with cooking spray.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl at least 2 minutes until gelatin is completely dissolved.
Cool 5 minutes.
Pour into blender container.
Add cheeses; cover.
Blend on medium speed until well blended, occasionally scraping down sides of blender container; pour into large bowl.
Add whipped topping; stir gently until well blended. Pour into prepared pan; smooth top with spatula. Refrigerate 4 hours or until set.
Remove side of pan just before serving.
Store leftover cheesecake in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: irish potato soup
directions: Boil all ingredients (except milk and flour) until potatoes are tender.
Blend milk and flour.
Add to potato mixture, stirring well as you add.
Keep stirring on low heat until thickened.
Keep stirring or it will scorch!!

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar well. Sift dry ingredients together; add to oil and sugar. Beat eggs slightly and add to batter. Add vanilla; fold in apples and nuts. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cream cheese and scallions.
Mold into a ball and cover with chipped ham.
Make a day ahead so flavors blend.
Serve with crackers.

title: florentine layers
directions: Cook sausage, onions and garlic until sausage is done and no longer pink.
Add sauce and mushrooms and simmer for 30 minutes. Combine spinach, cheese, egg, grated Parmesan, pepper and salt.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook hamburger and chopped onion until brown; drain.
Combine all ingredients together and heat in oven until it's bubbly hot.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips on top.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Melt oleo.
Add zucchini and onion.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes, until tender.
Add parsley, salt, basil, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add the zucchini (cut in cubes). Add the tomato sauce.
Add the corn and salt and pepper to taste. Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes, or until zucchini is tender. Serve over rice.

title: longan-mandarin ice
directions: Drain longans and mandarins, set aside syrups.
Heat water and sugar in a saucepan until sugar dissolves.
Add lemon, longan and mandarin syrups, cool.
Mix syrup with fruit in a blender. Freeze in ice cream maker or use freezer tray method.

title: lemon blueberry bread
directions: Wash berries; let dry.
Sprinkle the 1 tablespoon flour over berries; toss gently to coat.
Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, sift together the remaining dry ingredients.
Gently stir in the berries, nuts and grated rind; set aside.

title: all-bran bread or rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over first 4 ingredients and add eggs. Dissolve yeast in a little lukewarm water and add to mixture. Work in flour and let rise.
Bake at 350°.

title: vegetable sandwich spread
directions: Combine the above.
Mix well.
Add enough mayonnaise for good spreading consistency.

title: sweet dough rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and set aside. Scald milk and add butter and sugar to melt and cool to lukewarm.
Add egg and yeast. Gradually add flour until dough is workable. Flour table and knead the dough for 5 to 10 minutes, working to a soft satiny finish.
Put dough in greased, large bowl.
Cover and let raise for at least 2 hours. Punch down and form into rolls and place in greased pan and let raise another 2 hours. Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes until tops are browned.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Pare carrots and slice into sticks. Cook until almost tender; drain. Melt margarine; add sugar and spices. Cook together until slightly glazed in appearance. Add drained carrots; cook for 3 to 4 minutes, shaking pan constantly, coating carrots. Serve at once.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix well sugar, cinnamon and flour.
Stir into apples and place in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients until all is fairly moistened.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until apples are done.
Serves 12.
Terrific served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and drain spinach,
mix with all other ingredients. Better if sits overnight.
Serve with crackers or fritos scoops.

title: 7 cup cookies
directions: Blend sugars and oleo.
Cream well.
Add oil, egg and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Fold in rice krispies, oatmeal and coconut.
Chill about 1 hour.
Shape into balls - flatten with glass dipped in sugar.

title: rhonda's mexican chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Doritos) in
a large saucepan and cook 10 minutes. Layer Doritos and grated cheese.
Mix in casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 6 minutes. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fudge candy
directions: Melt together the margarine and cheese.
Mix the cocoa and confectioners sugar.
Mix together. Add the vanilla and black walnuts.

title: brownie sundaes with honey berry sauce
directions: In small bowl, combine honey, lemon juice and peel; mix well. Gently mix in berries.

title: irish potato casserole
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in oleo for 5 minutes.
Add pimiento to flour; stir and add milk.
Stir and cook until thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add potatoes.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: quick salad
directions: Mix fruit cocktail, pineapple, marshmallows, pudding and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Add bananas just before serving.
Good served on a slice of angel food cake.

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter and sugar.
Roll into balls.
Dip in chocolate.
Leave top of ball uncovered.

title: jogging in  a jug
directions: Drink 2 ounces twice a day or once a day.
Good for arthritis and several other things.
Mix up and put in refrigerator.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill for best results.

title: one minute cookies
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in pan.
Boil 1 minute, then add next ingredients (oats, peanut butter, salt and vanilla).
Drop on wax paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until fully cooked.
Remove from bone.
Melt margarine; mix with Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing.
Put into a cake pan.
Place chicken pieces on top, then mix rest of ingredients together and pour on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until bubbly.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles in boiling water.
Rinse and drain.
Mix Fri-Pats and spaghetti sauce together.
In 9 x 13-inch pan layer sauce, noodles, sauce, mushrooms, olives, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Layer cheese sparingly so there is enough for top.
Continue to layer until ingredients are used. Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbling done.
Best if refrigerated overnight then cooked.

title: apple cider vinegar
directions: Take one teaspoon of cider in a glass of water; add some honey.
It helps take the edge off your appetite and gives you an overall good feeling.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add both sugars and molasses; cream well.
Add eggs and beat for 1 minute.
Add raisins and dates to mixture. Blend remaining ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoons into lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375 degrees for 8 minutes.
Do Not Overbake.
Remove from oven when top still looks doughy.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter together with fork and make crumbs.
Then mix real good with hands.
Mix pudding according to package then refrigerate until it sets up.
Sprinkle 3/4 of crumb mix on the bottom of pie shell.
Add pudding and then spread with Cool Whip (optional).
Sprinkle remaining crumb mix on top.

title: leprechaun pie
directions: Thoroughly blend together the condensed milk and the limeade frozen concentrate.

Fold in the whipped topping, adding green food coloring a few drops at a time until desired hue is attained. Pour the filling into the prepared graham cracker pie shell. Garnish pie with dollops of whipped topping and lime slices too, if desired.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix and serve chilled.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix the oleo, powdered sugar and vanilla together thoroughly. Stir together the sifted flour, salt and chopped nuts and stir in. Chill dough roll into 1-inch balls (can be pressed down with a fork).
Place 2 1/2 inches apart.
Set oven at 400°. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until cookies are set but not brown.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.
Cool and roll again.

title: mae's chili
directions: Brown chuck and sausage; add all other ingredients and simmer for 2 hours.
Taste before adding pepper pods.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute cornflakes and almonds in oleo.
Add cheese.
Put cornflake mixture on top of the chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: red, white and green salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, onion and tomatoes.
Stir together mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar and sugar; pour over vegetables and toss.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Salad will keep for several days.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar pie crust cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and cut in butter.
Add beaten eggs, half and half and vanilla.
Chill dough at least 2 hours, preferably overnight.
Knead dough with mixture of 1 part sugar and 1 part flour until not sticky.
Roll thin and cut into desired shapes. Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes until lightly browned.
Allow to cool.
Ice and decorate as desired.

title: chicken enchilitas
directions: Stir chicken, pepper, 1/2 cup picante sauce and cream cheese in saucepan until smooth on low heat.
Spoon 1/3 cup chicken.
Mix into tortilla shells.
Line up in pan.
Melt Velveeta cheese and milk in saucepan.
Let set for 1 hour.
Pour over top of tortillas.
Pour on rest of picante sauce and cheese mix.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until heated.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and beat well. Add the flour, cinnamon and remaining ingredients.
Divide into 3 greased cake pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: old fashioned nut cake
directions: Melt butter; blend with sugar, then blend eggs one at a time. Put vanilla flavor in.
Then add nuts; add flour.
Add raisins. Mix all together.
Grease tube pan.
Bake in tube pan in a preheated 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken alfredo
directions: Stir and cook slowly until thick.
Serve over fettuccine noodles or small spaghetti.
Add chicken to sauce after it has cooked.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix milk and cheese (soften).
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in a slightly greased casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: white fudge
directions: Boil butter, sugar and milk to soft ball stage.
Let cool. Add marshmallow whip, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until starts to set. Pour in pans and cut in squares.

title: squash souffle
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Drain.
Add crackers, butter, egg yolks, cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until firm and golden.
Serve while hot.
Serves 6.

title: peach pickles
directions: Peel peaches and place in clean jars.
Heat water and sugar and pour over fruit.
Add cloves to taste.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Combine cream cheese and sugar.
Add pineapple, strawberries and banana; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in 8 x 8 square dish.
Cover and place in freezer for approximately 5 hours.

title: zucchini bran bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, spices and sugar.
Stir in Chex crumbs and nuts.
Combine eggs, milk, oil, zucchini and raisins.
Add to flour mixture; stir just until moistened.
Spread evenly in pan.
Bake 70 to 80 minutes or until tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion, celery and garlic in oil until tender but not brown.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce, Worcestershire, salt, sugar, chili powder and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer uncovered 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with cold water; stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover; simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Bake in unbaked pie shell until solid (as in pumpkin pie).
Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: relto's shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and chill. Serve with crackers.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add egg, salt and mashed bananas. Beat for 2 minutes. Add soda to sour milk. Add to first mixture and beat. Add flour and nuts. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots 5 minutes.
Drain.
Pour sauce over carrots and let stand 8 hours or overnight.

title: apple cider biscuits
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt. Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Stir in cider just until moistened. Turn onto a lightly floured surface and knead 8 to 10 times. Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness; cut with a 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheets. Sprinkle with cinnamon; pierce tops of biscuits with a fork. Bake at 425° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes with jackets on until tender.
Cool slightly, peel and then mash.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an unbaked deep dish pie crust and bake 10 minutes at 425°, then reduce temperature to 350° and cook for 40 minutes.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Brown onion and garlic lightly in oil in saucepan. Add meat and cook until brown, stirring with fork. Add remaining ingredients and simmer uncovered 1 1/2 hours.

title: strawberry yogurt pie
directions: Stir yogurt gently into whipped topping in large bowl until well blended.
Spoon into crust. Freeze 4 hours or overnight until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes or until pie can be cut easily.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and fruit, if desired. Store leftover pie in freezer.

title: stewed squirrel
directions: Clean squirrel.
Place the squirrel in a container with small onion, salt and pepper and boil until meat comes off the bone. Serve.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Blend in flour; gradually add cream and broth, stirring steadily to boiling point.
Cook on low 1 minute.
Add pepper, nutmeg and sherry.
Mix 1/2 sauce with mushrooms and spaghetti.
Add remaining sauce and cheese.
Add sauce to chicken.
Butter casserole dish.
Layer spaghetti, chicken and end with chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a large dutch oven pan place V-8, celery and onion.
Cook all other vegetables until tender.
Season as you prefer (I use oregano, basil and bay leaves).
Serves 8. 108 cal. per serving. 0 gm. of fat. 90% fat free.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake layers of cake mix as on the box except put in 3 pans and don't bake as long.
Before putting layers together, make sure cakes are cool.
Put first layer of cake at bottom of punch bowl. Put on vanilla pudding (save enough for other layers).
Layer banana slices over pudding, next layer pudding over bananas and next layer is strawberries.
Punch bowl should be full.
Keep refrigerated.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell and bake for 5 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.

title: spinach salad
directions: Layer spinach, then bacon, eggs and peas.
Mix mayonnaise and salad dressing together and spread over top; seal.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Blend all ingredients (half of onions).
Pour into casserole dish; cover with remaining onions.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until done.
Can be frozen.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp together to form ball. Decorate with shrimp.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes crosswise in 1/4-inch slices.
Place in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper.
Mix soup and milk together and pour over potatoes.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender. Remove from oven and lightly stir.
Cover top of potatoes with sliced Velveeta cheese and return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla; beat until fluffy. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cocoa; add to creamed mixture. Stir in nuts. Spread in a greased jelly roll pan (cookie sheet will do). Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes. Sprinkle marshmallows evenly over cake; return to oven for 2 to 3 minutes. Using a knife dipped in water, spread the melted marshmallows evenly over cake. Cool.

title: peach pot pie
directions: Melt butter in Pyrex dish.
Mix together flour, sugar and milk.
Pour mixture over melted butter.
Put fruit over mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Best to use frozen peaches.

title: cantonese vegetable soup(vegetarian)
directions: Heat 1/2 cup of the broth in a large soup pot over high heat. When broth is boiling, add onion, garlic and ginger.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce and remaining 5 1/2 cups of broth.
Bring to a gentle boil.
Add all remaining ingredients except scallions. Bring to a simmer and cook for 10 minutes.
Garnish with scallions and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese bars
directions: Cream together yolk, vanilla, sugar and cream cheese until soft.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with 1 package crescent rolls (separate them on perforations).
Press together.
Top with cheese mixture.
Top with another package rolls.
Beat egg white and brush on top.
Cover with powdered sugar.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: beet and pineapple salad
directions: Drain
beets into measuring cup and add enough water to make 1 1/2
cups.
Heat
juice
and add to jello and sugar to dissolve. Let
cool until thickens.
Add beets and pineapple. Pour in
mold or	flat
dish.
Serve
on lettuce and top with spoon of mayonnaise.

title: pocket rolls
directions: Mix lukewarm water and yeast and set aside for 1 to 2 hours. In a large bowl mix boiling water, sugar and Crisco.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add beaten egg, flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Mix all ingredients together and put in bowl with lid on.
Place in refrigerator overnight.

title: grammie's zucchini cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine the first 10 ingredients. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Combine the cream cheese, oleo, vanilla and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Ice cake.

title: cherry delight
directions: Have all ingredients cold except for cream cheese and margarine.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Mix completely.
Stir in flour mixture and then stir in hot water.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Divide corn between 2 ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pans.

title: matzo balls and chicken soup
directions: Combine eggs, water and melted fat in medium bowl.
Stir in matzo meal (which can be purchased at your super market or deli), salt, pepper and nutmeg. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: wassail holiday punch
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients 10 minutes, then strain syrup into a container.
Combine cranberry juice, lemon juice, and red wine in large saucepan and bring to simmer.
Mix with syrup and serve warm. Makes 40 servings.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Pour in two unbaked pie crusts.
Bake in hot oven (420°) for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 375°.
Bake for 45 minutes more.
Makes 2 pies.

title: perfect sunday dinner rolls
directions: Add sugar to yeast and water. Beat eggs in warm water; add oil and salt. Add egg mixture to the yeast mixture in a large bowl. Slowly add flour. Cover with a cloth and let stand overnight. Flour wax paper.

title: blueberry betty
directions: Melt butter and mix with bread.
Put 1/3 of bread in baking dish and top with 1 cup of berries.
Sprinkle with half the lemon juice and half the brown sugar.
Repeat, ending with bread.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix 1 cup warm water and 2 packages of yeast together.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Crust:
Mix together flour, melted margarine and pecans in bowl by hand.
Spread thin in a 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 5 to 6 minutes to form crust.
(Preheat oven to 350°).

title: buttercream icing
directions: In mixer bowl, beat Crisco and water until creamy.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Slowly blend in sifted powdered sugar until all is added.
Blend on high speed until all the sugar is moistened.
Add teaspoon of water if you want a creamier consistency.

title: jimmy's baked striper recipe
directions: Place aluminum foil in the bottom of a shallow pan.
Spread about 1 stick of butter in the center area of the foil where the fish will lie.
Place the filleted striper on foil.
Spread about 1 tablespoon of mayonnaise on each fillet (like you would spread it on bread).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place onion slices on top of the mayonnaise, then put bacon strips across the top.
Put in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Do not cover.

title: crock-pot pizza
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Cook noodles as directed on box.
Make two layers.
First, layer in crock-pot:
1/2 ground beef, 1/2 green pepper, 1/2 noodles, 1/2 mushrooms, 1/2 pepperoni, 1/2 pizza sauce, 1/2 Cheddar cheese and 1/2 Mozzarella cheese. Repeat for second layer.
Cook 3 to 4 hours in crock-pot.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli as directed on package; put in pan and stir in 1/4 cup butter.
Add cubed Velveeta cheese.
Roll out Ritz crackers.
Melt butter.
Mix crackers and butter together.
Put over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Blend in salad oil, sugar and eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients in order given.
Batter will be stiff.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Do not grease pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl combine oats, sugars, flour and salt. Combine soda and water.
Stir into oats mixture along with shortening and vanilla.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove and allow to stand about 2 minutes before removing to wire rack to cool. (Poor Man's Cookies because they contain no eggs, milk or nuts.)

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together over medium heat.
Stir until thickened.
Whisk in 3 tablespoons butter.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie crust.
Beat egg whites with 3/4 cup sugar and cream of tartar until stiff.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: baked custard(pudding)
directions: Beat eggs just enough to combine yolks and whites.
Add salt and sugar and stir to blend.
Stir in scalded milk gradually, but briskly.
Add vanilla. Pour into a glass 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 25 minutes.

title: lazy girl peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter and pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or glass dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk well.
Pour into melted butter.
Spoon peach slices evenly in dish.
Drizzle remaining syrup from peaches over mixture; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until crust is golden brown.

title: stir in drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat eggs with fork.
Stir in oil, vanilla and lemon.
Blend in sugar until mixture thickens.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg; stick into mixture.
Drop with teaspoon, 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with glass or fork dipped in sugar.
Bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes, or until delicate brown.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray cookie sheets with cooking spray. In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla until well mixed.
Add raisins.
(Batter will be stiff.)

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies very fine.
Set aside.
Cream together the cream cheese and butter.
Set aside.
Mix pudding with milk.
Add the Cool Whip and cream cheese mixture to the pudding mixture. Alternate layers of pudding mixture and cookies and end with cookies on top layer.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer at medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until center is almost set; cool.
Refrigerate 3 hours. Top with fruit.

title: carrot bisque(soup)
directions: In medium saucepan, heat ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until carrots are tender.
Place in blender; process until smooth.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Place second pie shell on top and crimp edges.
Make slits in top.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°, or until bubbly and brown.
Makes 2 pies (depends on size of pie shell).

title: low fat ice cream
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well. Just put in freezer.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust.
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer except coconut.
Add coconut last.
Pour in a deep 9-inch pie dish coated with 1/2 cube margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: popcorn treat
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle cinnamon over mixture and toss lightly.
Makes 2 servings. 150 calories; 3 grams fat per 1 cup serving.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: In a heavy, small saucepan, heat and stir 1/2 cup of the chocolate pieces over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.

title: melba's delight
directions: Combine and mix well flour, butter and chopped nuts.
Pat into the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
(You may substitute a 9-inch graham cracker crust, if you wish.)

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown beef; drain off fat.
Add to water and sauce in 3 or 4-quart saucepan.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients, except noodles.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, butter and condensed milk.
Put in skillet and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn off heat.
Add marshmallows, peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until mixed well. Pour batter into an 8-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: reindeer chow
directions: In a small Ziploc bag, add hay and magic dust.
Be very careful with the magic dust.
If it hits the floor, it will lose its magic.
On Christmas Eve, follow these directions:
Shake well.
Just before bedtime, place the reindeer chow out with Santa's cookies or sprinkle on your yard.
Hop into bed.
Shh ... listen for Santa!
Yields enough magic hay for 9 tiny reindeer.

title: white chocolate black walnut candy
directions: Line a baking sheet with aluminum foil and set aside.

In a double boiler, melt the chocolate with the butter and oil over hot (not simmering) water, stirring constantly until the chocolate is melted and smooth.	Remove the top part of the double boiler and stir the nuts into the melted chocolate.
Pour the mixture out onto the prepared cookie sheet.
Spread to desired thickness. Refrigerate for 20 to 30 minutes, or until set.
Slide a metal spatula under the chocolate to loosen from the foil.
Break into uneven pieces.
Store in airtight container in the refrigerator. Yields about 1 1/4 pounds.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; let stand overnight or all day in refrigerator.
Bake for 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: hot lettuce dressing
directions: Cut
bacon
in
small
size pieces and fry until crisp. Remove bacon
from
fat.
Mix
sugar, vinegar, water and salt together. Mix
into
the
slightly beaten egg, then stir into the bacon
fat until it thickens.
Pour over lettuce which has been
broken
in small pieces; add bacon pieces on top of it. Toss all together.

title: creamy potato bake
directions: Spread potatoes evenly in lightly greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with sour cream; sprinkle with bacon and onions. Top with cheese. Bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Serve hot. Serves 6.

title: country potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on until done.
Drain and let cool. Thinly slice the unpeeled potatoes.
Butter bottom of 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Put one layer of potatoes, salt, pepper, half of cheese and bacon in casserole.
Dribble half of the butter over layer.
Make another layer the same way.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until bubbling hot, about 15 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and cut up.
Put in mixing bowl with pickles, eggs and onions.
Fry bacon crisp.
Lay on paper towel to drain. Mix mustard, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add to bacon drippings and simmer for a few minutes.
Crumble bacon over potatoes.
Pour in sauce and mix all together.
Delicious hot or cold.

title: caramel marshmallows
directions: Cut marshmallows in half and set aside.
Melt slowly the caramels, margarine and milk.
Dip marshmallows in caramel and roll in Rice Krispies.
Set aside until set up and firm.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream softened margarine and sugar (do not use mixer).
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix well.
Use one bag of potato chips.
Punch holes in bag and crush with hands, not too small.
Add to dough and mix. Drop by teaspoon on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: crab gumbo(from maryland seafood marketing authority)
directions: Remove all cartilage from crabmeat.
In 4 to 5-quart pot, cook onion, celery and garlic in margarine or butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, okra and seasonings.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add crabmeat and heat through.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Serves 6.

title: vanilla wafer pie
directions: Heat to boil the milk, salt, juice and jello.
Add 2 beaten eggs; mix good and cool in refrigerator until livery.
(Beat about 10 minutes.)
Add drained peaches.
Grease plate with butter and line with wafers.
Pour mixture in and serve with whipped cream.

title: crescent chicken hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix cream cheese (room temperature) with all other ingredients, then stir in chicken.
Put mixture (about 1 tablespoon) on Pillsbury crescent rolls; fold.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. (Optional: Brush with butter.)
Make small or large.
Just cut triangles in half to make 2 triangles.

title: cheese grits
directions: Cook grits as instructed on the package using 2 Tbsp. less water.
While they are HOT, add the cheeses and butter (or margarine).
Pour into 9-inch square baking pan.
Top with paprika. Let it sit at least one night in the fridge before baking.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix soups and water together.
Put rice in a greased casserole dish.
Pour half the soup mixture over rice.
Dip chicken pieces into melted butter and lay on rice.
Pour other half of soup mixture over the chicken.
Bake at 325° to 350° uncovered 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: golden medley
directions: Combine macaroni, broccoli, ham, tomatoes and salt.
Heat cheese and milk over low heat.
Stir sauce into macaroni mixture. Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs that have been tossed in margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked beans with tomato sauce
directions: Soak and cook beans as directed for boiled beans.
Turn into a bean pot or heavy casserole.
Combine salt, brown sugar, molasses, mustard, tomatoes and onion; add to beans.
If the liquid does not cover the beans, add enough hot water to cover.
Scrape rind of salt pork and cut gashes in fat 1/2 inch apart.
Press into the beans, leaving only the rind exposed; or cut in 1/2-inch slices and bury in the beans or lay on top.
Cover and bake in a slow oven (250° to 275°) 6 to 8 hours, adding more water as necessary to keep the beans just covered.
Remove cover for last half hour of baking. Makes about 12 servings.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soups and water or milk in baking dish.
Add rice and stir.
Arrange chicken on top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for an hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes or until brown.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar, egg and applesauce.
Mix dry ingredients, raisins, nuts and cloves.
Drop by teaspoon.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put each ingredient on top of one another in a bowl.
Put bacon on top.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Mix and serve.

title: snack bars(makes 12 bars)
directions: Put in a large saucepan the first 3 ingredients.
Cook over low heat until blended.
Remove from heat; add cereal.
Spray 8 x 8-inch pan with cooking oil.
Press mixture into pan.
Cut into 12 pieces.

title: mammaw's oyster casserole
directions: Cover the bottom of a 13 x 14-inch Pyrex dish with a thin layer of crumbled saltine crackers.
Add the oysters; do not drain.
Top with another layer of saltine crackers to cover oysters good.
Top with a stick of butter, chopped.
Cover crackers with milk; add a pinch of salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 425° for 40 minutes, or until the top crust is brown.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Boil until thickened and stir in 3 drops of red food color, 3 Tbsp dry strawberry jello. Cool. In a baked pie shell place 1 quart of sliced strawberries, cover with above mixture. Chill. Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: peanut butter oatmeal bars
directions: Cream oleo and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla and peanut butter.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add and mix well.
Mix in oatmeal.
At last, add chocolate chips.
Bake in jelly roll pan at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: the best pesto ever
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a blender at high speed for 30 seconds, or to a thick, smooth sauce, stirring down if necessary with a rubber spatula.
Serves 4.

title: punch
directions: Mix and freeze.
Thaw by pouring warm 2 liter bottles of 7-Up over.

title: mawmaw's fudge(the best!)
directions: Place chocolate chips, butter and marshmallow cream in large bowl; set aside.
In heavy 4-quart saucepan bring to boil evaporated milk and sugar, stirring constantly.
When mixture reaches full rolling boil, start timing and cook 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; pour over chocolate mixture in bowl, stirring until well mixed.
(Be careful - it's very hot!) Beat with electric mixer or wooden spoon until it begins to hold its shape.
Beat in vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan; spread evenly.
Chill; cut into 60 pieces. Store in airtight container.
Makes 5 pounds of mouth-watering melt-in-your-mouth fudge!

title: texas pecan pralines
directions: Mix 5 ingredients in large heavy saucepan on low heat.
Cool until sugar dissolves.
Increase heat to high and boil to 210° on candy thermometer, about 5 minutes.
Add pecans and oleo.
Boil, stirring, to 230° thread stage, about 5 minutes.
Cool 1 minute. Beat with wooden spoon until thick and creamy, about 5 minutes. Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Cool.
Store in airtight container for a month.

title: mini chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Use lightly greased griddle or frypan (375° if griddle).
In small bowl, combine batter and chocolate chips.
Pour 2 tablespoons of batter and chocolate chips on griddle.
Turn when bubbly.
Cook until desired lightly browned surface is obtained. Serve with syrup.

title: parsley salad
directions: Cover wheat with water and set aside.
Wash, drain and chop parsley.
Cut up onions with most of greens.
Drain wheat well. Add parsley and onions, salad oil and lemon juice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Let stand several hours.

title: bubble bread
directions: Thaw bread.
Grease Bundt pan.
Sprinkle nuts on bottom.
Cut 1 loaf of bread into small pieces and distribute on bottom of pan. Mix sugar, butter and pudding.
Sprinkle 1/2 mixture on cut bread.
Layer 2nd loaf of bread and sprinkle on the rest of the pudding mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Invert on plate immediately.

title: cheesy pork casserole
directions: Crumble pork into a 3-quart casserole. Stir in mushrooms and onion. Cover with heavy-duty clear plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 5 to 7 minutes until pork is done, stirring twice. Drain fat. Cook and drain the egg noodles.
Add noodles, 1 1/2 cups cheese, peas, soup and seasoning.
Stir well. Cover and microwave at Medium 9 to 11 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring once. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Cover and cook at Medium for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: custard
directions: Mix ingredients; pour in pan.
Set pan filled with the mixture in a pan of water and bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Chill and sprinkle brown sugar on top.
Put in broiler and brown 2 to 3 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup of the lukewarm water.
Mix all other ingredients in a large bowl.
Add yeast mixture and the other cup of warm water.
Mix well.
Let rise for 2 or 3 hours in bowl. Place in refrigerator for 4 hours.

title: ralston brown rolls
directions: Mix together, oil, boiling water, cereal, salt and sugar.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to cooled first mixture.
Add eggs and flour.
Put in bowl and cover.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Does not need to set out and raise.

title: triple twirl alfredo
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.

title: buttermilk pecan waffles
directions: Combine the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until light.
Add buttermilk; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and beat until batter is smooth. Stir in butter.
Pour about 3/4 cup batter onto a lightly greased preheated waffle iron.
Sprinkle with a few pecans.
Bake until golden brown.
Yields 7 waffles (about 8 inches each).

title: russian tea
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and store in a closed container. Add 2 or 3 teaspoons to a cup of hot water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese. Stir in pineapple. Add 1 cup pecans. Add pepper, onion and salt. Form in ball. Roll in 1 cup pecans.

title: beef and vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package; drain.
Set aside. Heat oil in medium skillet over medium-high heat; add beef, onion and garlic.
Stir-fry 2 to 3 minutes or until beef is no longer pink.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients, blend well. Cook until mixture thickens and boils, stirring constantly.
Add vegetables; cook until thoroughly heated.

title: cinnamon fingers
directions: Cream sugar and butter and add egg yolk.
Sift together flour and cinnamon.
Combine ingredients and mix well.
Press into jelly roll pan.
Beat egg white until foamy and spread over dough. Sprinkle with one cup of chopped pecans and gently press them down.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.
As soon as removed from oven, immediately cut into fingers and remove from pan to cool.
Freezes beautifully.

title: english toffee
directions: Melt butter and add other ingredients.
Stir and cook until candy thermometer reaches 310°.
Pour over nuts which have been toasted for 15 minutes at 200° on a buttered cookie sheet.
When cool, spread 2 squares melted chocolate over candy.
(Use white or dark chocolate.)
Break into pieces when cool.
Tastes like a Heath bar.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Mix together in order given and put in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening until creamy.
Add flour and mix. Then add milk, egg yolks, and vanilla.
Beat with mixer 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cranberry (jello) salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 1 cup hot water, then add 1 cup cold water. Grind or chop apples and oranges, using 1/2 of the skins of fruit, also.
Sugar may be added to hot Jell-O mixture.
Mix all ingredients in order given and chill overnight.
This is always a favorite recipe for our family.

title: erlene's pillow-soft rolls
directions: Combine 1 1/4 cups flour, sugar, yeast and salt. In a saucepan, heat sour cream and water to 120° to 130°. Add to dry ingredients and beat until blended. Beat in eggs until smooth. Exchange beater for dough hook and turn to speed 2. Add enough of remaining flour to form a soft dough. Continuing on speed 2, knead 5 minutes, until dough is smooth and elastic.

title: chicken hot dish
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 bread cubes on bottom. Combine chicken, celery, green pepper and onion.
Spread over bread cubes.
Top with rest of cubes.
Beat eggs.
Add milk with salt and pepper.
Pour over layers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, whip soup together and spread over top. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: pineapple icebox dessert
directions: Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and beat until smooth.
Add a little pineapple juice if too heavy to spread. Crush vanilla wafers.
Line the bottom of pan with 1/2 of cookie crumbs.
Spread on mixture, then the crushed pineapple, then the whipped cream, then the rest of the crumbs.
Store overnight in freezing unit.
Optional:
Add vanilla to whipped cream; if sweetened add powdered sugar instead of granulated sugar as it makes water in bottom of pan.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding mix.
Stir until well mixed. Add marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Add more nuts if desired.
Mix well, pour into dish and refrigerate.
Can be frozen.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown pork in Dutch oven or put into casserole; add rest of ingredients.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: chuck roast in foil
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place roast on heavy aluminum foil. Sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Spread mushrooms soup on top.
Wrap roast in foil and seal well.
Bake for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until tender.

title: pecan fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°; grease 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
In separate bowl, mix butter, sugar and eggs until mixture is light and fluffy.
Beat in cocoa and vanilla, then blend in flour mixture.
Fold in pecans.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: banana cake(nellie hunt-edison)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in bananas.
Bake in 2 round pans at 350°.
Frost with favorite frosting.
Nellie made her home at Walker Post 1978 to 1981.

title: mexican corn dip
directions: Mix the sour cream, mayo, green chilies, corn and cheese in a bowl.
Add shots of Tabasco to taste (at least 3 to 5).
Serve with Fritos Scoops.
Yummmm!

title: glazed onions and carrots
directions: Place carrots in a large saucepan with 1-inch of boiling water.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add onions.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes longer or until just tender.
Drain and return vegetables to the pan.
Add margarine, brown sugar and ginger, stirring frequently.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes or until vegetables are glazed.
Makes 4 cups.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Beat sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs.
Dissolve the soda in the milk (soda makes the milk sour), add vanilla.
Slowly stir in flour and baking powder.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: aunt carol's date balls
directions: In large saucepan melt butter and dates.
Add eggs and sugar. Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies, vanilla, nuts and salt.
Grease hands, form into balls and roll in coconut. Chill.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with 3 strips of bacon if you like that flavor.
Pour one (8-ounce) can of tomato sauce over loaf.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: deviled crabs
directions: Mix first 5 items.
Butter individual crab-shaped Pyrex dishes or Pyrex custard cups.
Fill with crab mixture.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and top with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: pronto pups
directions: Mix.
Heat oil until hot.
Dip wieners in mixture.
Drop in oil and cook until golden brown.

title: crustless coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding flour last.
Pour into greased pie pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 325°.
Cut heat off and leave in oven another 10 minutes.
It forms its own crust.

title: muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place oven rack in the center of oven for better heat distribution.
Lightly grease or place paper baking cups in muffin tins.
In a large mixing bowl, combine egg, milk and oil.
Set this bowl aside.
In separate bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir with fork.
Make a well in the middle of dry ingredients and put wet ingredients in. Mix until moistened.
Batter should be lumpy.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan immediately. Makes 10 to 12 muffins.

title: pork fried rice
directions: In Dutch oven, cook pork chops in oil and 1/4 cup soy sauce. Remove and set aside.
Fry rice in remaining liquid.
Add more soy sauce slowly until light brown in color.
Put pork on top of rice and set aside.
Put more soy sauce in deep pan and saute coleslaw and onion powder.
Scramble eggs loosely.
Remove and chop.
Mix all together.
Serve with duck sauce and sweet and sour sauce.
Recipe may be doubled, except for eggs.

title: deer roast
directions: Place roast in large container.
Add vinegar and enough water to cover.
Soak overnight.	Drain; rinse.

title: horseradish jelly
directions: Boil sugar and vinegar 3 minutes.
Add horseradish and return to a boil.
Stir in pectin.
Bring to a boil.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir and skim.
Put jelly in hot sterilized jars and seal with wax.
Yields 3 (6 ounce) jars.

title: ham and cheese poppy seed rolls
directions: Slice entire square of rolls so that you have a top and bottom. Return bottom portion to tray. Combine other ingredients except ham and cheese. Spread mixture on bottom portion of rolls. Top with cubed ham and cheese and the top portion of rolls. Wrap in aluminum foil and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: marzetti
directions: Saute the hamburger with the onion and green pepper in the Crisco.
Make sauce with the soup, tomato paste, water, salt, pepper, oregano and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook the noodles. Grate the cheese. Alternate layers, starting with noodles, hamburger mixture, tomato sauce and grated cheese.
Grease baking dish well. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes.

title: brandy slushies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and freeze 24 hours, stirring once in a while to maintain slushy texture.
Makes 1 gallon.
But use a large container to allow room to stir.

title: gazpacho
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine olive oil, vinegar and garlic. In a food processor, mince basil and add to bowl.
Puree the vegetables in small batches and add to bowl.
Add tomato juice, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate soup for at least 4 hours before serving.
Stir soup and serve. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs until smooth. Add sugar, syrup, melted butter, chopped pecans and vanilla. Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle more pecans along top of pie and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients to soft-ball stage. Remove from stove. Add the vanilla and peanut butter. Mix well. Put pan in sink with cold water in it. Beat fudge by hand until too thick to beat. Put in buttered pan. Chill in the refrigerator. Slice and enjoy.

title: scandinavian salad
directions: Layer vegetables.
Mix liquids.
Pour mixed liquids on vegetables.
Place in refrigerator 24 hours.
Drain to serve.

title: 7 layer dip
directions: Spread the bean dip in a shallow 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix the sour cream and seasoning together.
Spread on top of bean dip. Layer lettuce, then chopped onion, green pepper, tomatoes and cheese.
Serve with Doritos.

title: golden pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Cool before cutting. Garnish with whipped cream and nuts, if desired.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sour cream, cornmeal, corn, baking powder and salt.
Add chopped peppers and half of the cheese.
Spread in well-greased baking pan (12 x 8 x 2-inch) and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Make spaghetti sauce. Layer in large casserole starting with sauce and end with sauce. Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° almost an hour or until done.
Let set awhile before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as instructed.
Pour out half of it into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Melt together caramels, butter and milk.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle with half a bag of chocolate chips.
Pour rest of batter and bake for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle rest of chocolate chips on hot cake.
Spread.

title: baked corn au gratin
directions: Put in casserole dish.
Put in dish below with water.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: christmas punch
directions: Pour orange juice, lemon juice, tea and sugar into a bottle or pitcher.
Stir these ingredients; refrigerate at least 2 hours. Also refrigerate the ginger ale and club soda.
Open can of mandarin oranges when you are ready to serve the punch.
Pour contents of can into punch bowl.
Add the juice and tea mixture to the bowl.
Stir well.
Add chilled ginger ale, club soda and the Decorative Ice Cubes.
Serve in punch cups or tall glasses. Serves 8.

title: orzo with pine nuts and basil
directions: Bring 3 quarts water to boil.
Add orzo; cook until tender, 6 to 8 minutes.
Drain thoroughly.
Place pine nuts in large dry skillet and cook, stirring, over medium heat until brown, 5 minutes.
Mix toasted pine nuts with orzo in bowl; season with salt and pepper and toss with olive oil.
Just before serving, finely chop basil and fold into orzo.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: kentucky bourbon cake
directions: Combine cherries, raisins and bourbon.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Drain fruit; reserve bourbon.
Cream butter or margarine and sugar together until light.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine 1/2 cup flour and pecans.
Sift remaining 4 1/2 cups flour, nutmeg and baking powder.
Add flour and bourbon alternately to butter mixture, beating well after each addition. Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg whites into flour mixture, soaked fruit and pecans.
Pour into 2 greased 5-inch star cake pans lined with waxed paper.
Bake 3 1/2 hours at 275°.
Ice with regular batter-sugar icing.

title: quick chicken dumplings
directions: Boil chicken.
Remove from water and cut into bite size pieces.
In water used to boil chicken add margarine, bouillon, and soup letting boil.
Meanwhile, cut biscuits into quarters, and drop into boiling mixture.
Push biscuits down into mixture.
Do not stir or they will clump.
Cover.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook until dumplings are done.
Serves 10.

title: rice pudding
directions: To cooked rice, add remaining ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven until set and brown.
Can top with meringue, if desired.
Refer to meringue recipe within this cookbook.

title: oven stew
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In roasting pan or 2 Dutch ovens, mix meat, carrots, celery, onions, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Mix flour, sugar and salt; stir into meat mixture(s).
Stir in tomatoes, water and beef bouillon.

title: basque fish soup
directions: Saute onion, celery, garlic and butter in large pan until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, wine, parsley, salt, pepper and thyme. Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
At this point refrigerate or freeze if desired, or add fish and simmer 7 to 10 minutes until fish is opaque and flakes easily with a fork.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: friendship cake - chain letter cake
directions: This is a cake that requires a starter obtained from one of your friends.
This is sometimes a mixed blessing, as it is difficult to find other people willing to keep the chain cake going.
Following are the instructions for the 30 days required to complete the task.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine; add cocoa, well beaten eggs, flour, salt and sugar.
Beat well.
Then add nuts and stir again.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Pour marshmallows over cake while still hot.

title: frozen banana smoothie
directions: In a blender container place all ingredients.
Cover; blend on high speed for 2 minutes.
Reduce speed.
Blend 1 minute longer or until frothy.
Serve immediately.
Makes about three 9 ounce servings.

title: seafood quiche
directions: Bake pie shell at 350° for 10 minutes.
Repair shell, if needed.
Beat eggs; add seasonings and milk and beat well.
Place Swiss cheese in cooled pie shell along with seafood.
Pour in egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes (golden brown on top). To reheat/serve: Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Cover bottom of casserole dish with warmed beans.
Layer on top of beans the tomatoes, sour cream, onions and olives.
Then layer shredded lettuce, another layer sour cream and avocado. Sprinkle more cheese on top and serve warm with chips.

title: broccoli-chicken divan casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender.
Drain well.
Cook chicken breasts and cut into bite-size pieces.
Spread broccoli on bottom of casserole dish.
Place chicken over this and sprinkle cheese over top.
Now add cream of celery soup mixed with water. Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until cheese melts and starts to brown.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Dissolve soda in warm water and add to mixture; add salt and flour, a little at a time.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake.

title: salted nut roll bars
directions: Heat sugar and corn syrup until dissolved and bubbly.
