Remove from heat and add peanut butter; mix well.
Add cereal and peanuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: raspberry cooler
directions: In blender combine sherbet, ice cream, syrup and milk.
Blend until smooth.
Add cream of coconut if desired.
Garnish with whole raspberries.
Makes 3 servings.

title: michigan "go blue stew"
directions: Combine last 5 ingredients.
Cut meat into 1 1/2-inch cubes into a large casserole.
Add vegetables.
Add soup mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 250° for 5 hours.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Chop and grate broccoli, onion and cauliflower.
Mix salt, sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise.
Pour over vegetables.

title: venison neck(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place neck in a roasting pan.
Add 1 1/2 inches of water into pan.
Add sliced onion and garlic. Cover.
Cook for 1 hour, then reduce heat to 350°.
Continue to cook for 4 to 6 hours, adding water if necessary, until meat falls off the bone.
Serve on hamburger or deli rolls with mustard or horseradish sauce.

title: mom's apple cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or sheet cake pan.

title: never fail meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch with 2 tablespoons cold water; add 1/2 cup boiling water and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is clear and thickens.
Remove from heat and allow mixture to cool.
With electric mixer at high, beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Set mixer on low speed and add 6 tablespoons sugar gradually.
Add salt and vanilla if desired.
Add cooled cornstarch mixture. Gradually return mixer to high speed and beat well.
Spread on pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until golden brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli 5 minutes and drain.
Cool and add eggs, mayonnaise, soup and 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Place in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and rest of cheese.
Bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cookies and cream cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions.
Fold in cookie pieces.
Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake according to package directions.
Let cool completely. Spread with Cool Whip and drizzle with chocolate syrup. Refrigerate.

title: caramel pecan cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, margarine and one egg.
Mix until crumbly.
Press gently into pan.
Beat milk, one egg and vanilla until blended.
Stir in pecans and toffee candy.
Pour over cake base in pan.
Spread, but do not stir.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Center may appear loose; let set and cool.
Yields about 36 bars.

title: chocolate velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Make paste of cocoa and vinegar and add to butter mixture.
Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and add to butter mixture, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and melt Hershey's chocolate.

title: potato casserole
directions: Pour hash browns, 1/2 cup oleo, salt, pepper, onion, chicken soup, sour cream and cheese into casserole.
Sprinkle on corn flakes and pour 1/4 cup oleo on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Chop peeled apples and set aside.
Pour oil in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and eggs and beat until creamy on low speed.
Add flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices which have been sifted together.
Mix well, then add pecans and raw apples.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in three loaf pans which have been well greased or lined with aluminum foil.

title: glazed baked ham
directions: Trim excess fat from ham.
Score top in a diagonal pattern and insert 10 cloves in gashes.
Place ham on a rack or open roaster. Bake in a preheated 325° oven about 2 hours.
Brush ham with apricot jam or preserves mixed with wine.
Bake 30 minutes longer. Brush once or twice with remaining glaze as it bakes.
Serves 10 plus.

title: grandma's potato soup
directions: Put diced potatoes and diced onion in kettle of water which 1/2 teaspoon of salt has been added.
When mixture starts boiling, add the macaroni.
Stir well when adding.
Boil until potatoes, onion and macaroni are done.
Drain water off.
Add the evaporated milk and margarine.
Just heat until warm.
Don't boil.
This has been passed on for at least 5 generations, starting with Grandma Barnett.
We all love it.

title: gumdrop bars(makes 40)
directions: Sift flour, salt and cinnamon together.
Beat eggs until light; beat in sifted sugar and milk gradually.
Add flour mixture in thirds, beating until smooth after each addition.
Add gumdrops and nuts.
Spread in greased pan; bake in a 325° oven for 35 minutes.
Cut into 4 x 1-inch bars.
Spread tops with frosting; decorate with sliced gumdrops.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Take turns holding the mixer until eggs are fluffy.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix until smooth, but do not overmix. Grease hot griddle with shortening.
Pour batter to make 4 inch pancakes.
Cook until puffed, turn and cook other side until golden brown.
We like to cut them into shapes and spread butter and jelly.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Combine melted oleo, onion, salt, cheese, eggs and broccoli. Blend and stir muffin mix in.
Pour into a greased well 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into squares. Makes 12 servings.

title: fresh peach cake
directions: Bake cake as instructed on box. After cake is done, top with jello mixed with 1 cup water, sliced peaches and lay on top of cake. Mix pudding as directed on box. Cover with peaches. Top with Cool Whip.

title: oven round steak
directions: Combine and bake at 300° until steak is tender and done.

title: new england meat pie
directions: Make and arrange pie crust.
Brown meats.
Drain excess fat. Add spices.
Mix well.
Add mashed potatoes to meat mixture until thick consistency.
Cover pie with pie crust.
Bake at 350° until pie is golden brown.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits into fourths with scissors.
Mix cinnamon and sugar in plastic bag.
Toss cut up biscuits in bag until well coated.
Layer biscuits in well-greased Bundt pan, sprinkling chopped pecans and coconut in between layers.
Melt brown sugar and butter together; boil 1 minute.
Pour over contents of Bundt pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon whippersnap cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg until thoroughly blended. Sift powdered sugar on wax paper; then drop mixture by teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar.
Roll to coat.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: lemon cream cheese pie
directions: In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water, mixing until smooth.
Cook and stir over medium-high heat until thickened and clear.
Quickly stir in egg yolks.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from the heat; stir in 1/3 cup lemon juice, salt and butter.
Cool for several hours or overnight.

title: ginger and peach chicken
directions: Spray large skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Over medium heat, cook chicken until no longer pink.
Remove from skillet; keep warm.
In 1 cup measuring cup, place reserved peach syrup (add enough water to make 1/2 cup).
Stir in cornstarch, ginger and salt.
In same skillet, cook peach syrup mixture, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add reserved chicken, water chestnuts and pea pods; heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli pieces in small amount of water until tender. Drain, leaving small amount of liquid; set aside.
Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Stir in flour and cook about 2 minutes. Add milk; stir constantly.
Add grated cheese.
Blend.
Puree half of the broccoli in blender.
Leave remaining broccoli in pieces.
Add chicken broth, all broccoli, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: pink elephant slush
directions: Mix all together; freeze 24 to 48 hours.
To serve, fill glass 1/2 to 3/4 full, then add 7-Up.

title: *no crust egg custard*
directions: Mix sugar and flour in a bowl.
Beat in eggs; add vanilla and milk.
Melt butter and add to mixture.
Pour in greased Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: oriental chicken and grapes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange chicken in large shallow baking pan, skin side up;
bake 20 minutes.
Drain excess fat, remove skin and turn chicken pieces.
In small bowl, combine mustard, soy sauce, honey and garlic powder.
Brush mixture on chicken and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake chicken 20 to 25 minutes longer or until browned, basting once during cooking.
Add grapes around and on chicken; return to oven 5 minutes longer or until grapes are heated through.
Serve with pan juices.

title: baked salmon molds
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Add enough milk to salmon liquid to make 1/2 cup.
Add salmon and remaining ingredients; mix well. Place in greased custard cups.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes. Serve with sauce, made by adding 1 cup milk to condensed mushroom soup.

title: christmas white cake
directions: Combine Brazil, walnuts, dates and cherries.
Sprinkle with flour.
Take juice from cherries and mix flour, sugar, eggs and butter.
Combine all ingredients and bake at 270 degrees for 1 1/2 hours.

title: delicious pumpkin bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt and spices together.
Cream sugar, oil and eggs in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in pumpkin.
Add flour mixture gradually, beating well after each addition.
Stir in water and pecans.
Pour into 2 well-greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 5 minutes to 1 1/4 hours, or until loaves test done.
Cool in pans for several minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: spinach salad
directions: To blender, add vinegar and onion; grind.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Refrigerate until ready to use. Remove stems from spinach and tear leaves into bite-size pieces. Add water chestnuts, bean sprouts and eggs in a large salad bowl. Toss well with dressing.
Let stand about 15 minutes before serving to let flavors blend.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Combine onion, celery, green pepper and margarine in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave, covered, at High until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: Heat oven to 300°. In an 8 x 10-inch Pyrex dish, melt 1 stick butter.
Sprinkle over butter each ingredient evenly.
Do not stir.
Pour milk over top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Cool and put in refrigerator.
Remove 1 hour before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook rice in lard until lightly browned.
Add onions, green peppers, celery, tomatoes and sugar.
Heat to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat to simmer for 25 minutes, or until rice is tender. Stir in meat; cook slowly for 10 minutes.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in pan.
Add onion, carrot and cook until soft.
Add tomatoes (not drained), all ingredients partly cover pan.
Simmer very low 40 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 450°, until golden brown, in a greased pan.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cream cheese and beat with hand beater.
Cool (leave in bowl).
Add fruit cocktail to cooled Jell-O.
Chill until thick.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into large pan or mold.
Chill until firm.
For 1 box of Jell-O, divide ingredients in half.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bring milk to boil.
Add dry ingredients, all combined.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks with 1 tablespoon water.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes longer.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown at 350°.

title: cherry chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Drain cherries, reserving juice.
Cook cherry juice with cornstarch until thickened.
Stir cherries back into thickened juice mixture.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.

title: war time candy
directions: In a heavy sauce pan mix the sugars and milk together.
Place on low to medium high heat.
Stir constantly.
Bring the contents to hard boil.
Take off heat.
Add and stir in the marshmallow fluff, peanut butter and chopped nuts mixing well.
Pour into a greased 9x12 pan.
Cut into squares and wrap in plastic wrap.

title: chicken waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended.
Garnish with shredded carrots if desired.
Serves 4.
(Other nuts may be substituted for walnuts.)

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce and spices. Simmer 40 minutes.
Boil lasagna noodles as directed on package. Layer in lasagna pan or dish as follows: noodles, meat sauce, Longhorn cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix egg yolks, Eagle Brand and lemon juice.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.

title: salsa verde
directions: Blend all items together in a blender and blend to preferred thickness.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again with baking powder and salt.
Cream the Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add extract last.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat applesauce and while hot, add to butter and sugar.
Beat in beaten eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Use a portion of flour mixture to coat chopped nuts, raisins, pineapple and cherries.
Add flour to creamed mixture.
Blend and add nuts and fruit.
Bake in a large greased tube pan at 325° about 1 1/2 hours.

title: maple syrup meatballs
directions: Combine egg and milk; stir in stuffing mix, celery, dry mustard and dash of pepper.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Add ground ham and pork.
Mix well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs.
Bake in shallow pan, 15 to 18 minutes.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze. When frozen, place in moisture proof and vapor proof containers. Seal and freeze.
Serve in sauce.

title: aunt mary's carrot salad
directions: Cook carrots to "just crisp" stage and drain; set aside. Combine in saucepan the tomato soup, vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper and cook until well blended.
In a large serving bowl, mix together all ingredients.
Serve warm or chilled to compliment your dinner.

title: microwave croutons
directions: Cook bread cubes on High for 2 minutes.
Mix together margarine, Italian seasoning and garlic salt.
Sprinkle over cubes. Cook on High for 2 minutes, stirring 2 or 3 times.
Cook on High 3 minutes until dry and crisp.

title: magic cookies
directions: Cream together and drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 325°.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, flour and salt.
Add milk and melted butter. Add flavoring.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell and bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: kellogg's corn flakes loaf
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pinto bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; drain well.
Add beans and catsup.
Pour in a casserole dish.
Mix cornbread according to package directions.
Pour on top of the beans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cornbread is done and brown.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash and sort cranberries.
Core apples and cut in quarters; also quarter orange.
Grind cranberries, apples and orange in meat grinder or food processor.
Pour into bowl and add sugar.
Mix well; refrigerate overnight.
This can be made few days ahead, as the longer it sets, the better it tastes.
This may also be frozen.

title: no-roll pie crust
directions: Sift dry ingredients directly into a 9-inch pie pan.
Mix oil and milk in a cup.
Pour over flour mixture and mix with a fork until no dry flour shows.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Prepare cake mix to package directions.
Divide cake mix batter into 30 paper lined cupcake tins.
In bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar, egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop 1 rounded teaspoonful of cheese mixture onto each cupcake.
Bake per package directions.
Frost, if desired.

title: pop overs
directions: Grease muffin pans.
Mix above ingredients and put in muffin pans.
Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 or more muffins.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, baking soda and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla with an electric mixer until well blended.
Stir in zucchini and pecans. Add dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely on a wire rack.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix altogether and put in pretty bowl; top with crushed nuts.

title: baby food plum cake
directions: Combine and bake for 1 hour at 375°.
Cool.

title: baked cauliflower and cheese
directions: Arrange cauliflower in ovenproof baking dish.
Scald milk. Combine milk with all other ingredients.
Pour over cauliflower. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Dump in pie filling; smooth out.
Dump in pineapple; smooth out.
Don't mix.
Dump in cake mix evenly.
Add nuts on top and then oleo pieces.
Bake one hour until lightly browned.

title: congo squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Add sugar and eggs to margarine.
Mix well. Sift flour and baking powder.
Stir dry ingredients into margarine mixture and mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Put in 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Slice cookie dough in 1/2-inch slices and place in pan.
Press dough together.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese (room temperature) and powdered sugar, then add thawed Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled baked cookie dough.
Arrange fruit in circles around pizza.
Mix water and preserves and brush over top of fruit; coat fruit well.
May prepare dough and cheese mixture ahead.
Two to three hours before serving, add fruit.

title: popovers
directions: Blend milk and eggs in blender.
Add butter.
Blend.
Add flour and salt.
Blend.
Don't overblend.
Pour into well-greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: oreo delight
directions: Let ice cream set out until it becomes soft and easy to work with.
Blend in Cool Whip and mix these 2 ingredients well.
In another bowl, crush the Oreo cookies into small pieces.
Add these to other mixture and mix well.
Place this in a Tupperware oblong container and place in the freezer.
Let freeze, then cut into squares and serve.

title: chicken 'n broccoli salad
directions: Melt butter in skillet over low heat.
Add chicken in single layer; pour in wine.
Place round of waxed paper over chicken. Cook, covered, until chicken is springy to the touch, 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove chicken and cover loosely; refrigerate to cool. Peel and trim broccoli stems; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Separate tops into 1/2 inch florets.
In medium saucepan, blanch broccoli in boiling water just until bright green, 30 to 40 seconds. Drain, rinse under cold running water until cool and drain well.

title: chili con queso #2
directions: Cut cheese in cubes.
Melt in microwave or double-boiler.
Add soup and milk.
Stir until well blended.

title: jalapeno corn casserole
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter until tender.
Combine rice, sauteed vegetables and rest of ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: farmer cupcakes
directions: Mix sugar and margarine well.
Add egg, then mixed cocoa and soda.
Add flour and beat well.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan or cupcake shells at 350°.
Bake cake 40 minutes and cupcakes 35 minutes. Frost with any frosting.

title: party cheese wreath
directions: Beat cheese and cream cheese with electric mixer on medium until blended.
Add juice, bell pepper, onion, Worcestershire sauce and red pepper.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight in a mold.

title: goulash
directions: Fry onion until light brown.
Add meat and cook.
Cut cheese into small pieces and add with vegetables to meat.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 3.

title: coventry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
In large bowl with mixer at medium speed, mix butter, 1 cup packed brown sugar and egg yolks until blended.
Reduce speed to low; beat in flour, buttermilk, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, vanilla extract, nutmeg and cloves until blended.
Spoon into baking dish.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix strawberries, eggs and oil.
Stir in dry ingredients, then nuts.

title: 24 hour freezer pickles
directions: You will also need clean canning jars.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix eggs and sugar well.
Pour in milk and vanilla.
Mix well. Sprinkle nutmeg on top of pie.
Bake in 9-inch pie shell in 425° preheated oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until set, not firm.
Overbaking causes filling to separate.

title: cole slaw
directions: Marinate the cabbage and carrot in the milk and sugar overnight. Drain.
Mix together the mayonnaise, buttermilk or sour cream, onion, Tabasco sauce and celery seed. Stir into slaw. Refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Combine potatoes, sour cream and butter.
Beat on low speed, then beat until light and fluffy.
Pile lightly in a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, covered, in a slow oven at 325° for 1 hour.
Toss bread crumbs in 1 tablespoon melted butter and sprinkle over potatoes. Continue baking, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: cool lemon chicken salad
directions: Mix dressing, basil, juice and peel in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, mix lightly, refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce lined platter.
Makes 4 servings.

title: squash quish
directions: Mix together and pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350 to 375° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, green pepper and onion together.
Drain off grease.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, creamed corn, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies from cake mix
directions: In a large bowl, stir in all ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop from a teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until centers of cookies are golden brown.
Edges will look darker.
Cool on cookie sheet for a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Fry sausage; drain and crumble.
Mix corn meal, flour, salt and baking powder with milk until smooth.
Stir in sausage.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: night before breakfast
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt together.
Add bread cubes, cheese and sausage to egg mixture. Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage salad
directions: In a dry frying pan toast sesame seeds, almonds, and Ramen noodles.
Set aside.
In a bowl, combine cabbage, green onions, and pineapple.
Set aside.
To make dressing, mix vegetable oil, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Combine cabbage mixture and dressing; chill.
Toss in toasted items right before serving.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Pour fruit in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly on top of fruit.
Melt margarine and pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: arroz - fried rice
directions: Rinse rice according to directions; mash garlic with 1/2 teaspoon salt to make paste.
Set aside.
Heat oil in a large pot; add rice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until lightly browned. Add onion and garlic paste.
Cook and stir until onion is tender. Add tomatoes; cook and stir until tomatoes are softened and blended into rice mixture.
Add water and 1 can tomato sauce. Cover and simmer until water is absorbed, 3 to 5 minutes.
Reduce heat to very low and steam 30 to 40 minutes until rice is tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Combine all ingredients; refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Start in a cold oven.

title: no cook pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and put in a gallon glass jar.
Make a solution of ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Finish covering with cold water; cover and let set 30 days.
Wash and slice cucumbers; add 2 cups sugar and let set 1 week.
Can or eat.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Cook onions in butter or margarine in large skillet until soft; add ground beef and brown.
Drain off grease.
Stir in tomato paste, mushrooms, 2 cups water, celery, green pepper, vinegar, salt, pepper and cheese.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and mix with sauce.
Turn into baking dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl (set aside 1/3 cup of flour to flour pastry cloth with).
Using a pastry knife, cut shortening into flour.
Add ice cold water a little at a time. If you don't sift your flour and use a pastry knife, it won't be perfect.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake at 450° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: jellied pigs feet(koseliena)
directions: Put all ingredients in pot.
Cover with water and boil until meat falls from bones.
Remove all bones.
Pour into bowl. Refrigerate until jelled.
Remove fat from top.
Invert and serve.

title: irish plum cake
directions: Cream the butter or margarine with the sugar until light and fluffy.
Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in the almond extract, syrup and ground almonds. Reserve 1/2 cup of the flour.
Sift the remainder with the baking soda and salt.
Add the flour to the butter mixture alternately with the milk, beating well after each addition.
Coat the raisins and currants with the reserved 1/2 cup of flour.
Fold them into the batter along with the grated peels.
Distribute the batter evenly in a well buttered and floured tube pan.
Bake the cake in a 300° oven for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Let it cool in the pan for 45 minutes, then remove to a wire rack to cool further.

title: cabbage stir-fry
directions: Fry ground beef and season with chicken packets from noodle packages.
Use wok or large frying pan.
Add shredded cabbage. Mix wel and cook until cabbage is wilted.
Place noodles in boiling water and cook for 5 minutes (until done) and drain.
Mix noodles with cabbage mixture and serve hot.
Sprinkle with soy sauce on top of each serving, if desired.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions. When done, place on rack and cool 4 to 5 minutes. Prick well all over cake with big fork. Stir the can of Coco Lopez cream of coconut and immediately pour over the cake. Use it all. Can make cake ahead and freeze if desired.

title: date nut roll
directions: Cut marshmallows, dates and nuts.
Mix together with milk and rolled cracker crumbs, keeping a cup or more of crumbs to roll loaf in after well mixed.

title: marie winkler's apple crisp
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender or fork.
Peel, slice and arrange apples in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan.
Crumble the crumb mixture over the apples. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or microwave on High about 20 minutes, covered, leaving small steam vent.

title: party eggs
directions: Crack eggs, pouring whites into a mixing bowl and leaving yolks in one half of each shell.
Place in an egg carton or small muffin tin to keep upright until ready to use.
Beat egg whites until stiff; season with salt and pepper.
Place toast on a baking sheet and butter.
Distribute bacon and divide the egg whites between the toast, mounding the egg whites high on each.
Make an indentation in the center of the egg whites and slip the yolks into the indentions.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes, until whites are browned and yolks are set to your preference.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon.
Add hamburg, onion and beans.
Add chili sauce, brown sugar, mustard, vinegar and salt.
Mix. Bake in a 2-quart casserole for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook and drain pasta; place in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Italian seasoning.
Add chopped onion and sausage, cut in bite-size pieces.
Add grated cheese, tossing until combined.
Oil a large baking dish.
Place pasta mixture in dish and cover with spaghetti sauce.
Sprinkle top generously with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute onions until limp.
Crush crackers. Place 1/2 crackers in casserole dish.
Alternate layers of onion and cheese. Top with crackers. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: butterscotch mallow cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together for 4 minutes.
Stir in marshmallows and bake in Bundt pan 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool cake 15 minutes on cake rack and remove from pan.

title: yum yum bars
directions: Mix together; pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill.
Cut into bars.

title: gram's wonderful salad
directions: Clean & rip lettuce - dry.
Add celery & spring onion - toss with dressing.
Put on plates and garnish with oranges and nuts in cruet or container.
Mix salad dressing and stir until the sugar is dissolved.

title: russian coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with the sour cream.
Pour 1/2 batter into well-greased tube pan, ten-inch size.
Sprinkle 3/4 of the filling and the raisins onto the batter in the pan.
Pour the remaining batter into the pan to cover the filling.
Sprinkle the remaining filling on top and bake at 350° for 45 or 50 minutes.

title: dessert or salad
directions: Mix together well. Will be ready to serve within an hour.

title: pasta-tuna salad
directions: Put the pasta in boiling water for 13 to 15 minutes; drain and set aside.
Put the oil (or butter) in a pan with the mixed vegetables over low heat.
Cover and let it simmer for 15 minutes (after 3 minutes add 3 tablespoons water and cover again).
In a salad bowl, mix mayonnaise, salt and oregano with the tuna.
Add the cooked pasta and vegetables.
Sprinkle the sliced olives on top (if desired).

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cover raisins with hot water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain; reserve 1/2 cup raisin liquid.
Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon.
Gradually add sugar to shortening in mixing bowl.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in raisins and reserved raisin liquid. Add sifted dry ingredients, rolled oats and nuts; mix thoroughly. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, until golden.
Yields 60 to 72 cookies.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until clear.
Stir in jello. Pour over sliced peaches as soon as jello is dissolved.
Put in crust.
Cool.
Top with lite Cool Whip.
For strawberry, use fresh strawberries and strawberry jello.

title: pacific lime jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in water and add juice from pineapple.
Let jell, then beat until frothy.
Fold in crushed pineapple, cottage cheese, horseradish, salad dressing and nuts.
Chill until firm and cut into squares.

title: spice tea(liquid)
directions: Boil sugar and 4 cups water.
Boil 12 cups water and tea bags. Place cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and cloves in a bag and boil. Combine all these together and cool, then add the rest of ingredients.
Makes 1 gallon.
Heat to serve.

title: sloppy franks
directions: Cover and microwave onion, green peppers and margarine in a 1-quart casserole on High until tender, 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in barbecue sauce, ketchup and franks.
Cover and microwave on High for 2 to 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir.
Cover and microwave until mixture boils.
Spoon mixture onto buns on serving plate.
Microwave, uncovered, until buns are hot.

title: classic popcorn balls
directions: Combine ingredients (except popcorn) in saucepan and cook to 270° (soft crack stage).
Pour over popcorn and mix well.
May be formed into balls or spread in 9 x 13-inch greased dish and cut into squares.

title: brown pie
directions: Saute butter and onion until onion is clear.
Add rice and stir for about one minute.
Put in casserole dish with remaining ingredients and 3/4 can of water.
Cover and cook for 30 to 45 minutes at 375°, until there is no more water.

title: tom turkey chowder
directions: Saute onions in butter in bottom of large pot.
Add potatoes, celery, water, salt and bouillon.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in milk, turkey, corn, thyme and parsley.
Heat through and serve.

title: tex-mex potato soup
directions: Chop onion into small pieces.
Lightly brown with margarine in soup pan.
Add ham chunks, chilies, salt and pepper.

title: western omelette
directions: Scramble the eggs, adding milk, if desired.
Add the chopped ham and diced onion; stir well.
Melt the butter in a 12-inch frying pan over medium heat.
Pour the egg mixture in the pan and let it cook until the eggs begin to set, about 3 to 5 minutes. Turn the eggs as neatly as you can; allow them to set and cook another 3 minutes.
Divide into 6 servings.
Serve on plain bread.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine pineapple and pudding.
Fold and whip in a large bowl. Add other ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Serves 6.

title: mexican salad
directions: Chop lettuce, tomato, onion and pepper.
Mix in chips and Ranch Style beans.
Top with cheese and dressing.
Chill 1 hour.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour and milk in a bowl.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Pour mix in baking dish; do not stir.
Add fruit, placing fruit on top of mixture; do not stir!
Bake in oven at 325° for about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: aloha cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and spread on cake and then refrigerate.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil sliced squash in salted water until tender.
Drain off water and mash.
Add grated cheese and butter, leaving out enough cheese to go on top.
Add beaten egg and milk.
Add crushed crackers to mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake in shallow casserole at 350° until set and brown.
Good!

title: soy falafel
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Press and mash the tofu.
Mix with remaining ingredients in a medium bowl.
Form into 1-inch balls. Bake on oiled baking sheet for about 30 minutes, turning occasionally until golden and crusty on the outside.
These make a great sandwich served with sliced fresh tomato in pita pockets with a sauce made of plain yogurt and fresh dill.
(Not a children's favorite!)

title: sausage and rice jambalaya
directions: Cook sausage until browned; remove drippings.
Combine ground beef, onions, green onions and bell pepper.
Cook until browned. Add tomatoes, rice, water, salt, black pepper and red pepper. Cook until rice is tender.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni as directed on package.
Mix chicken, mushrooms, mushroom soup and sour cream with Rice-A-Roni.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly on top.

title: seashell super salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss lightly.
Chill.
Serve on salad greens.
Makes 6 average servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in casserole dish.
Salt and pepper to taste. Pour soup and water over chops and mix around with spoon.
Slice potatoes and place them around chops.
Cut up onion and place around potatoes and meat.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: rolled buttermilk dumplings
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add buttermilk and mix lightly with a fork.
Turn out on a floured board.
Knead lightly 4 or 5 times and roll to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into pieces. Boil gently for 12 minutes.
Do not uncover during cooking.

title: coco casa coconut cream cake
directions: Mix cake by directions on box and bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Remove from oven and punch cake full of holes while still warm. Pour a can of coconut cream over cake, then pour a can of Eagle Brand milk over the cake.
Place cake in refrigerator until cool. After cake is cool, put large carton Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with coconut.

title: pottsfield green tomato relish
directions: Put vegetables (with skins) through grinder.
Mix together with salt and let stand overnight.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and cook 2 hours.
Seal in sterilized jars.
Makes 16 to 17 pints. (You may add more tomatoes, onions and peppers, if desired.)

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars, then add eggs and vanilla. Mix well.
Mix soda, baking powder, salt, flour and oatmeal flour together.
Add it to butter-sugar mix.
Mix all together.
Add chocolate and nuts.
Bake in oven on cookie sheet (greased) at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
(Drop dough on cookie sheet by teaspoonful size.)
Done if when flipped over, bottom is slightly tan.
Do not overbake.

title: buckeye cookies(candy)
directions: Melt chocolate bits with paraffin in a double boiler.
Mix melted butter with creamy peanut butter.
Add vanilla and confectioners sugar a little at a time.
Roll peanut mixture into small balls and use a long pronged fork to dip balls into melted chocolate just leaving the top exposed to look like a buckeye. Drain and place on wax paper to set.

title: winter warm-up
directions: Pick over lentils for stones and weed seeds.
Rinse and add to water in a crock-pot or cooking pot.
Add barley, celery, onion, potatoes, carrots, herbs and tomato paste.
Simmer until tender. Add parsley and sugar substitute.
Salt to taste.

title: graham cracker dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13 pan with whole graham crackers, not broken. Mix together box of chocolate pudding and vanilla pudding with 3 cups of milk. When

thickened, add 1 (9 ounce) container of Cool Whip into pudding. Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over graham crackers. Next, line another layer of graham crackers on top of pudding mixture. Then pour the rest of pudding mixture over graham crackers. Finally put the last container of Cool Whip over the pudding mixture. Must chill for 4 hours.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread in a small baking dish about 1/4-inch thick.
Chop artichoke and spread evenly over cheese. Drizzle margarine on top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake 10 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: lemon cheesecake bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and melted butter. Press into greased 9x13 pan. Beat cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar. Beat 5 minutes and pour over crumbs. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, 1 tablespoon of milk and sugar in a large bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup of milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk for 1 to 2 minutes (mixture will be thick).
Stir in pumpkin and spices with wire whisk.
Mix well. Spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate 4 hours until set.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch or 2 round cake pans.
Sift together the flour, sugar, cocoa and soda.
Add mayonnaise, warm water and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into pan or pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool; frost with your favorite frosting.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar in large mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition. Add milk alternately with vanilla wafer crumbs, beating well after each addition.
Stir in pecans and coconut.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for several minutes. Invert onto serving plate.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: stuffed meat loaf
directions: Mix ground meat, eggs, cracker crumbs, milk and 1/4 cup diced onion.
Add 1/2 of meat mixture to a baking pan and pat down.

title: large jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
When cooled, add the cranberry jelly*, crushed pineapple and strawberries (do not drain fruits).
Refrigerate.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Cream together the first 4 items.
Add all others and beat well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in floured and greased pan.

title: claremont salad
directions: Cut vegetables; add garlic and marinate.
Cover and refrigerate 3 days.
Mix once or twice daily.

title: pumpkin pies
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, nectar and sugar.
Beat a little.
Add 1 egg at a time.
Grease pan with Wesson oil.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: aloha bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in bananas.
Add flour, soda, baking powder, pineapple and coconut. Pour into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: strawberry banana trifle
directions: In saucepan stir sugar, cornstarch and gelatin, stir in water until smooth.
Bring to a boil, cook and stir for two minutes, or until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in strawberries and set aside.
In a mixing bowl combine milk and pudding mix.
Beat on low speed for two minutes, set aside.
Toss bananas with lemon juice, drain and set aside.
Place half of cake cubes in a trifle bowl.
Layer with half of the pudding, bananas, strawberry sauce and whipped cream.
Repeat layers.
Cover and refrigerate for at least two hours.
Garnish with the additional fruit, if desired.

title: buttermilk white cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add butter, shortening, vanilla and 3/4 cup buttermilk.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed on electric mixer.
Add remaining buttermilk and egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes more.
Bake in two greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil and drain broccoli according to package directions. Melt garlic cheese and butter in microwave. Mix soup and onion in with cheese and butter mixture. Mix with drained broccoli. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: cap'n crunch candy
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and white syrup and bring to rolling boil for 2 minutes.
Add peanut butter and when cool, pour over Cap'n Crunch cereal and mix well.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.

title: angel pie
directions: Butter and flour a glass pie plate.
Preheat oven at 275°. Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until soft peaks form. Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 cup sugar.
Beat slowly until sugar is blended.
Put in pie plate (try to form a mound with the filling, less on sides, more in middle).
Bake for 1 hour at 275°.

title: sue's spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef; add onions and peppers.
Brown a little more, then add other ingredients, except beans and mushrooms.
Cook slowly for 2 1/2 hours.
Wash and slice mushrooms and add to mixture.
Cook 1/2 hour longer.
Add beans; cook until beans are hot.
Cook spaghetti noodles with broccoli flowerets.
Serve sauce on noodles with grated sharp cheese on top.
Serve with crusty French bread and dill pickles.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt the butter; stir in flour, cheese and then milk until smooth.
Stir constantly over low-medium heat until thickened (like a white sauce) or in a microwave.
Slice potatoes fairly thin and place in a buttered baking dish.
Toss with onion.
Add the white sauce.
Bake at 375° until tender and brown, about 1 hour.
Serves 4 to 5, but is easily doubled or tripled.

title: vegetable lentil soup
directions: Dice carrots, celery and onions.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch pieces.
Mince garlic.
In 5-quart Dutch oven over medium high heat, in hot olive oil, cook vegetables until tender.
Add garlic. Cook until brown.
Stir in tomatoes, lentils, broth, potatoes and water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce to low and cover. Simmer for 50 minutes.
Thinly slice escarole.
Just before serving, stir into soup.
Cook until wilted.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by directions on box.
Mix egg (beaten), soup, mayonnaise, onion, grated cheese and chopped broccoli; salt and pepper to taste.
Take 1 stick of melted butter and mix together with 1 sleeve of crumbled soda crackers.
Spread on top of casserole and cook 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pistachio crumb cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together; beat well.
In a separate bowl mix last 3 ingredients together.
Grease tube or Bundt pan. Place 1/2 batter into pan then add 1/2 sugar mixture; add remaining batter and top with remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix together meat, oats and milk.
Form into small meatballs. Brown in margarine and place in casserole.
Mix together vinegar, sugar and sauce.
Pour mixture over meatballs.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: greek pita pizza
directions: For each 1 serving pita pizza use 1 pita.
Place on nonstick cookie sheet, flat.
Cover pita with tomato slices.
Sprinkle garlic and oregano on tomatoes.
Add desired amount of ingredients; top with Mozzarella cheese and then with crumbled Feta cheese. Bake in 400° oven for approximately 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Slice into 4 triangles.
(Not in microwave; conventional oven only.)

title: shrimp and chicken jambalaya
directions: Saute the onions in butter for 5 minutes and add the tomatoes, juice, tomato paste and water.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add the garlic, celery, bell pepper, parsley, thyme, bay leaf and cloves.
Stir well.
Add the shrimp and sausage and cook for 30 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove bay leaf and stir in rice.
Season to taste.
Gradually stir in chicken.
Bake in buttered casserole at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: strawberry margarita pie
directions: Mix pretzels, sugar and butter.
Press into 9-inch pie plate and refrigerate.
Mix condensed milk, strawberries and lime juice in large bowl until blended.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into crust.
Freeze 6 hours or overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes or until pie can be cut.
Garnish with extra whipped topping.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs for 10 minutes.
Cut in half; take the yolks.
Mix all ingredients together.
Take a spoon; put mixture back into the egg whites.

title: white whisper
directions: Serve over ice or crushed ice. Very refreshing.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: Boil ham and water 3/4 to 1 hour on simmer.
Add chicken broth and seasonings to ham and water along with chopped vegetables. Bring to a boil and then cook on low for about 45 minutes.

title: diabetic raw apple cake
directions: Cream oil, eggs and Sugar Twin.
Add dry ingredients and beat. Add apples, nuts, raisins and dates.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 350° for 40 minutes, or until done.
After a day or two, put in refrigerator, as anything that doesn't have real sugar in it will mold quickly.

title: sour cream fruit dip
directions: Combine sour cream, sugar and cinnamon. Chill.
Serve with sliced apples or other fruit.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring milk and sugar to soft ball stage.
In a warm bowl, combine peanut butter, Fluff and vanilla.
Combine both mixtures. Mix well.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth. Beat in rest of ingredients. Chill and serve with sliced fruit or graham crackers.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in bottom of soup pot.
Add onion, carrots and celery; saute over low heat until soft. Add flour and cornstarch, cooking until bubbly.
Add stock with milk and make a smooth sauce.
Next add the soda and cheese.
Cook until cheese is melted, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Add parsley a few minutes before serving.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Put undiluted mushroom soup in top of double boiler.
Heat; add cheese.
As cheese melts, stir into mushroom soup.
In the meantime, melt butter in frying pan.
Saute onions and peppers. When well sauteed, add to soup and cheese mixture.
Stir well. Stir in sea leg pieces.
Add Old Bay seasoning to taste.
If too thick, add very small amount of hot water.

title: chili crack corn
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain off excess fat.
In large gumbo pot, combine cooked meat and chili powder.
While on medium heat, stir in beans, tomatoes and water (to taste).
Bring to boil; reduce to simmer and cook for 30 minutes.
Serve over crumbled crackers and top with warmed corn.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown rice in pan with butter; do not overcook.
Add onions and green peppers.
Mix cumin, garlic, salt and pepper in water thoroughly and add to rice.
Then add stewed tomatoes and simmer until most of liquid is absorbed.

title: caesar's salad
directions: Dressing:
My favorite is Julie's Royal Caesar's Dressing available at Safeway, produce department.

title: turtles
directions: Melt caramels with cream.
Add pecans.
Stir until well mixed. Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet. Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Spread over top of caramels.

title: strawberry mint jam(makes five 8-ounce jars)
directions: Measure berries into bowl.
Add mint; mix.
Mix sugar into fruit; let stand 10 minutes.
Add lemon juice to pectin in small bowl.
Stir in fruit.
Continue stirring 3 minutes.
Ladle into hot, scalded containers.
Cap tightly.
Stand at room temperature for 24 hours, then freeze.
Keeps in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a round Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: cajun burgers
directions: Combine the first 10 ingredients; mix well.
Form into patties; broil, fry or grill to desired doneness.
Toast buns. Top each burger with a slice of tomato, avocado and dollop of sour cream.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In greased casserole dish, mix the first 4 ingredients.
Lay chicken pieces on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine and add cocoa. Add remaining ingredients and blend well. Bake in unbaked pie crust at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: snickers bars
directions: Melt caramels with water and butter.
Add peanuts.
Melt chips and shortening.
Divide in half and put half mixture in 8-inch buttered foil pan.
Cool.
Top with caramel mixture and then remaining half of chocolate mixture.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken breasts in polynesian sauce(lo-cal)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Trim
and
fringe fat, if any, from chicken.
Arrange chicken breasts,	skin side up in a shallow, nonstick pan.
Bake, uncovered,
to 25 minutes, until skin is crisp and well rendered
of fat.
Drain and dissolve melted fat in the pan.
Combine
remaining
ingredients;	spoon
over chicken breasts.
Cover the pan loosely with foil.	Lower oven temperature to 350° and bake
an
additional 25 to 30 minutes, until chicken is done and
sauce	is thick.
Makes 8 servings, 215 calories each.

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Cut slice from top of bread loaf; cut in bite-size pieces. Remove center of loaf and cut in bite-size pieces.
Saute celery and onions in butter until tender.
Add cheese and stir over low heat until melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients thoroughly. Stir constantly.
Spoon into bread shell.
Serve with vegetables and bite-sized bread cubes.
Makes 2 cups.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients until smooth and well mixed.
Add crabmeat or imitation seafood.
Serve with crackers or a veggie tray.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Stir together flour, pudding mix and baking powder.
Combine eggs, milk and margarine.
Add to dry ingredients; mix well. Spread in a greased 8 x 8
x2-inch dish.
Drain peaches, reserving 1/3 cup liquid.
Chop peaches and sprinkle on top of batter.
Beat together the cream cheese, 1/2 cup sugar and reserved peach liquid.
Pour on top of peaches.
Combine 1 tablespoon sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Using a wooden spoon, blend cream cheese, egg, sugar and salt.
Carefully fold in chocolate chips; set aside. Combine dry ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Fill cupcake papers 3/4 full. Drop 1 heaping tablespoonful cream cheese mixture into center of each.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: eskimo cookies
directions: Place margarine in bowl to soften to room temperature.
Stir in the rest of the ingredients.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
May be placed in refrigerator to firm, if desired.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 15 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Serve warm with raw vegetables or crackers.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes; drain very well.
Pat dry.
Measure 3 cups grated potatoes and combine with onion, eggs, flour, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
In a large skillet, slowly heat oil (1/8-inch deep) until very hot, but not smoking.

title: orange supreme(diet)
directions: Boil water, Jell-O and cream cheese together.
Remove from heat and beat with mixer until cheese melts.
Add ice cubes.
Beat whipping cream with mixer until firm.
Add Equal and almond extract.
Continue beating.
Pour into dish and chill until firmly set.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in saucepan on medium-high heat until it comes to a boil.
Cook to soft ball stage and remove from heat. (Soft ball stage is when a drop of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into a cup of cool water.)
Add peanut butter and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into a buttered pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: mexican casserole dish
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet.
Layer 3 times in casserole dish in this order: Doritos, enchilada sauce, meat, corn, beans and water.
Pour soups (do not add water) over top.
Cook, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, then add grated cheese and return to oven until cheese has melted.

title: deluxe pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Then mix in next five ingredients.
Stir in nuts and pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Should be less set in center than edge.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables (corn, beans, peas and pimento).
Mix and toss lightly with onion, green peppers and place in casserole.
Combine salt, pepper, vinegar and oil in small saucepan.
Heat over medium-low heat until boiling, stirring frequently.
Heat 2 minutes.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate and serve after 24 hours.
Great for large gatherings.

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Remove seeds from all peppers; run peppers through blender until all juiced.
Slowly boil peppers, vinegar, and sugar 10 minutes. Remove from heat, add pectin.
Boil hard for 1 minute.
May also add green food coloring.
Pour into clean sterilized jars and cook in water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 5 1/2 pints.

title: stuffed peppers(for freezing)
directions: Grease large skillet with butter.
Add tomato paste and cheese to hamburger.
When
cheese
is melted, add cooked corn and peas (these should
be
cooked
dry).
Pour cooked rice in last.
If mixture is dry, add liquid from vegetables.

title: soda bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients and scallions; mix oil and buttermilk well.
Slowly add liquid until it forms a ball.
Remove dough; knead 3 or 4 minutes until smooth.
Form into 2 round loaves. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mom's yummy breakfast
directions: Cook sausage in skillet until color changes, but do not brown. Drain.
In a 9 x 14 x 2-inch baking dish, place bread in bottom. Sprinkle meat on bread, then cover with cheese.
Combine eggs and milk; pour over cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
In the morning, bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven until set and light brown.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Roll chicken in flour, brown in butter; set aside.
Mix soup, seasonings, water and drippings into pot.
Cook and stir to a boil. Spread Minute Rice into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour all but 1/2 cup soup mixture over rice and stir to moisten.
Top with chicken and rest of soup mixture.
Bake, uncovered at 375° for 30 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onion together.
Add other ingredients; cook until done.
Best to simmer on low for about 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts.
Set aside.

title: italian potato salad(insalata di patate)
directions: From my mother-in-law, Evelyn Campanelli.

title: kids super supper
directions: Saute onion and margarine until tender.
Add hot dogs; brown lightly.
Reduce heat; add soup, cheese and water.
Cook over low heat until well blended and cheese is melted.
Stir in pasta which has been cooked according to package directions.
Serves 6.

title: golden brown oven chicken
directions: Mix
the
first
six
ingredients well.
Crush stuffing mix. Dip
chicken breasts or tenders in mixture made from the first
6 ingredients.
Roll
chicken
in stuffing mix.
Place chicken
in lightly greased baking dish.
Spoon melted margarine
over chicken and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes for chicken tenders or 1 hour for larger pieces.

title: country style scalloped corn
directions: Melt butter and beat eggs.
Drain the whole kernel corn. Combine all ingredients together, adding the muffin mix last. Pour mixture into a greased 7 x 11-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serves 10. (May spoon batter into muffin pan cups
Bake 20 minutes or until golden brown and toothpick inserted comes clean.
Immediately remove muffins from pan.
Makes 12 muffins.)

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: First boil vinegar, sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.
After mixture has cooled, pour over the remaining ingredients.
Put all in a gallon jar and age for 7 days, then they are ready for eating.

title: bean soup
directions: Cook beans with onion, bell pepper and Ro-Tel tomatoes until tender.
Cook hamburger meat, drain and add to soup.
Add chili powder and garlic salt as needed.
Add 1/2 cup of tomato sauce if needed.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine raisins, water and lemon juice in pan; bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Add enough juice from raisins to make a smooth paste.
Add to raisins and cook, stirring constantly, until clear and thickened.
Add butter and
cool.
Pour into a 9-inch pastry shell.
Adjust top crust.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade bisquick mix
directions: Mix and store in icebox.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all together; shake well.
Great on cole slaw or green salad.

title: butterfly shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp, split but don't cut all the way.
Wash and dry with towel.
Cut bacon into 3 pieces.
Spread shrimp open and place bacon on top.
Warm skillet.
Dip shrimp in eggs, place in skillet (bacon side down).
Brown until crisp and turn until done. Remove.
Saute onion for several minutes; add seasoning and broth.
Cover and cook 3 minutes.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Pour gravy on shrimp and top with spring onions and cracked almonds. Do not overcook shrimp.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix Bisquick, cheese and sausage.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° first 15 minutes and at 325° for 2nd 15 minutes.

title: joy lange's frosting
directions: Cream all ingredients together.
Will keep in a covered container (if you hide it from your husband) in the refrigerator at least a month.

title: tangy grilled sirloin
directions: Combine all ingredients except steak in small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Place steak on grill over medium coals.
Grill steak 16 to 20 minutes for rare to medium, turning once.
Brush cooked side frequently with sauce. Carve steak into thin slices and serve with remaining sauce.

title: spinach squares
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except rolls.
Mix well.
Unroll crescent rolls, but do not separate.
Press them onto bottom of a 9 x 13-inch buttered baking pan.
Press the seams together.
Spread the spinach mixture over the dough.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Serves 48 squares. Approximate calories per serving:

title: english muffins
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cool scalded milk to lukewarm. Add 1 cup water, salt, sugar, yeast and 2 cups flour.
Beat well. Let rise, covered, until doubled in bulk.
Add slightly softened shortening and remaining flour.
Beat and knead thoroughly.
Let rise again until double in bulk.
Place on floured board or use corn meal.
Flatten to 3/4-inch thickness and cut with 2 1/2-inch cutter.
Bake 15 minutes on hot griddle (not buttered) turning once or twice.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; set aside.
Mix the remaining ingredients; add to the first set.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 325°. Store tightly covered.

title: chad's ants on a log
directions: Clean celery and cut into 2-inch lengths.
Put Cheez Whiz in celery.
Line raisins on top.

title: potatoes stuffed with sour cream and cheese(microwave)
directions: Pierce each potato skin in several places with a fork.
Put the potatoes in a dish and cook at 100% for 7 to 9 minutes. Halfway through time, turn dish 1/2 turn.
Cut a thin slice off top of each potato.
Hollow out potato, leaving 1/4-inch layer lining the skin side.
In a bowl, combine potato pulp with butter, egg yolk and sour cream and mix well.
Stuff potatoes with the mixture; sprinkle with the Cheddar cheese.
Cook at 100% for 3 to 5 minutes, giving dish 1/2 turn halfway through cooking time.
Let stand for 2 minutes.

title: the bread of fulfillment
directions: Beat the broken eggs with rotary beater of relinquishment until all identity is lost in lightness.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well with the arm of persistence.
Pour into earthen vessel of self.
Bake in a moderate oven of patience.
Do not open to check baking process.
Trust the automatic heat control of God's timing. When well done, remove from the vessel of self and serve every crumb to your neighbor.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put beef meat in bottom of pan.
Wrap 1 chicken piece in 1 piece bacon and put on top of meat.
Heat mushroom soup and pour over.
Cook in oven at 250° for 3 1/2 hours.

title: noodle roni parmesano with chinese sausage
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups hot water, milk and margarine.
Bring just to a boil.
Add pasta, contents of seasoning packet and Chinese sausage.
Reduce heat to medium.
Boil, uncovered, stirring frequently, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add sugar peas.
Stir before serving.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Soften the Philly and fold in the cranberry, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: herbal vinegar
directions: Shake the vinegar plus one of the other ingredients; refrigerate 4 days.
Strain.
You may add a sprig of fresh dill or mint if appropriate.
Bottle and refrigerate.
Use to make salad dressing and marinades.

title: sherry wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Beat for 5 minutes. Pour into a greased Bundt pan or angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before removing from pan. Dust with powdered sugar, or frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: chicken tacos
directions: Cover chicken with water.
Add peppercorns, 1/2 small onion (sliced) and 1 bay leaf.
Bring to boil and simmer 45 minutes. Remove chicken, debone and shred.
Retain broth.
In large skillet, saute garlic and diced onion in oil until tender.
Add oregano, cumin, green chiles and tomatoes with chicken broth and shredded chicken.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: good corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Then stir well; return to oven.
Reduce heat to 325° and cook approximately 35 minutes more.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, put in a 9 x 13-inch dish and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade potato salad dressing
directions: Mix egg and sugar together in small saucepan.
In a one cup measuring cup combine cold water, vinegar and cornstarch.
Mix until cornstarch is dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1 teaspoon margarine and 1 teaspoon mustard.

title: ruth's green tomato pickles
directions: Mix together.
Cook on medium heat for 40 minutes.
Fill and seal jars.

title: cheese pennies
directions: Mix margarine and cheese; blend in flour, cereal and salt by hand.
Form into balls the size of a quarter and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: in the pan chocolate cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and cocoa together in a 9 X 13 ungreased cake pan. Make 3 holes in middle of mixture. Hole #1 put vinegar. Hole #2 put oil. Hole #3 put vanilla. Pour cold water over all. Mix all together well. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve plain or with frosting.

title: cheese-topped vegetable supper
directions: About 1 hour before serving, cut broccoli into 3 x 1-inch pieces. Cut squash lengthwise in half and discard seeds.
Cut each squash half crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Cut off peel. Cut onions crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Separate into rings. Slice cheese into 1/4-inch thick slices.

In a 12-inch skillet over high heat, in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook broccoli, stirring quickly and frequently, about 5 minutes or until broccoli begins to brown. With slotted spoon, remove broccoli to large bowl.
In the same skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon hot salad oil, cook squash slices, turning them occasionally until they begin to brown, about 5 minutes. Remove to bowl with broccoli.

In the same skillet over medium heat in 2 tablespoons hot salad oil, cook onions and salt 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in sugar. Cook about 5 minutes or until onions are browned and very tender. To onions in skillet, add broccoli, squash and 1/2 cup water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 minutes or until broccoli and squash are tender.
Tuck cheese slices among vegetables. Cover and cook 5 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix pie filling and Eagle Brand together. Fold in whipped topping, marshmallows and nuts, if desired. Refrigerate overnight.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter or margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Blend milk and vanilla.
Thoroughly stir together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt; stir into cream mixture. Blend in chopped nuts.
Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Place balls 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Lightly flatten balls with sugar and cinnamon bottom of tumbler.
Bake cookies at 375° until done, 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen.

title: icebox nut cake
directions: Heat milk and melt marshmallows.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs to make batter.
In a large separate pan, mix fruit and raisins.
Pour batter over this and mix well.
Then, last mix in nuts.
Mix well.
Work by hand.
Pack in pans lined with wax paper.
Pack well. Put in refrigerator overnight. Turn out of pans next day and wrap in heavy Reynolds Wrap.
Put in freezer or refrigerator.
Keep in refrigerator after removing from freezer. Can keep 1 year or longer if frozen.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix thoroughly; add tears of joy, sorrow and sympathy.
Flavor with love and kindly service.
Fold in 4 cups prayer and faith. After pouring all this into daily life, bake well with the heat of human kindness and serve with a smile, anytime.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries and mix with marshmallows and sugar.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, chop the apple and cut white grapes in quarters.
Mix all this and nuts and whipping cream with ingredients from the night before.

title: green macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook broccoli and put in food processor.
On low heat, melt cheese, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli and rest of ingredients.
Mix well and serve as a colorful side dish.

title: mexican bean bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough into two long rectangles. Place in ungreased, 11 x 7-inch, glass baking dish.
Press onto bottom and 1/2 inch up sides to form crust.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: fruit roll(no cooking)
directions: Mix in large bowl; shape in rolls and roll in graham cracker crumbs from 15 additional crackers.
Roll in foil and store in refrigerator.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend cake mix, sour cream, oil, sugar, water and eggs.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour 2/3 of batter in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.

title: oriental broccoli salad
directions: Chop broccoli.
Combine juice, vinegar and salad dressing mix. Mix well.
Add oil and soy sauce; mix well.
Pour dressing mixture over chopped broccoli and sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate mixture overnight to achieve best flavor.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Cube cheese; melt in double boiler over low heat.
Add milk and blend.
When cheese is fully melted, mix in tomatoes and chili.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix egg, mayonnaise and mustard in large bowl; beat well.
Add milk and Old Bay; mix well.
Fold in onion powder and Italian bread crumbs.
Mix well, then add 1 pound of crabmeat.

title: zesty steamed carrots and red potatoes
directions: Place a steamer rack in a 4-quart saucepan over 1-inch water (water should not touch bottom of rack). Bring water to boil. Arrange potato slices in bottom of steamer. Cover and steam for 10 minutes. Add carrot slices; cover and steam until vegetables are just tender, about 7 to 10 minutes longer. Remove vegetables to serving bowl. Add remaining ingredients; toss gently to coat evenly. Enjoy.

title: johnny cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo and add to beaten eggs.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Roll in wax paper and place in refrigerator.
Slice and bake.
(Slice thin for crisp cookies or slice thick for chewy cookies.)

title: holiday butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and milk.
Add vanilla.
Combine flour to baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Roll out on floured area and cut with favorite cookie cutters.
Decorate with icing when cool. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Place sliced apples in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: quick beefaroni casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute meat, onions, green pepper, mushrooms and olives in margarine for ten minutes.
Add Beefaroni and sour cream; mix well.
Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Garnish with olive and mushroom slices if desired. Serves four to six.

title: chip's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients; simmer for a few hours until flavors combine and it reaches desired consistency.

title: tyresha's tangerine punch
directions: Combine chilled ingredients in the punch bowl.
Drop in the vanilla ice cream by tablespoons.
Stir thoroughly.
Ladle into the punch cups and serve at once.
Garnish with tangerine slices.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, soups and egg.
Begin with 1 layer of noodles and place diced chicken on top.
Add soup mixture, then cheese.
Repeat layer.
Add 1/2 cup milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: two bean chicken salad
directions: Trim green beans; cut diagonally into thirds.
In a medium saucepan bring water to a boil.
Add greens; bring water to a second boil.
Boil 3 minutes.
Drain; immediately plunge into ice water to chill.
Drain thoroughly.
In a large bowl combine green beans, garbanzo beans, chicken and tomato; mix lightly.
Add dressing; toss lightly.
Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 4 one-half cup servings (440 calories).

title: mayonnaise cake(rich chocolate)
directions: Stir to blend.
Beat until smooth. Bake in Bundt cake pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 325° to 350°.

title: refrigerator bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice onions and peel on cucumbers.
Mix onions and cucumbers with salt and let stand 2 hours.
Drain for 15 to 20 minutes. Combine sugar, vinegar and celery seed and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Mix well.
Put in jars and refrigerate.
They are ready to eat the next day.
Will keep up to 6 months in the refrigerator.

title: brown oatmeal buns
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal; cool until lukewarm.
Add oil, brown sugar and salt.
Add softened yeast.
Add 4 to 4 1/2 cups flour and knead, using remaining flour.
Put into greased bowl; let rise until double.
Punch down; form into 24 small buns on greased cookie sheet (11 x 16-inch size pan).
Let rise again. Bake at 375° for about 15 minutes, or at 350° for about 20 minutes, until golden on top.

title: spanish-style fillets
directions: Combine onion, garlic and oil in a bowl; cover and microwave at High for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in cornstarch, chili powder and tomatoes; cover and microwave at High 3 to 3 1/2 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in olives and chiles. Spoon half of sauce into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange snapper fillets over sauce with thickest portions to outside.
Drizzle lemon juice over fish; sprinkle tops with salt.
Top fish with remaining sauce.

title: savory cheese bread(microwave)
directions: Combine milk and butter in a 2-cup glass dish.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and yeast in large mixing bowl.
Add milk mixture and egg.
Mix 2 tablespoons of soup mix and 1/4 cup cheese in small bowl; set aside.
Add remaining soup mix and cheese to batter.
Divide batter evenly between 2 well-greased 8 x 4-inch microproof loaf pans.
Sprinkle with reserved onion-cheese mixture.

title: mrs. field's cookie recipe
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together the flour, oatmeal (put small amounts of oatmeal into blender until it turns to powder), salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all those ingredients and add chocolate chips, Hershey candy bar (grated) and chopped nuts.

title: taco and corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown ground beef or sausage in large skillet and drain off fat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of water, seasoning mix and tomato sauce; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Pour meat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Gently mix in tortilla chips and corn.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake 20 minutes.

title: rice krispies
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows in saucepan.
Add Rice Krispies; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth out; cut into squares (butter pan).

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in oven at 350° for 35 minutes in a casserole dish until golden brown.
Serve with Doritos or assorted crackers.
You may add shrimp, oysters or crabmeat.

title: crab salad
directions: Cook rotoni in 2 tablespoons oil and 1 teaspoon salt; drain. Mix with remaining ingredients and chill in refrigerator overnight.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Cook hamburger in a skillet. Drain while running hot water over hamburger. Place hamburger in a small stockpot with water, corn, green beans, peas, carrots, onion and potatoes. Season, using equal amounts of salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Simmer for 1 hour or until carrots are done to liking.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish (2-quart).
Mix flour, milk and sugar thoroughly.
Pour batter into dish over melted butter.
Pour drained fruit over batter and top with pineapple chunks.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with milk or ice cream.

title: silvia's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan or decorative cake mold.
In a large bowl, beat butter or margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla and eggs; beat until blended. Blend in cake flour and baking powder gradually.
Stir into sugar mixture alternately with milk.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Smooth top.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.
Place cooled cake top side down on a platter dusted with powdered sugar.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil peeled potatoes until almost tender.
Put potatoes in casserole dish.
Saute bacon, onion and butter and then put over potatoes.
Pour sour cream over bacon and then sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: betty's election day liver spread
directions: Leave the braunschweiger and cream cheese at room temperature for about hour so it's soft enough to mash together.
Add remaining ingredients and mold in container.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: curried chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: christmas rocks
directions: Cream butter, eggs and sugar; mix altogether.
Drain green cherries but use liquid of red cherries.
Drop by tablespoonfuls on cookie sheet that has been sprayed with cooking oil.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Melt butter in a large bowl, then add confectioners sugar and milk. Stir. Add chocolate chips, then stir and add marshmallows. Microwave for about 7 minutes, then stir in peanut butter. Put in a 13 x 9-inch aluminum foil lined pan.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into muffin paper cups set in muffin pans.
Freeze.
Remove to plastic bags for storage.
Peel off paper few seconds before serving.
May be used for a dessert!
Serves 12.

title: sourdough starter
directions: In large glass or pottery bowl combine yeast, sugar, salt and flour.
Gradually add water, while beating, until smooth.
Cover with plastic wrap or a damp cloth and let stand 2 days at room temperature.
Beat before using.
After using, add 1 cup each flour and warm (not hot) water to remaining starter and beat until smooth.
Store in refrigerator in a large glass jar or crock with a tight-fitting lid, allowing room for expansion.

title: oatmeal raisin spice cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat margarine and sugar until creamy. Add eggs, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt and mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts and mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies or 12 to 13 minutes for crispy cookies.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack or wax paper.
