title: party hot dish
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
This can be mixed in advance and kept in refrigerator overnight.
If you do this, add the almonds just before putting in the oven.

title: excellent pie crust
directions: Mix Wesson oil, milk and flour.
Add salt.
Roll out between two pieces of wax paper.
Lay in pie pan for baking.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients, except coloring, in pot.
Cook at medium heat 5 to 7 minutes.
Divide into as many parts as you want colors.
Add unsweetened Kool-Aid, one package to each part dough, or food coloring, to desired coloring.

title: sausage bread
directions: Chop bell pepper and onion.
Brown with sausage; drain.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Arrange by layers in greased Bundt pan, first biscuits, second sausage mixture and third cheese.
Continue in layers until all ingredients are used, ending with biscuits. Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool 15 minutes before removing from Bundt pan.

title: caesar's fish
directions: Arrange fillets in a single layer in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Drizzle with dressing; sprinkle with cracker crumbs. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Top with cheese and bake 5 more minutes or until fish flakes with a fork.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Mix pie crust mix, dill weed, water and mustard until pastry forms a ball.
Divide into halves.
Roll one half into rectangle, 15 x 8-inches on lightly floured cloth-covered surface.
Arrange 1 package of ham over rectangle to within 1/2-inch of edges.
Roll up tightly, beginning at 15-inch side.
Pinch edge of pastry into roll to seal well.
Cut into 15 (1 inch) slices.
Place slices, cut sides up, 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat with remaining pastry and ham. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until pastry begins to brown.
Garnish with sprigs of fresh dill if desired.
Serve warm.

title: jan's meat stock
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pan and bring to a boil. Turn heat down and simmer for 2 hours.
Skim off fat, strain broth. (May be used for soups or stews or eaten like it is.)
Save meat for other uses.
Will keep in fridge up to a week.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs and margarine; pat firmly on bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Add condensed milk; beat until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
In small bowl, toss together 1/2 cup chips with flour to coat; stir into cheese mixture.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips evenly over top.
Bake 1 hour, or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool to room temperature.
Chill.
Remove sides of pan. Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: apple jack for apple pie
directions: Heat water, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg until very hot and sugar is dissolved.
Dissolve cornstarch in small amount of cold water.
Add to other mixture and cook until very thick.
Cool in refrigerator.
Add apples to cool mixture.
Use these apples for apple pie.
Apple Jack is best when you prepare the day before.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage and crumble.
Spread crescent rolls in bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle sausage on top, then tomato, onion, then cheese.
Top with raw eggs.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 minutes.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans; place in large kettle.
Cover with water (2 inches); stir in 2 tablespoons salt and the baking soda.
Soak overnight.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar, cocoa, milk and salt.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in peanut butter and rolled oats.
Then drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, rice (1/2 flavored package optional), soup mix, soup, water (I mix soup and water together before adding to mixture).
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Add crushed Cheez-Its to top and generously sprinkle with cut up butter.
Bake for another 20 minutes or so until butter and Cheez-Its are crisp.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Melt butter and combine with remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle on top of potato mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat eggs.
Lightly mix ingredients.
Cook on hot grill, slightly buttered.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Put pretzels, oleo and sugar into baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Seal edges so Jell-O doesn't soak through.
Mix Jell-O, hot water and frozen berries.
Pour over mixture and refrigerate until thickened.

title: banana cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Great for overripe bananas.

title: persimmon fruit salad
directions: Combine fruits and nuts, stirring gently.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour over fruit mixture.
Toss lightly. Chill for 1 or 2 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: breakfast egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown the sausage and drain off fat.
Beat the eggs and then add all remaining ingredients.
Top with the bread.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.

title: no cook fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Mix sugar and cocoa together.
Mix wet and dry ingredients together.
Stir in nuts and vanilla. Spoon into pans and refrigerate.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter and add unbeaten egg.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with applesauce and raisins.
Bake in greased tube pan (or 2 loaf pans) at 350° for about one hour, (less if in loaf pans).

title: annabel's special k cookies
directions: Bring to a boil, sugar and syrup.
Add peanut butter and cereal.
Press into 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Melt together and spread over top the chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.

title: sugar cookies(recipe used at umw luncheon)
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add cooking oil, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients, a little at a time.
Make into small balls and press.
Decorate with colored sugars if desired.
Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes (do not overbake).

title: ice cream pie
directions: Combine ice cream (soften), cream cheese (soften), marshmallow cream and whipped cream.
Stir together until ingredients are all the same color.
Pour into pie crust.
Put into freezer for 2 hours.
Ready to eat.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and shortening.
Mix in salt and flour and knead for 2 minutes.
Let rise for 1 hour. Roll 1/4 inch thick and cut into triangles.
Fry in fat heated to 420°.

title: mom's apple kuchen
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to liquid mixture at one time.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with sliced apples, overlapping slices.
Press apples slightly into dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar (if desired) and dot with butter.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water, salt and butter together to boiling point.
Add flour all at once and remove from heat.
Stir constantly until mixture leaves side of pan.
(Forms a ball).
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Add eggs one at a time, beating each in thoroughly, before adding the next.
Drop by tablespoons a little distance apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake in hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes longer.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn and flour.
Add remaining ingredients ending with beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Pour into a 2 quart casserole and bake in 350 degree oven about 45 to 60 minutes.

title: texas brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt in double boiler or Teflon pan the margarine and cocoa.
Mix in bowl the eggs, salt, sugar and flour. Add melted margarine and cocoa and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 10 x 14-inch greased pan.
Do not overbake.
Spread on package of miniature marshmallows over top of brownies and return to oven for 5 minutes with oven off.

title: sweet sour slaw
directions: Cut cabbage in fourths, remove cores, slice and grate in food processor.
Clean carrots and grate by hand.
Clean and cut green pepper into thin strips and cut in small pieces.
Cut celery into thin strips and cut into small pieces.
Cut onions into small pieces and mush in food processor.
(You will never see onions in slaw.)
Mix well together.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Arrange in serving dish, add to lettuce in layers:

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix egg, shortening and milk thoroughly.
Combine mixtures, stirring just enough to dampen flour.
Add blueberries.
Put cupcake papers in muffin pan and fill 2/3 full.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and cut cauliflower into pieces.
Drain; rinse and drain peas.
Combine well drained vegetables with Colby cheese chunks in bowl.
Sprinkle dry dressing mix over top of cauliflower, peas and cheese.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Just before serving, stir in Miracle Whip until all is covered.
Salad is ready to serve.

title: spinach and beef dip
directions: Combine spinach, cream cheese, mayonnaise, milk and dried beef; mix thoroughly.
Stir in sour cream or yogurt, onions, garlic and dill until well blended.
Serve with vegetables or chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat eggs and vanilla.
Add pumpkin and mix well.
Add dry ingredients, carrots and raisins.

title: cherry pudding delight
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, break up cake in 2-inch pieces to cover bottom. Pour prepared pudding over cake.
Dab cherry pie filling evenly over pudding.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together and shape into small balls. Place in a 3-inch baking dish.
Cover with barbecue sauce and bake about 1 hour at 375° until sauce is thick.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes
directions: Cut the tops off the tomatoes and with a small spoon, gently scoop out about 1/2 of the pulp.
Salt lightly and turn upside down on a paper towel.
Mix together tuna, celery, onion and mayo to taste.
Fill the tomatoes with the tuna mixture.

title: sugar-free peanut butter candy
directions: Cream peanut butter with 1 tablespoon milk.
Add raisins and mix well.
Break graham cracker into small pieces and mix with other ingredients.
Add sweetener and vanilla.
Form mixture into 6 balls of candy.

title: pecan pie(grandmother's)
directions: Mix brown sugar with milk, then add butter, egg and vanilla. Add pecans.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 350° for 25 minutes.

title: skiers french toast
directions: Bring the ingredients to a boil.
Grease 9 x 13-inch pan and put above caramel in bottom.
Cut Texas toast (4 strips per slice).
Put close together on top of sauce.
Beat together topping and pour on top of bread.

title: poor man's cakes(fattigmann)
directions: Spread flour in flat ring on counter.
Add sugar, eggs, cooled butter and cardamom in the middle of the flour.
Knead until smooth; lots of kneading makes it better.
Place in refrigerator for an hour or overnight.
Remove a portion of dough and roll to a pie crust thickness.
Cut in diamond shapes and make a slit in the center; pull one end through the slit.
Deep fry in hot oil.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: caraway bacon rice
directions: Cook bacon in a large skillet over low heat until crisp. Drain.
Add 1 tablespoon bacon grease to skillet.
Add onion to skillet and cook until soft.
Add green pepper and garlic.
Cook until pepper is crisp-tender.
Stir in rice, sauerkraut and caraway seed.
Heat thoroughly.
Add crumbled bacon and season to taste.
Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix together in mixer. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: summer surprise dessert
directions: In shallow 9 x 12-inch glass dish, combine all fruit and mix well.
Sprinkle brown sugar over fruit.
Top with sour cream. Cover with plastic wrap; refrigerate 3 to 4 hours or overnight. The sour cream will seep through the brown sugar to the fruit.
To serve, gently stir the fruit; spoon into sherbet glasses.

title: pasta and bean soup
directions: In 3 quart sauce pan combine tomatoes, snappy tomatoes, beef stock, lemon juice, garlic, onion, cumin, tobasco sauce and basil. Simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in beans and green pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add cooked macaroni and heat through.
Note:
1 cup = 98 calories, 1 gram fat and 18 grams carbohydrates.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time; do not overbeat.
Add vanilla and flour; mix well. Add sour cream and mix again.
Grease a 10-inch spring-form pan and sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.

title: chewy raisin walnut shortbread bars
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Using pastry blender or fork, cut in butter until mixture resembles fine meal.
Press into greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Meanwhile combine eggs, brown sugar and vanilla; beat well. Stir in baking soda, walnuts, raisins and coconut.
Spoon over hot crust evenly.
Return to oven; bake an additional 20 to 25 minutes or until top is set.
Careful not to overcook.
Cool completely. Cut into 20 bars.

title: crock-pot beef stew
directions: Put in large crock-pot in order given.
Start out on high until it boils, then cook on low the rest of the time.
Cook 10 hours. Do not stir until done.
May put it on in evening and let cook all night.

title: pumpkin fudge
directions: Butter or grease 1 (8 x 8-inch) pan. In a 3-quart saucepan, mix together sugar, milk, corn syrup, pumpkin and salt. Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to medium and continue boiling; do not stir.

title: quick sourdough french bread
directions: In large bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Blend.
Add water and sour cream to flour mixture.
Blend and stir in 2 to 2 1/2 cups flour until dough pulls away from the side of the bowl.
On floured surface, knead in remaining 1 cup flour until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl; cover loosely with plastic wrap.
Let rise in warm place until doubled (about 25 minutes).

title: butterscotch topping
directions: Cook all together for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Store in cool place.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter with a fork until it becomes crumbly.
Put 1/4 cup of this mixture aside.
Place remaining mixture in the bottom of an unbaked pie shell.
Cook this in a 350° oven until pie shell becomes brown.
Remove from oven.
Pour the cooked vanilla pudding into the pie shell.
Sit in refrigerator and cool completely.
Top with a 12 ounce box of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with 1/4 cup of mixture that you had put aside.
Keep pie refrigerated until ready to use.

title: plain biscuits
directions: Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together in a large bowl.
Put shortening into flour mixture.
Add milk to flour mixture.
Stir quickly with a fork just enough to make a soft dough.
Put dough on lightly floured board and knead 6 to 8 times, forming a ball.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick and cut with floured cutter.
Place biscuits on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: perky pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add pecans; cool well. Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon in a bowl.
Add nuts and mix.
Bake in buttered shallow pan at 225° for 2 1/2 hours, stirring every 15 to 20 minutes.

title: dena's oklahoma slaw
directions: Sprinkle onion on cabbage.
Sprinkle sugar on cabbage and onion.
Do not stir.
Heat to boiling the remaining ingredients. Pour over cabbage mixture, cover quickly and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, celery and cubed eggplant.
When tender, add can of mushroom soup and salt and pepper to taste. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare chocolate cake and mousse according to directions on package.
Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Let the cake cool for 30 minutes.
Poke holes in the cake with fork and pour liqueur over it to fill in holes.
Line the bottom of a large dessert bowl with cake, which has been broken into pieces.
Add mousse on top of cake.
Add whipped cream on top of mousse, then a layer of crushed candy.
Repeat layers, ending with a layer of crushed Skor or Heath candy on top of whipped cream.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: beet and nut salad
directions: Drain beets and pineapple.
Heat liquids.
Dissolve Jell-O in them.
Chill until syrupy, then add beets and pineapple.
Pour in 1-quart mold.

title: chuck bake
directions: Form meat into one very large patty, about 1/2-inch thick and place on a large piece of aluminum foil.
Melt margarine in pan and brown onion.
Place onion on top of meat.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over meat.
Seal foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Open foil and broil 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Saute the onion and butter.
Chip the celery and pepper and add to onion.
Cook until tender.
Add the peas, soup, chestnuts and pimento.
Cover with cracker crumbs. Bake for 45 minutes.

title: fruitcake cookies
directions: Dredge fruit in flour.
Add salt, coconut and nuts.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Drop by spoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 275° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Store cooled cookies in an airtight container about 5 days before serving.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Melt butter.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add juice from crushed pineapple, pineapple and coconut, mixed well.
Pour into 2 crusts.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Brown meat (drain). Add remaining ingredients except tortillas and cheese. Bring to a boil. Layer meat mixture, then tortillas. Cover with cheese. Bake 30 minutes.

title: caramel icing
directions: Combine margarine, brown sugar, sugar and evaporated milk in large saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a rolling boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil for 15 minutes or until mixture begins to thicken, stirring constantly; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into large mixer bowl.
Beat at high speed until smooth.
Spread over cake layers.

title: sunshine barbecue chicken
directions: You will need one large 14 x 20-inch oven cooking bag.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 425° until cooked through. While the potatoes are still hot, slice the top of each cooked potato and scoop out inside of potato (leaving the empty potato shell) and place in a mixing bowl. Add butter, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper and beat with electric mixer as if you were making mashed potatoes. When potatoes are creamy and free of lumps, pour in packet of baked potato seasonings and mix well with a spoon. Spoon mashed potato mixture back into the empty potato shells until full. Top with Cheddar cheese and return to the oven to bake until cheese is melted and potatoes are hot.

title: methodist punch made for presbyterians
directions: Add sugar to hot tea, then add remaining ingredients except ginger ale and sherbet.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and any flavor sherbet.
Makes 36 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix chocolate pudding as directed on box.
Mix peanut butter, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip together, then swirl in the chocolate pudding.
Put the mixture into the graham cracker crusts.
Place in freezer for 2 hours.
Makes a great dessert frozen or slightly thawed.

title: 6 layer casserole
directions: Grease a 2-quart casserole dish.
Place potatoes, celery, ground beef, sliced onions and minced green peppers in layers in dish.
Combine tomatoes, salt and pepper; spoon over vegetables in casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until vegetables are tender.
Garnish with green pepper slices.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt half of the butter and cook lobster in it for 3 minutes. Remove lobster.
Add remaining butter and blend flour smoothly with it.
Scald and add milk and bring again to boiling point, stirring constantly.
Add seasonings, crabmeat and lobster.
Cook 5 minutes. Beat and add cream, egg yolks and sherry.
Cook 2 minutes and serve on toast.

title: colorful candy popcorn balls
directions: Pour popcorn into a large bowl.
Add peanuts and milk chocolate candies.
Mix together with spoon.
Put margarine and marshmallows in a large bowl.
Microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until marshmallows are puffed.
Using pot holders, take bowl out of microwave.
Mix together with spoon.
Add gelatin to marshmallow mixture.
Stir with spoon until mixture is all the same color.
Pour marshmallow mixture over popcorn mixture in bowl.
Quickly stir with spoon until marshmallow mixture evenly covers popcorn.
Let mixture cool slightly.
Grease your hands well with some margarine.
Shape mixture into balls with hands. Place balls on waxed paper until completely cool.
Makes 24 balls.

title: lemon butter sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Heat 1 or 2 minutes until flavors blend. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve over asparagus, broccoli and fish.

title: blueberry tea bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.

title: hot clam dip
directions: For a quick snack, mix seedless raisins with peanut butter and orange marmalade and fill celery ribs.

title: four decker mocha dessert
directions: Crust:
In a mixing bowl, cut butter into flour until crumbly. Stir in 3/4 cup of peanuts.
Press the mixture evenly over the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together; cover and chill overnight. Serve in hollow pumpernickel bread with remaining bread for dipping on side.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Pell a bnane. Put penut butr on it.
Put chocklit ice crem on it.
Then put gumey wrms on it.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Add peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Add confectioners sugar and mix until smooth.
Grease pan with margarine; press into pan and chill.

title: corn and green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into a large shallow casserole dish.

title: watermelon pickles
directions: Add water to watermelon rind and lime powder to cover.
Soak 3 hours or overnight.
Cut in chunks or strips.
Rinse several times.
Drain.
Boil in clear water for 2 1/2 hours.

title: lucy's pasties (meat pies)
directions: Combine first four ingredients in large mixing bowl; add salt and pepper.
Shake Worcestershire sauce liberally and mix until you see sauce.
Cut shortening into flour and salt with pastry cutter until crumbly.
Add water gradually to form a dough.
Flour pastry board or counter.
Roll out a handful of dough at a time (tennis ball size) until very thin and about the size of a luncheon plate.
Scoop a cooking spoonful of filling onto pastry (size can vary).
Bring top and bottom edges of pastry together and pinch together all the way down to the edges.
Overlap two sides over top.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Flour bottom and grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lightly spoon flour into cup.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except topping.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of 9-inch square pan.
Spoon salsa over cheese.
Layer chopped vegetables and top with shredded cheese and chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: continental chicken
directions: Arrange dried beef on bottom of greased crock-pot.
Wrap each piece of chicken breast with 1/2 strip of bacon and place on top of dried beef.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and cherry fruit filling.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Frost when cool.

title: cornflake macaroons
directions: In large mixing bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Stir in cream of tartar and vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff and glossy.
Fold in pecans, coconut and cereal.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto well-greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove immediately from baking sheet.
Cool on wire racks.

title: grasshopper pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with condensed milk; beat until blended.
Add lemon juice and creme de menthe.
Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into baked pie crust and let set.
Top with whipping cream.

title: chocolate-peanut butter coated apples
directions: You will need 10 to 12 wooden ice cream sticks.

title: buttermilk spice cake
directions: Sift first 7 ingredients together.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs (one at a time)
and vanilla flavoring and mix.
Add sifted ingredients, alternately, with buttermilk.
End with dry ingredients.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Blend together oleo, powdered sugar, milk and peanut butter. Add nuts, coconut and graham cracker crumbs.
Make balls 1-inch on wax paper.
Melt 1/2 bar paraffin with 8 ounces chocolate chips in double boiler.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture; cool on wax paper.

title: pineapple lime jello
directions: Use half juice and half water in Jell-O.
Soften cream cheese. Let Jell-O stand until partially set.
Whip cream cheese and pineapple.
Mix into Jell-O and re-set.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Add chips (chocolate) and pecans. Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet 8 to 10 minutes (bake).
Makes 3 dozen cookies.

title: spice cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add raisins; mix well.
Blend ingredients alternately with cold water.
Chill.
Using flour on hands to prevent sticking, roll dough in finger sizes in granulated sugar.
Place on cookie sheet in finger shapes; they will flatten down.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: pie crust i
directions: Cut
shortening into flour and
salt.
Add
vinegar
to milk. Do not stir.
Combine at once
with
the flour mixture. (May need a little more milk.) Yields 2 pie crusts.

title: eva's squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°.
Dot with buttered crumbs on top if desired.

title: turkey wings with mushroom sauce
directions: Wash and dry turkey wings, separating them at the joints; discard wing tips. Combine flour, salt and pepper.	Dredge turkey pieces in the seasoned flour.
Heat oil in heavy, deep skillet. Brown turkey pieces well on all sides.
Add mushrooms and onions. Arrange turkey pieces in an even layer evenly dispersed with mushrooms.	Sprinkle with thyme.
Blend chicken stock and tomato paste.
Pour over turkey.
Cover, simmer on low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until tender, adding more liquid if needed. Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Blend and heat but do not boil. Serve over hot noodles. Serves four.

title: jeanne's fruit cake
directions: Prepare in a double broiler.
Mix ingredients thoroughly. Top with red cherries and 1/2 pecans.

title: lasagna florentine
directions: Prepare lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain.
In a large saucepan, heat oil.
Add onion and garlic; cook until tender.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
In a medium bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, spinach and 1/2 cup Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Mix well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spread rice on bottom of casserole dish; spread with onion or mushroom slices or both.
Mix cans of soup together.
Pour 1/2 of soup mixture over rice.
Add chicken and cover with rest of soup mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with French fried onion rings and bake 1 more hour.

title: spinach gourmet
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; saut onion until tender. Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring until thick and bubbly.
Drain spinach in a colander; place on paper towels. Press until barely moist.
Stir spinach, eggs, salt and pepper into sauce.
Spread in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Combine crushed flakes and cheese; mix well. Sprinkle over spinach mixture. Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: creamed or scalloped celery
directions: For Creamed Celery:
Wash the stalks of celery and cut them into pieces.
Place the celery in a saucepan, cover with boiling water and boil until tender (about 1/2 hour), by which time the water should be reduced to about 1/2 cup.
Make a sauce with the celery water, milk and flour.
Add the cooked celery and season with salt and pepper.

title: vermont maple walnut muffins
directions: Combine wet ingredients.
Add dry ingredients to wet.
Stir only until moistened.
Add walnuts.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit refresher
directions: When in season, fresh strawberries can be sliced up and added, also.

title: elegant lemon cake roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until light and lemon colored; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating constantly.
Stir in lemon extract and vegetable oil; set aside.
Beat egg whites until foamy; gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until stiff, but not dry.
Fold yolk mixture into whites.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold into egg mixture.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan and line with waxed paper; grease and flour waxed paper.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sift powdered sugar in a 15 x 10-inch rectangle on a linen towel.
When cake is done, immediately loosen from sides of pan and turn out on sugar.
Peel off waxed paper.

Starting at narrow end, roll up cake and towel together; cool on a wire rack seam side down. Unroll cake; spread with half of creamy lemon filling and re-roll. Place on serving plate, seam side down, and spread remaining filling on all sides.
Combine coconut, water and food coloring in a plastic bag.
Close securely and shake well.
Sprinkle colored coconut over cake roll.
Refrigerate for 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and add cheese while hot and mix until partially melted.
Add flour, eggs and salt and mix well.
Add milk and melted butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: yummy soup
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large pot.
Simmer about one hour. Enjoy!

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a shallow 2-quart baking dish. Brown ground beef in a large skillet; drain.
Return to skillet; add taco seasoning, tomatoes and corn.
Bring mixture to a boil over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Pour mixture into a baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Mix egg, milk and cornbread mix. Pour over mixture.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Boil diced potatoes until tender. Drain. Brown hamburger and onion until done. Put potatoes and hamburger in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add salt, pepper and butter. Stir together. Pour milk over top until lightly covered. Can put shredded cheese on top, if desired. Bake in preheated oven for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Pour sweet potatoes into baking dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar over potatoes.
Place pineapple over brown sugar.
Place coconut over pineapple.
Place pecans over coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Remove from oven and completely cover casserole with marshmallows.
Put back in oven and brown marshmallows. Serve while hot.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer until melted.
Crock-pot works good.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as instructed on box.
After cooking, chill.
Mix together sausage, cottage cheese, lemon juice, Romano cheese, egg, spinach, salt, pepper and oregano.
Stuff shells with mixture. Top with tomato sauce, Mozzarella cheese, Swiss cheese and oregano.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° in a baking dish.

title: frosty strawberry squares
directions: Spread evenly in a shallow pan (10x13-inch).
Bake 20 minutes at 350° stirring it occasionaly.
Then sprinkle 2/3 of it in the pan and reserve 1/3 for the topping.

title: tangy orange punch
directions: For each serving, place 1 cup punch, 1/2 cup orange crisp and 3 ice cubes in a tall glass.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook ground beef and onion until brown.
Drain excess grease. Add tomatoes with liquid, tomato paste, sugar, salt, oregano, thyme, pepper, garlic salt and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling, stirring to break up tomatoes.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes or longer, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaf. Prepare lasagna noodles as package directs.
Drain.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange half of noodles.
Combine eggs and Ricotta cheese.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture over noodles.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Top with sauce.
Repeat.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Cook bacon until crisp in skillet; add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and heat. Cut onions fine; pull lettuce apart.
Mix and just before serving, pour mixture over the lettuce.
Stir well.

title: cajun beans and rice
directions: Soak bean overnight and drain. Fry bacon and chop up.
Add onions and garlic to same pan.
Saute until golden brown.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 hours.
Add hot water if needed.
Serve over rice.

title: saucy baked chicken
directions: Use thighs or beasts of chicken.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Fill it with meat.
Mix Russian dressing, apricot preserves and Lipton soup and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, water and vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Sift flour.
Add salt, soda and cream of tartar. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Blend in grated coconut.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets, 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 3 to 4 dozen.

title: homemade mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into small, bite size pieces.
Place in pot; cover with water.
Boil at medium temperature until potatoes are tender.
Drain water.
Add 2 or 3 tablespoons of butter and a little milk.
Also add salt to taste and a dash of pepper.
With mixer, mix until creamy.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sausage squash casserole
directions: Cook sausage and garlic until brown.
Drain off fat.
Cook squash, covered, in small amount of water until tender.
Drain. Stir squash and next 6 ingredients into meat.
Fold in eggs.
Bake in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Cook hamburg; add cabbage, tomatoes, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Add water until ingredients are covered.
When cabbage is cooked, add rice and simmer until done.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth; spread on tortilla.
Roll up tightly.
Cut into bite size slices.
Make 1 day ahead.
They are better when they are a little soggy.
Serve with a bowl of salsa to dip tortillas in.

title: pork chops with paprika-dill sauce
directions: Dredge chops in seasoned flour (reserve 2 tablespoons).
Heat butter in large skillet and brown chops on both sides; set chops aside.
Add onions and garlic to skillet and saute over medium heat 6 to 8 minutes, or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in paprika and bouillon and cook over high heat to deglaze skillet.
Add chops; bring to boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 45 minutes, or until chops are tender.
Remove chops to heated serving dish and keep warm.

title: apricot-cheese salad
directions: Drain and chill fruit. Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add fruit juices. Chill until slightly thickened. Fold in fruit and chill until firm.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add beaten eggs and cream until smooth.
Add peanut butter and stir well.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Form into tiny balls and press with fork onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes in oven at 375°.

title: butterfinger ice cream
directions: Blend thoroughly the chocolate milk, condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Add crushed Butterfingers.
Pour into a 4-quart ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: In a 10 to 12-inch skillet over medium heat, stir beef until crumbly and browned; drain.
Stir in garlic, onion, basil and tomato sauce.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Cook noodles in salted water for about 8 minutes; drain.
Spoon meat mixture into a 13 x 9-inch casserole dish; top evenly with noodles.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Whip the cream cheese, sour cream and milk; pour over noodles.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven until heated through.
Can be made a day ahead and chilled. If so, allow 1 hour to cook in oven.

title: dip batter for shrimp
directions: Use ice water and the batter doesn't start rising until you start frying.
You might not use all of the water.
You want batter to just cling and coat shrimp lightly.
Shrimp is dipped into batter, then dropped in deep fat to fry.
Frying only takes a couple minutes.

title: rum balls
directions: Mix crushed vanilla wafers, sugar, cocoa, syrup and nuts. Blend well.
Add rum and blend again.
Roll into small balls about 1/2-inch each and roll in powdered sugar.
If balls won't stick together, add a little more rum.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat chocolate squares and shortening in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in ungreased pan (8 x 8 x 2-inches).
Bake until brownies begin to pull away from sides, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy baked beans
directions: Brown meat in skillet, adding onion and green pepper in time to simmer.
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: seafood on the grill
directions: When grilling seafood, season with lemon, butter, salt, pepper, onions and bell peppers. Wrap in foil and place on grill for approximately 20 minutes. Easy to cook. Tastes great!

title: fresh apple muffins
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; stir in 1 cup apples and make a well in center of mixture.
Combine milk, oil and egg; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Combine remaining
1/2 cup apple, 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over muffin batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
1 dozen.

title: old-fashion peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Cook to soft ball stage or when a soft ball forms in 1/2 cup water, then add next 3 ingredients, mixed together.
Pour onto buttered platter.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chili
directions: In heavy skillet, brown ground beef and onions in hot shortening.
Add chili powder, catsup, salt and water.
Cook slowly for 1 hour; add beans and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry apple butter
directions: Wash and slice tart apples.
Add water to cover.
Cook until soft.
Press through sieve.
Measure, then boil apple pulp, blueberries, sugar and spices until it's thick.
Pour, while hot, into jars.
Process for 10 minutes in hot water bath.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Use 3 teaspoons of mix to one cup hot water.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Beat milk and juice until stiff.
Fold in Cool Whip, pineapple and pecans.
Pour into 2 graham cracker pie shells.

title: coconut pie
directions: In saucepan, on top of stove, mix milk, sugar and egg yolks together.
Gradually blend in flour and salt.
Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell and top with meringue after cooked.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine first seven ingredients.
Place chicken in mixture and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Coat each piece with crumbs.
Arrange on shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes or until juices run clear.
Makes 8 servings.

title: brownie cake with buttermilk icing
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar; set aside.
Bring margarine, cocoa and water to boil.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture; stir quickly.
Whisk together the eggs, buttermilk, soda, salt and vanilla.
Pour into the other mixture; beat well.
Bake in a greased and floured pan (15 x 18-inch) for 20 minutes at 350°. Five minutes before cake is done, make the Buttermilk Icing.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of muffin cups, or use paper baking cups.
In mixing bowl, beat egg well.
Stir in milk and oil with egg.
Add flour, sugar, baking powder and salt, all at once, to liquid mixture.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Fill each muffin cup half full of batter.
Drop scant teaspoonful of jelly on center of batter.
Add more batter to fill cup 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peach pie
directions: Combine all ingredients (except Cool Whip).
Cook until mixture begins to thicken (4 to 5 minutes).
Let cool.
Pour into cooked pie shell and cool.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: high rise biscuits
directions: Combine flour and baking powder; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, mixing well.

title: garlic bread
directions: Combine
liquid ingredients.
Spread on bread.	Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix crumbs, 1/2 Parmesan, garlic, oregano and pepper.
Roll chicken in mixture; drizzle with melted margarine.
Place in greased dish and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Turn breasts over and bake another 20 minutes.
Pour soup mixed with milk over top. Sprinkle with remaining half of Parmesan and paprika. Bake 20 minutes more or until done.

title: caramel corn
directions: Cook brown sugar, margarine, corn syrup and salt over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook 5 minutes and remove from heat.
Add soda; stir until foamy.
In large bowl pour mixture over popcorn. Mix until well coated.
Spread evenly on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add oil, vanilla and water.
Add vinegar last.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add remaining ingredients and mix. Refrigerate.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, apple, celery and nuts.
Mix sugar with enough mayonnaise to be of desired consistency.

title: strudel cake
directions: Make cake according to directions on box.
Remove 1 cup cake batter and put into medium bowl; add nuts, brown sugar and cinnamon and mix well.
Pour 1/2 of regular cake batter into a greased, floured Bundt cake pan.
Pour brown sugar, etc. mixture over the cake batter in the Bundt pan.
Add last 1/2 of regular cake batter to this.
Bake at 350° approximately 35 minutes (or until done).
After cake is removed from pan, but still warm, pour a glaze made of 10x sugar and water over cake.
Can be topped with additional chopped nuts.

title: good 'n easy muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Combine all ingredients just until moist.
Spoon into greased muffin cups, 2/3 full. Bake 15 to 20 minutes. Do not overbake.
Great "company" bread.

title: crab soup
directions: Melt butter in a large saucepan.
Add celery and cook 3 minutes, stirring often, until crisp-tender.
Add flour and stir over low heat until frothy.
Cook about 3 minutes, stirring often to prevent browning.
Add hot pepper sauce.
Gradually stir in milk.
Increase heat to medium and bring to a boil.
Immediately reduce heat so milk simmers.
Add crab meat, return to a simmer and cook about 3 minutes until crab is hot.
Stir in scallions. Makes 4 servings.

title: luau brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease bottom of 13 x 9 pan. Melt 1/2 cup butter and chocolate chips; blend. To chocolate mixture, add 1 1/2 cups sugar, flour, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 4 eggs. Mix well. In a separate bowl, mix cream cheese, 2 teaspoons vanilla, 1 egg, 1/2 cup sugar and coconut.

title: chocolate devil's food cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add sour milk.
Mix all the dry ingredients together and add next.
Add vanilla.
Add the boiling water last.
Bake in two 8-inch pans at 350° for 35 minutes, or until done.
When cool, split layers and fill with custard filling, giving you a four-layer cake.
Frost with your favorite frosting.

title: candy flavored walnuts
directions: Combine first three items.
Stir over low heat until sugar melts.
Boil to 238°.
Remove from heat.
Add nuts.
Stir until creamy.
Turn out on waxed paper and separate nuts.
Makes about 2 1/4 pounds of nuts.

title: crab appetizer
directions: Layer this in Corning dish and serve hot.
Either microwave or toaster oven.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt butter and chocolate over hot water.
Take off stove and stir in sugar, flour, salt and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake in oven preheated to 375°.
Turn down to 325° and cook 30 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream.
Nuts may be added to mixture before baking, if desired.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, oil and yeast.
Knead enough to hold together and roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and fold in half.
Bake at 400° for approximately 20 minutes.

title: reuben spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Keep warm in a slow cooker. Serve on cocktail rye.

title: carnation cheeseburger loaf
directions: Blend milk, egg and cracker crumbs; add other ingredients, except cheese.
Line loaf pan with heavy waxed paper and place 1/2 cup cheese on bottom of pan.
Place 1/2 meat loaf mixture over cheese; top with another 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Cover with remaining meat.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Allow to stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: confetti potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes, soup and milk; add cheese, onion, green pepper, pimento, pepper and 1/2 cup of cracker crumbs.
Pour into shallow casserole; top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: blueberry ice-box pie
directions: In saucepan combine 1 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in 1/8 cup water.
Add blueberries and lemon juice.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Cool. Blend softened cream cheese and 1 1/2 cups sugar until creamy. Slice bananas in bottom of pie shell.
Spread cream cheese mixture over bananas and top with blueberry filling.
Refrigerate and serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: date nut candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter until it forms a soft ball.
Lower heat.
Add dates and stir until most have dissolved.
Remove from heat and beat 3 minutes.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let stand 1 hour or more.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with vegetable dippers in red or green bell pepper or serving bowl.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple, cherries and pecans. Mix and chill.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Add cream cheese.
Blend well with mixer.
Stir in marshmallows.
Spread over chilled jello mixture. This salad looks nice on the table during Christmas and Valentine's Day.

title: taco in a bowl
directions: Cook Success rice according to package directions; drain and set aside.
In large saucepan, combine Hormel chili, water, onions, green chilies, seasonings and rice.
Heat.

Turn into serving bowl and top with shredded lettuce, shredded Cheddar and Monterey Jack cheese, diced avocado, corn chips, diced onions, sliced olives, sour cream, chopped green or red pepper (as desired).
Serves 3 to 4.

title: rainbow jello
directions: Add 1 cup of boiling water to first flavor. Dissolve.
Pour 1/2 of jello into 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
While this sets, mix the other half of jello with 2 tablespoons of sour cream. After first part sets, repeat with each flavor.
Easy, but takes time.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour in baking dish.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: chop suey cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Top with a Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: lime and cream cheese salad
directions: Soften cream cheese with evaporated milk (5 1/2 ounce can or 2/3 cup).
Mix lemon jello with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.
Add cheese and milk.
Pour into mold and let it set. Mix lime jello with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water. Add crushed pineapple.
When cool, pour this mixture over the first salad letting it fall onto a spoon in order to avoid holes.
Allow the mixture to set.

title: aunt pauline's shrimp salad
directions: Combine cooked shrimp, cooked potatoes, celery and onion.
Add French dressing, lemon juice and salt.
Chill.
Just before serving, add the mayonnaise.
Serve on a platter garnished with salad greens, tomato wedges and avocado slices.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: one dish spareribs and potatoes
directions: Wash and place ribs in desired roasting pan.
Add onion, garlic, caraway seeds, salt, pepper and water.
Bake, covered, in oven at 350°.
Turn ribs over after 1 hour.
One hour later, add potatoes.
Thirty minutes later, add sauerkraut.
Cook until potatoes and meat are tender.
Remove ribs and add butter to sauerkraut, potatoes and juice.
Mash potatoes if desired.

title: frozen pickles
directions: Let first 4 ingredients stand for 5 hours; drain.
Mix sugar and vinegar in bowl and stir until clear.
Add celery seed.
Pour over pickles and put in containers.
Store in freezer.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: casserole
directions: Line a large casserole bowl with pie crust.
Chop cooked meat in bite size pieces and put in bottom of crust.
Cook vegetables in water; then add mushroom soup.
Pour over meat.
Top with second crust; brush with milk.
Cut slits in top crust.
Bake at 400° until crust is brown.

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions.
Drain well. In saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender but not brown.

In a large mixing bowl, stir together the mushroom soup, celery soup, milk and cheese. Add drained broccoli, cooked onion, ham, uncooked rice and Worcestershire sauce; mix well. Bake, covered, at 350° until rice is done, 45 to 50 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine and chill the apricot jello, boiling water and cold water.
Add crushed pineapple (with juice drained; save juice for topping) and bananas.
Chill until firm.
Add topping.

title: pecan chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Melt butter in small saucepan over low heat; remove from heat.
Whisk in 1/4 cup Dijon mustard.
Set aside.
To grind pecans, process pecan halves in small batches with on/off pulses in food processor to a fine powder.
Place ground pecans in shallow dish; set aside.

title: pumpkin bread(microwave)
directions: Combine sugar and oil in a large mixing bowl.
Stir in eggs and mix well.
Add water and flour slowly.
Add salt, baking soda, nutmeg, allspice, vanilla, pumpkin and pecans.
Mix until blended.
Line bottom of bowl with a circle of wax paper.
Pour 1 1/3 cups batter into pint bowl.
Cover with vented plastic wrap. Microwave on Medium (50%) 7 minutes, rotating bowl 1/2 turn after 3 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Halve peppers lengthwise; discard stem and seeds.
Parboil peppers in boiling, salted water 8 to 10 minutes; drain and place in shallow baking dish with 1/8 inch of water.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: apple salad
directions: Core and dice apples (can be peeled, if desired).
In large bowl, put apples, marshmallows, drained pineapple and nuts.
In small saucepan, beat egg.
Add sugar, flour, pineapple juice and water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens like pudding.
Pour over apple mixture and chill.

title: connies pineapple cream salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to boil.
Let cool.
In a glass bowl, dissolve jello enough to make wet.
Let cool.
Add pineapple and sugar to jello.
Mix in all dry ingredients to jello mixture except cheese.
Beat whipping cream and fold into mixture a little at a time (or use LaCreme or Cool Whip).
Add cheese and mix thoroughly.
Cover and place in refrigerator until firm (usually overnight).

title: summit lemon squares
directions: Mix margarine, flour and 1 cup sugar and press into a 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 325°.
Mix well the eggs, 1 cup sugar, lemon juice, 1 tablespoon flour, baking powder and pecans.
Pour on top of the pastry.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: cream-style corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients together. Add remaining ingredients. Roll into small balls and flatten with a fork. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and salt together and alternate with milk.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Mix well.
Bake in a tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Cool and frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Brown meats in a large skillet and drain.
Add the other ingredients one at a time and mix thoroughly.
Makes a large amount and is very good with nachos and tortilla chips.

title: mom's spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix tomato paste and sauce with water; bring to boil.
Turn heat down to medium and add baking soda.
Break bubbles with a spoon so it doesn't boil over.
When bubbles are done forming, add garlic, parsley and basil leaf.

title: vidalia onion spread
directions: Combine onions, mayonnaise and cheese.
Pour mixture into a 1-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Blot with paper towel to remove excess oil.
Serve hot with crisp crackers.

title: basic biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and stir with a fork only until dough leaves sides of bowl.
Turn dough out onto lightly floured board and knead just until smooth.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet, slightly touching.
Grease tops of biscuits with oil.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Makes 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Drain beans.
Chop onion, pickle and eggs.
Mix all ingredients and let marinate for 4 hours.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In a medium bowl, mix flours, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
With a pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles course crumbs.
With a fork, stir in milk just until mixture forms a soft dough and leaves side of bowl.
On a lightly floured surface, with floured hands, knead dough 10 times.
Pat dough into a 5 x 5-inch square.
Cut into four 2 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch squares.
Cut each square into 2 triangles. Place triangles, about 1/2-inch apart, on a large cookie sheet. Brush with beaten egg and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 8 biscuits.

title: sweet-sour scallops
directions: Cut scallops in half and bread with flour and garlic powder. Dip into egg and fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain on paper towel.
Set aside in warm oven.

title: spice cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in hot water.
Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in hot water and soda mixture.
Sift together and stir in the flour, baking powder, salt and spices. Drop spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: cake mix cinnamon rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast into warm water and stir to dissolve.
Add cake mix and mix well.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Knead until smooth and elastic. Place dough in a greased bowl and cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch dough down and divide into 3 portions. On a greased counter, roll each portion to 1/4-inch thickness. Spread with soft butter.
Sprinkle on brown sugar and cinnamon. Roll and slice into 1-inch slices.
Place in greased pans.
Let rise again until doubled.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Roll from pans and glaze with powdered sugar, milk and vanilla glaze.

title: strawberry chicken salad
directions: Shake together the first 7 ingredients. Refrigerate 2 hours. Pour over the spinach, oranges, chicken and strawberries. Toss.

title: fruit salad
directions: Empty pineapple, apples, Mandarin oranges, coconut, marshmallows and cherries into a bowl and mix well gently.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.
About 1 hour before serving, add Cool Whip.

title: chocolate marshmallow pie
directions: Melt ingredients, except Cool Whip, together; cool. Add 1 cup Cool Whip. Pour into baked pie crust. (Can use graham cracker or chocolate Oreo crust.) Frost with Cool Whip.

title: chicken breasts in sour cream
directions: Combine Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt, Tabasco and salt with sour cream.
Marinate chicken in these ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, roll chicken breasts in bread crumbs.
Cover with aluminum foil and place on cookie sheet. Bake chicken 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Remove foil and broil until golden brown.
Serves 8.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds.
Spoon into a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Put cabbage and onion in a frying pan with bacon drippings. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Fry on medium heat until just about done.
Add 1 tablespoon cider vinegar.
Cover.
Let fry on low for 10 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into 6 to 8 portions.
Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Dredge on both sides in flour.
Melt shortening and brown meat on both sides quickly.
Place in a baking dish; pour onion, soup and milk over meat.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: one minute cookies
directions: Boil together milk, sugar, butter and cocoa for 1 minute. Take off fire and add oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir well and drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chili casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Pour chili into 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over chili.
Stir cornmeal mix, oil, egg and milk together until smooth.
Pour cornmeal batter over chili and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until cornbread is golden.
Serve and garnish as desired with olives and sour cream.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Chop and peel
apples; pour sugar over them and let set 10 minutes.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for an hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl combine all ingredients, mix well. Pour batter into two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° approximately one hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and knead until elastic, about 5 minutes. Roll out to fit a greased pizza pan.

title: egg and sausage strata breakfast casserole
directions: Butter a 2-quart casserole dish.
Slightly beat eggs and milk to blend.
Stir in salt, pepper and mustard.
In dish, layer in this order:
bread crumbs, egg sauce, browned sausage and cheese. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: caesar salad
directions: Mash garlic and add to salad oil; let stand.
Just before serving, tear romaine into salad bowl, sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Strain salad oil to remove garlic clove and pour over romaine; toss.
Pour eggs and lemon juice over salad; toss.
Add Parmesan cheese and croutons, tossing gently, and serve.
Makes 24 servings.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add vegetables.
Let set in refrigerator for at least 1 hour before serving.

title: low-fat brownies
directions: Combine flour and cocoa.
Melt baking chocolate with canola oil in a double boiler.
Mix egg whites and sugar to make a meringue.
Mix with applesauce, yogurt and vanilla extract.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread oil in a 9 x 9-inch pan, wiping out extra oil.
Pour in mixture.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: zero salad dressing
directions: Just mix all together and blend well.

title: curried cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water until barely cooked.
Drain. Put cauliflower in a 2-quart casserole.
Mix together soup, mayonnaise, cheese and curry powder; spoon over top.
Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Stir in crumbs to coat.
Sprinkle over top. Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: potato cheese mold
directions: Boil potatoes, cool slightly and mash.
With mixer beat in butter and eggs, mix well.
Stir in parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Put chips in bottom of 3-quart casserole dish. Pour chicken over chips and set aside. Mix both cans of soup, can of tomatoes, pepper and salt. Pour over chicken. Add onion over top and bake 35-45 minutes at 350 degrees. Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake an additional 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted. (Very good!)

title: borderline soup
directions: In medium saucepan, combine chicken and beef broths.
Bring to a boil.
Add onion, zucchini, carrot and tomato.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are crisp-tender (about 10 to 15 minutes).
Season to taste.
While vegetables are simmering, fry tortillas in a little hot oil in a pan until crisp.
Drain.
Place tortilla wedges in 4 soup bowls.
Add cheese.
Ladle soup over this.
Serve steaming hot.
Serve with corn muffins.

title: glorified rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add Cool Whip last.
Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: chili with beans
directions: In large skillet, cook ground beef and onions until meat is well browned and onions are tender.
Stir in other items.
Cook, uncovered, about 10 minutes or until desired consistency.

title: bessie eakins lemon pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and boiling water.
Cook 15 minutes. Add butter, egg yolks, rind and juice.
Turn into baked pie shell. Top with meringue.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Heat blackberries with 1 1/2 cups sugar; set aside.
Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Make batter of flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk; pour this over melted oleo.
Pour blackberries on top of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until crust is golden brown.

title: mallow cups
directions: Mix
desired
amount of marshmallow cream with powdered sugar until it is a workable consistency.
This can be molded as for peanut butter cup, a design mold or bar.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add pineapple, juice and eggs. Mix with spoon.
Bake at 325° about 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Skin and debone chicken; cut into small pieces.
Cut Velveeta into small cubes.
Combine chicken, cheese, soups and Ro-Tel.
Mix well and set aside.
Spray a large flat casserole dish with a nonstick coating.
Crush the tortilla chips and line the bottom of the casserole.
Save some of the crushed chips to sprinkle on top after baking.
Pour chicken, soup, Ro-Tel and cheese mixture over the crushed chips in the casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° to 400°.
Sprinkle the remaining crushed chips over the top before serving.

title: kahlua
directions: Bake at 350° and stir often until done. After cooled, add chocolate chips and raisins.

title: beet pickles
directions: Wash beets and put in large pot.
Pour enough water over them to cover and cook until tender.
When done, skin and quarter.
Put into jars.
Heat vinegar, water and sugar together.
Pour over beets in jars and seal.

title: old fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream fat and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Bake at 450° for about 8 or 9 minutes.

title: dixie dog
directions: Combine all ingredients except hot dogs and make a batter; add enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Dry hot dogs and insert a small stick.
Dip hot dogs into batter and fry in deep hot oil until golden brown.

title: peanut butter cookies no. 1
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to a boil.
Add peanut butter; mix. Add Cocoa Puffs.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: pear preserves
directions: Peel pears at night and put sugar over them (no water). Do not
stir.	Next morning there will be plenty of water and juice to	cook
them.
Let
them cook slowly for a long time, until they turn pink or dark, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: candied yams
directions: Place yams in baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour and cinnamon. Add margarine and water.
Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Pour over yams.
Bake at 325° until thickened.

title: orange sherbet salad
directions: Boil 1` cup water.
Add Jell-O, sherbet and Cool Whip. Dissolve and add rest of ingredients and place in mold.
Chill overnight.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cheese, together.
Pour into lightly greased 2 1/2 to 3-quart baking dish.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: broccoli souffle(goes well with chicken with wine)
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Mix other ingredients, then fold into broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in greased dish for 20 minutes at 400°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Cut all candied fruit into small pieces.
Chop pecans.
Dredge all of these in a half cup of flour.
Set aside.
Grease a 10-inch tube pan.
Cut a circle of brown paper to fit bottom of pan.
Fit in pan and grease and flour again.
Preheat oven at 350°.

title: eggplant in tomato sauce
directions: In a large skillet, saute the eggplant, onions, pepper, garlic and salt in the olive oil.
Add tomatoes, bay leaf, dissolved chicken bouillon cube, vinegar and oregano.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add tomato paste and mix well.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove the lid, stir and discard bay leaf. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter and jelly cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off. In large bowl, combine all ingredients except 1 cup flour and oats. Shape into 1-inch balls; place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets. Flatten in crisscross pattern with fork dipped in sugar. Place 1/8 teaspoon jelly in center of each cookie. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until light golden brown. Makes 60 cookies.

title: hazelnut-parmesan asparagus
directions: Heat water to boiling; cover and cook 4-6 minutes or until crisp and tender.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Stir in mushrooms, and cook until light brown. Stir asparagus, basil, salt and pepper into mushrooms until vegetables are coated with seasoning and asparagus is heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese and hazelnuts.

title: lillian's kugle
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to drained noodles.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish at 400° to 425° for 1 hour.
(All dairy products can be low-fat except butter or margarine.)

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper.
Add soups and water to meat mixture.
Cook and drain noodles; add the cheese to the hot noodles to melt some.
Combine the noodles with the meat/soup mixture and pour into large casserole dish.
Top with olives if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
This recipe makes a large amount and can be frozen after cooking.

title: hot apple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Sprinkle chopped nuts and brown sugar on top and then bake.
Bake until brown.

title: knox blox
directions: Mix Knox and Jell-Os in a bowl.
Add the boiling water.
Pour into large shallow pan and chill until firm.
Cut into squares or shapes with cookie cutter.

title: cake-pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add flour and lemon juice and peel. Add beaten egg yolks and milk.
Add stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add 1/2 can of tomato sauce; mix well.
Place mixture in a baking dish and shape into a loaf.
Combine remaining ingredients and tomato sauce in a small bowl and pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for one hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Baste often!

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix
all
ingredients with one cup nuts.
Divide into 2 balls or
one large ball.
Roll in remaining nuts.
Serve with crackers. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fudge brownies with a crust
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine 1 cup of flour and sugar.
Cut into butter until crumbly.
Press mixture firmly on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: hanky panky's
directions: Brown hot and mild sausage on top of stove.
Drain off excess fat.
Melt Velveeta cheese over sausage; mix well.
Take mixture and spread over cocktail bread.
Put in oven; bake until brown.

title: cotton festival no-cook homemade ice cream
directions: Combine instant pudding with 2 cups milk in 1 gallon freezer can.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Add enough milk to fill can to fill line.
Freeze.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Mix jello with boiling water, then add crushed pineapple and juice to the boiling water.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Stir in container of Cool Whip.
Add walnuts (if desired) and marshmallows. Garnish with mandarin oranges and maraschino cherries.

title: orange chocolate fondue
directions: In large saucepan, combine pudding, juice and milk.
Bring to boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Pour into fondue pot.
Keep warm. Serve with fruits.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk, then mix with meat and egg.
Add 3/4 jar of Prego to meat mixture and shape to fit in loaf pan.
Pour remaining Prego over top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Lay cut up chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Pour broth over chicken.
Spread soup over chicken.
Pour peas and carrots over all.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix oleo, flour and milk in separate bowl.
Pour over top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until brown crust appears on top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine all
ingredients
in
a large bowl.
Stir well. Pour into unbaked
pie
crust
and top with crust, if desired. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Stir together and then mix with mixer for 3 minutes.
Bake in 350° oven (depending how hot oven is) for 50 minutes.

title: celery casserole
directions: Boil celery pieces about 5 minutes; drain. Mix with soup. Layer in baking dish: celery/soup mixture, egg slices and cracker crumbs. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° until
bubbly and cheese is melted.

title: coconut chiffon pie
directions: Beat softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Add milk and sugar. Fold in coconut, extract and Cool Whip.
Pour into crust and cover with upside-down plastic cover from graham cracker crust.
Freeze. Place pieces of pie in microwave for 10 seconds before serving. Freeze leftovers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken, sour cream, soup and pimentos.
Put into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and melted margarine.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
May be served in small tart shells.
Warm shells, fill with warmed filling and top with crumbs and margarine.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat. Cook onion, celery and green pepper until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except rice.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Reduce heat. Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Makes approximately 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown meat in iron skillet.
Before meat is done add onion and other vegetables.
Continue cooking for a few minutes, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Little bits of leftover tomato add color and flavor.
In a cup or small bowl make a roux with the flour and a small amount of water.
Add to meat mixture and continue cooking until a small amount of gravy thickens in the mixture.
Spoon mashed potatoes over the top and place skillet in 375° F. oven for 20 - 25 minutes or until mashed potatoes are beginning to brown on top.
Serve with a big spoon and let everyone help themselves. Great with buttered rolls and maybe a small salad.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Turn
into an oiled baking dish and bake at 350° for 45
minutes, or use as stuffing in a turkey.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, butter and vanilla until smooth.
(I mix mine by hand.) Fold in whipped cream.
Gently spoon into crust.
Spread with whipped topping or Cool Whip.

title: apple surprise
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Fill pie plate with sliced apples; sprinkle with cinnamon and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, margarine or butter and egg.
Pour over top of apples.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce and orange rind.
Let chill until nearly set and add remaining ingredients.
Congeal.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat lightly.
Add syrup and butter.
Place pecans in bottom of unbaked pie crust. Add filling.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: baked onions
directions: Place onions in casserole.
Combine all other ingredients and pour over onions.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cappuccino
directions: Dissolve coffee in boiling water.
Pour into small, tall cups, filling only half full.
Whip the cream.
Let guest add sugar, if desired, then spoon cream atop coffee and sprinkle with ground cinnamon.
Guest folds in cream until frothy.
Makes 6 or 7 servings.

title: best ever muffins
directions: Combine milk, egg and oil.
Add oil at once to dry ingredients.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 400° for 25 minutes. You can line your muffin cups with the paper muffin cups.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: remoulade sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients, except oil in food processor. Turn on and slowly dribble in the oil. Allow flavors to marinate overnight. Serve over large boiled and deveined shrimp on a bed of shredded lettuce. Sauce keeps well in refrigerator.

title: onion crescents
directions: Unroll dough; separate into 8 triangles.
Evenly sprinkle 1 teaspoon onion over the 8 triangles.
Roll each and place on cookie sheet.
Brush rolls with butter.
Sprinkle remaining onion over tops.
Bake as directed.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute onion and butter until tender.
Add cabbage, lima beans, carrots, potatoes, broth and salt.
Cover and bring to boil. Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Melt 1/4 cup butter or margarine in 4 quart kettle.
Blend flour, pepper and paprika. Stir in milk and heat to boiling while stirring.
Boil and stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, stir in cheese until melted.
Add vegetables with their liquid to cheese soup base.
Heat to serve.

title: chocolate tornado
directions: Spoon chocolate Cool Whip into 6 dishes.
Make a depression in the center.
Spread Cool Whip up sides of dishes.
Prepare instant pudding as directed.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon into center of Cool Whip.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine sugar, pineapple and cranberries and let stand.
Make Jell-O; let stand until it starts to jell.
Then add it all together.

title: lucille's apple crumble
directions: Mix sugar with 1 cup of water and boil down to syrup consistency.
Mix cornstarch in 1/4 cup water and add to syrup with butter.
Peel apples and cut them into one-inch pieces.
Cook the apples in the syrup until tender.
Place in a baking dish.

title: scallops provencal
directions: Rinse scallops and dry with a paper towel.
Roll scallops in flour.
In a wok or large skillet. Saute scallops and garlic in olive oil until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add snow peas, red peppers and mushrooms and mix until heated through.
Serve over rice.
Serves 5.

title: hot green bean and crab bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a heat-proof serving dish, mix together the beans, crabmeat and onion.
Add 1/4 c. bran, yogurt and seasoning and mix well.

title: eagle brand caramel pie
directions: Place both cans of Eagle Brand milk in saucepan; completely cover with water. Boil 3 hours, replacing water when needed. Keep both cans completely covered with boiling water at all times. After 3 hours boiling, cool cans completely. Open and pour into precooked pie shell. Top with Cool Whip and chopped pecans.

title: scallop pineapple
directions: Mix bread crumbs and pineapple.
Put in baking dish.
Combine eggs, sugar and butter.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana cream cheese pie
directions: Slice banana(s) and place on bottom and sides of baked pie shell. Mix cream cheese, Eagle Brand, lemon juice and vanilla thoroughly and pour into pie shell over the banana(s). Cover with Cool Whip. Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper. Add milk and cook until thick. Add Worcestershire sauce, soup, cheese, and pimento stirring well. Put greenbeans in casserole dish and cover with soup mixture. Sprinkle with crumbs and bake in a 350° oven for 20-25 minutes.

title: linguini with red clam sauce
directions: Saute garlic in butter.
Add parsley, oregano and clams with juice.
Stir in tomato sauce, wine and seasonings.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over pasta; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Boil water, sugar, and juice from cherries.
Add jello and stir.
Add cherries, pineapple, and nuts.
Add coca-cola.
Pour into casserole dish and chill.

title: unbaked cheese cake
directions: Mix together the Jell-O and hot water; let cool.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Whip the chilled milk until stiff, then whip all ingredients together.
Pour into an 8 x 13 x 2-inch crumb-lined pan.

title: vermont sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain sweet potatoes well.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until well mashed and smoothly blend in syrup, evaporated milk and butter.
Pour into greased baking dish. Top with marshmallows. Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes. Marshmallow should be golden brown.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: eggnog
directions: Place all ingredients into a large bowl and with an electric mixer, blend on high for 3 minutes.
Put into a pitcher or gallon jug and refrigerate until ready to serve.
