title: aunt nannie's corn chowder
directions: Saute bacon in Dutch oven.
Add onions and cook until transparent.
Add chicken broth or stock, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Put cornstarch in small container and add 1 cup milk. Stir until smooth.
Add to soup mixture and add 2 more cups of milk.
Bring to boil, stir and add chicken.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes on medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Serve with green salad and hot rolls.

title: wine gelatin
directions: Dissolve strawberry jello and sugar in boiling water, stir in wine and cold water.
Pour into a 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold on serving dish.
Garnish with sugared grapes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown meat in large pot with onions and seasonings.
Drain. Add potatoes to meat mixture and mash well until blended.
Fold into pie crust.
Top with other crust; vent.

title: healthy chocolate chip muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Combine yogurt and milk in medium mixing bowl.
Add yogurt and milk mixture to dry ingredients and mix just until ingredients are moistened. Fold in chocolate chips.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full and bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 12.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onion and put in a pot.
Cook, covered, for about 10 minutes.
Turn off heat and let stand in water, covered.
Mix together soups and milk, cook over low heat until melted into a sauce.
Drain potatoes.
Pour mixture over potatoes and turn with wooden spoon.
Pour in baking dish back.
Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly and brown.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and pepper. Chop remaining ingredients.
Mix in large saucepan.
Use 2 1/2 ounces of soup base. Simmer for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pesto sauce
directions: Place the garlic, basil leaves, olive oil, cheese and optional pine nuts in a food processor or blender and process until pureed. Keep refrigerated several weeks or freeze.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Put in bottom of 2-quart casserole dish.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Put on top of chicken.
Mix soup, lemon juice, curry powder and mayonnaise. Pour sauce over broccoli.
Spread cheese and bread crumbs on top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: grapenut bread
directions: Combine buttermilk, Grapenuts, sugar and cinnamon and soak for 3 hours. Combine remaining ingredients and mix together. Dissolve 1 teaspoon soda in 1/2 cup water. Mix all together. Pour into 2 greased bread pans. Bake 300° for 1 hour 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients; chop in the fat.
Add the mashed sweet potatoes; mix well.
Add gradually only enough milk to make a soft dough.
Knead a few strokes.
Roll dough 1/3 inch thick.
Cut in rounds and place on a baking sheet.
Bake in a hot 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: orange slush
directions: Place half of the yogurt, half of the juice concentrate and half of the milk in blender. Cover and blend on medium speed about 45 seconds, stopping blender occasionally to scrape sides, until thick and smooth. Pour mixture into 8 glasses. Repeat with remaining yogurt, juice concentrate and milk. Pour remaining mixture into glasses.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crabmeat, then stir in crabmeat. Spread on split Thomas English muffin.
Cut into quarters.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Chill or freeze until ready to use.
When ready to use, put under broiler until the cheese melts.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together and shake.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans in baking dish.
Mix sugar, vinegar and bacon grease.
Pour over beans.
Let stand for 4 hours.
Add almonds and crumbled bacon.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 40 minutes. Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water for 5 minutes; drain well.
Mix with next 5 ingredients.
Place in greased casserole and cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream together peanut butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar, then whipped topping.
Spoon into crust and chill until set, 3 to 4 hours, or freeze.

title: hot cheesy corn bread
directions: Mix and bake at 350° until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: huguenot torte
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and remaining ingredients.
Pour into well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven 40 to 45 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: chicken breast in mushroom sauce
directions: Coat chicken with flour.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot oil and oleo, cook garlic 30 seconds; discard garlic.
Cook chicken cutlets, until lightly browned on both sides.
Add soup, mushrooms and broccoli to skillet.
Cook until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 15 minutes or until chicken and vegetables are done.

title: icebox cake
directions: In
a
large mixing bowl with the wafer crumbs, add all other ingredients
in
small
amounts.
Mix by hand until all ingredients are mixed well.
Place in a lined pan and store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: bacon-cheese biscuits
directions: Combine flour and shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal; set aside.
Combine buttermilk and soda, stirring until soda dissolves.
Add buttermilk mixture, bacon, cheese and onion to flour mixture, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly 4 or 5 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: japanese salad
directions: Halve avocados.
Scoop out insides and cut in cubes.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Refill shells.
Chill.
Makes 4 salads.

title: oatmeal lace cookies
directions: Melt butter and add dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 1 minute; remove from cookie sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: hip padder balls
directions: Melt chocolate, 2 tablespoons butter and milk in double boiler or microwave.
Stir in vanilla and set aside to cool.
Cream remaining 1/2 cup butter and brown sugar in a bowl.
Beat in the egg.
Add the flour and the oats.

title: pecan pies
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, cornstarch and vanilla. Add melted butter and Karo syrup.
Mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shells. Sprinkle nuts on top (1/2 cup or more to each pie).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender with onion and celery if desired. Pull chicken into chunks and place in large greased casserole dish.
Mix sour cream, soups and broth; pour over chicken.
Mix margarine, stuffing and broth and sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: linguine bahamese
directions: Heat olive oil in skillet.
Add garlic, salt, pepper, crushed red pepper.
Let garlic lightly brown (do not burn garlic as it will have a bitter taste).	Add tenderized conch and saute for 1-3 minutes.
Add wine and let reduce slightly.
Add clam juice or stock and cook for 1 to 3 minutes longer.
Add parsley and cooked linguine.
Toss and serve immediately.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 9 1/2
x 13 casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix pineapple with pudding first.
Then add the rest.
Cool.

title: meat filling
directions: Brown meat, onion and garlic in hot oil.
Add the remaining ingredients; simmer for 30 minutes, stirring frequently to prevent burning.
Yield:
3 cups.
Carbohydrate 3 g, protein 7 g, fat 8 g, calories 112.
One serving = 1/2 cup meat medium fat exchange, 1/2 fat exchange.

title: magic icebox lemon pie
directions: Mix margarine or butter and vanilla wafers.
Press into pie plate for crust.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain grease.
Mix in rest of ingredients. Simmer about 45 minutes on medium to low heat until sauce thickens.

title: sweet and sour dill pickles
directions: Wash dills in cold water; drain and dry thoroughly.
Cut in strips and pack in jar or jars.
Must have a tight lid.
Bring the 4 syrup ingredients to a boil, then let cool.
Pour over pickles. Turn jar or jars upside down for 3 days.
Enjoy!

title: homemade play dough
directions: Heat under medium heat until unable to stir any longer.
Knead dough.
Allow to cool and is ready to play!
Store in airtight container.

title: butterscotch rounds
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons butter in each of two 8 or 9-inch layer pans.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup pecan halves over butter in each pan.
In large mixer bowl, dissolve yeast in hot water.
Add 1 1/3 cup flour and the remaining ingredients.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 2 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls over mixture in pans.
Let rise in warm place (85°) for 50 minutes.
(Dough will not double.) Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Immediately invert pans onto serving plates; let pans remain a minute so butterscotch drizzles down over coffee cakes.
(Makes 2 coffee cakes.)

title: honey bars
directions: Mix all ingredients into a thick, round ball.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
While still warm, spread with icing.

title: seven day sweet pickles
directions: 1st Day:
Wash cucumbers and cover with boiling water.

title: orange carrots
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, over medium heat, in 3/4 cup boiling water, heat carrots and salt to boiling.
Cover and cook 6 to 8 minutes, until carrots are tender-crisp.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Over medium heat, cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken bologna
directions: Cut the meat from the bones.
Add Tender Quick.
Grind twice; let set 24 hours.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and grind again, then process as any fresh meat (such as stuffed sausage) or stuff into cloth bags and boil in water 30 minutes.
Let cool, then slice and freeze.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake mix as package directs for 2 (9-inch) layers.
Remove from pans; cool thoroughly. In large mixer bowl, beat Eagle Brand and chocolate until well blended.
Gradually beat in water, then pudding mix until smooth. Chill at least 30 minutes.
Beat until smooth.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Place one cake layer on serving plate; top with 1 1/2 cups mousse mixture.
Top with remaining cake layer.
Frost side and top of cake with remaining mousse mixture. Chill.
Garnish as desired.
Store covered in refrigerator. Makes 1 (9-inch) cake.
Preparation time:
2 hours.
Total time: 3 hours.

title: apricot delight
directions: Combine jello, sugar and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in fruit and cool.
Combine milk and cream cheese, beating until smooth.
Stir in jello mixture and add nuts.
Pour into glass dish and refrigerate overnight and then serve.

title: millionaire pie
directions: In large bowl, mix lemon juice and milk until thickened.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Mix well.
Add sugar to whipped cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Heat undrained pineapple in small saucepan. Bring to boil. Add lemon Jell-O. Stir until dissolved. Place in refrigerator to cool. Prepare pudding mix with 2 cups milk. Combine pudding with pineapple mixture. Fold in Cool Whip. Line 9 x 13-inch glass dish with sliced angel food cake. Cover with half pineapple mixture. Repeat layers and end with pudding mixture. Cover and chill overnight.

title: smoke sausage and rice
directions: Rinse rice; drain.
Brown rice with a teaspoon of grease. Combine onion, celery, pepper, garlic, tomato, salt and pepper and 3 cups hot water.
Let cook for 20 minutes on low heat.
Add sausage and 1/2 cup hot water; simmer for 10 minutes.

title: wine-baked chicken
directions: Make sauce with the first 7 ingredients.
Pour over chicken and cover.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 375°.
Uncover last 15 minutes. Serve at once over hot rice.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Pull meat off bones.
Melt margarine in casserole.
In a separate bowl, pour margarine over stuffing.
Put half of stuffing in bottom of casserole.
Spread chicken over stuffing.
Pour 1/2 cup of broth over top of chicken.
Mix sour cream and soup; spread over chicken.
Top with rest of stuffing and 1/2 cup of broth over top of all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini nut loaf
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda, lemon peel, salt, cinnamon and ginger; set aside.
In another bowl, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and if desired, orange extract.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture along with zucchini and nuts; mix well.
Turn batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan to wire rack.
Cool thoroughly. Makes 1 loaf.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Bring liquid, spices, salt and sugar to boil.
Pour over chopped ingredients.
Let stand several hours before using. Keeps indefinitely and can be frozen.

title: apple cake
directions: Prepare apples; set aside.
Measure salad oil in bowl.
Add sugar and eggs; mix well.
Beat at low speed until creamy.
Sift flour and measure; sift again with salt and soda.
Add flour mix to creamy mixture in small amounts; beat well after each addition. When stiff, beat by hand.
Fold in apples and nuts by hand.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan evenly, using wax paper after greasing.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Top with whipped cream and enjoy.

title: snack crackers
directions: Put crackers in a large bowl.
Add seasonings and pour oil over all.
Stir every 15 minutes (5 times).
Bake on cookie sheet in a 275° oven for 15 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut in half lengthwise.
Boil in salted water until tender; drain well.
Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Add lemon juice and brown sugar; stir until mixture thickens.
Add carrots and stir until well glazed and heated through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: taco casserole
directions: Break up Doritos in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brown ground beef and drain off the grease.
Stir in the taco seasoning mix (do not add water).
Pour the ground beef mixture on top of the Doritos.
Heat 1/4 cup milk and 1 can Cheese cheese soup, then pour over the ground beef.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, onions and green peppers.
Anything else you desire may be added at this time.
Top with 2 cups of grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream and salsa, if desired.

title: zucchini chicken bake
directions: Cook and drain bacon, then crumble to form crumbs.
In a separate pan, saute onion and garlic until tender, then blend in soup, milk and zucchini.
Cook until zucchini is tender.

title: crusty chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Use 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Thoroughly mix mayonnaise, mustard and butter.
Dip the chicken breasts in the mixture and roll in the stuffing.
Place breasts in baking dish.
If there is stuffing left, stir it with the remaining butter mixture.
Sprinkle around the breasts.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake for an additional 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti with clam sauce
directions: Saute onion, garlic, celery and small amount of parsley in olive oil.
Add liquid from minced clams and salt.
Simmer slowly until onion is well cooked and about half of liquid has evaporated (5 to 10 minutes).
Add clams and remaining parsley.
Simmer, covered, about 5 minutes.
Cook spaghetti and serve with clam sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: marinated pork tenderloins
directions: Wash tenderloins and pat dry.
Lightly salt and pepper and place in airtight container.
Pour salad dressing and Worcestershire sauce on top and turn over to coat.
Place overnight in refrigerator.
Grill for 15 to 30 minutes over medium-high heat, until done.

title: white fudge
directions: Mix together and cook to soft ball stage, stirring continuously.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 pound butter.
Beat until smooth and creamy.

title: garlic butter
directions: Combine all ingredients; store covered in the refrigerator. Serve with crackers, bread or use on vegetables.

title: berry delicious chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray Pam on baking dish. Place chicken in a single layer in dish.

title: ground beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Layer all ingredients in casserole dish except for soup.
Pour soup over top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 400°.

title: wiggler's casserole
directions: Mix hamburger, vegetables and macaroni; season to taste.
Mix soup and milk and pour over mixture.
Bake at 400° for 1/2 hour.

title: party mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Melt margarine in large shallow roasting pan in oven until completely melted.
Take out and add seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add all cereal, pretzels and nuts.
Mix until well coated.
Put back in oven for 1 hour. Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool. Sprinkle with small amount of table salt and serve.

title: melting moments
directions: Mix until soft dough all ingredients except coconut.
If dough is too soft, refrigerate, then shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll into coconut.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes (until lightly browned).

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°. Try adding chopped green pepper, onion and pimiento.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Thoroughly combine dry ingredients in heavy 4-quart saucepan. Stir in milk. Bring to a bubbly boil on medium heat, stirring constantly. Bring to hard ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add oleo, nuts and vanilla. Beat until fudge thickens.
Pour in a buttered 8 or 9-inch pan.

title: rugelach
directions: Beat 1/2 pound butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in cream and salt.
Gradually add flour.
Divide dough into 4 parts, wrap each part and put in freezer for 1/2 hour.
Melt remaining butter.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Heat oven to 350°.
Working with each quarter piece of dough at a time, roll each part into a 1/8-inch thick round on a floured surface.
Brush with butter, sprinkle with 1 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon/sugar, 1/4 each nuts and raisins.
Cut round into 16 wedges, roll each up starting with the widest end.
Put on an ungreased baking sheet and bake until golden for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 64.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Quickly brown meat in 3 tablespoons oil. Add water and mushrooms. Stir in soup. Heat to boiling. Blend sour cream and flour. Add to meat mixture. Cook until it thickens.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: ham rolls
directions: Slice tops off of rolls.
Layer ham and cheese.
Put on tops. Mix all other ingredients and pour over rolls.
Sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apricot ice cream sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir until sugar dissolves.
Serve over vanilla ice cream.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk and lemon juice until thick.
Add softened cream cheese and mix well.
Add 1/2 Cool Whip and mix. Spread on top of crust, then put pie filling on top of that layer. Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: sausage-apple ring
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Press into 6-cup ring mold.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Drain grease a couple of times during baking.

title: mexican dip #2
directions: Spread cream cheese in the bottom of a glass pie plate.
Layer in order:
chili with beans, Mexican green chilies, Monterey Jack cheese, ripe olives and spring onions.
Heat in microwave oven until the cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: french toast with cinnamon
directions: In large frying pan, melt 1 teaspoon butter on low-medium heat. Whip eggs in mixing bowl.
Dip loaf bread in eggs.
Sprinkle with cinnamon to taste.
Cook in melted butter until golden brown. Smother with butter.
Sprinkle white powdered sugar over bread, then add syrup to taste.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and sweet potatoes.
Sift
together
flour,
salt,
soda,
baking powder and spices.
Add to sweet potato mixture.
Pour into 2 large, greased and
floured
loaf pans.
Bake for one hour at 350°.
(Will make 3 small loaves.)

title: lemon chicken with capers
directions: Spread pine nuts on baking dish and roast for about 4 minutes at 400°. Gently pound chicken breasts thin.
Salt and pepper. Heat oil in skillet and saute chicken until cooked.
Remove from pan and place on warm plate.
Drain skillet, add wine and bring to boil, scraping bottom of pan, reduce by half over high heat and add lemon juice and capers.
Remove from heat and add butter, whisking 1 tablespoon at a time.
Add any juice from chicken on platter.
Pour sauce over chicken and sprinkle with pine nuts.

title: homemade hot rolls
directions: Mix shortening and sugar with mixer.
Pour boiling water over shortening/sugar mixture.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water, then pour over mixture.
Beat 2 eggs; add.
Add 2 cups flour and salt, then use mixer to blend.
Add 4 more cups of flour and mix by hand.
Grease top of dough and put into greased Tupperware bowl. Seal bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out 1/4 inch thick, cut and dip in melted butter.
Fold over.
Let rise 2 to 3 hours. Cook at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Bring seasoning packet in Stove Top stuffing mix to boil in 1 2/3 cups water.
Saute 1 medium onion in 1/2 stick margarine.
Add 1 can chicken broth into mixture.
Mix the packet of dressing mix with the packet.
Place this on top of turkey.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Then add 1 cup boiling water.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch oblong pan at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or bake in layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: nutty fudge topping(for ice cream)
directions: Makes 1 1/2 cups thick and creamy topping; spoon over ice cream.

title: okra pickles
directions: Pack okra in jar (pints) and in each jar put 1/2 teaspoon celery seed, 1/2 teaspoon mustard seed and 2 teaspoons dill seed.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over steak. Marinate in refrigerator 1 to 3 days. Bring to room temperature, then broil or BBQ approximately 5 minutes per side. Slice thinly on the diagonal. Make 4 to 6 servings.

title: chutney
directions: Dice mangos.
Combine all ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat to simmer and cook slowly for 3 hours.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat with onions, drain.
Add beans, corn, taco sauce, Ranch style dressing and tomatoes.
Add 1 cup water.
Cook slowly for 2 hours.
Serve over corn chips and grated cheese on corn chips (I cook mine in crock-pot).

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: hamburger corn pone casserole
directions: In skillet, brown onion, green pepper and ground beef; drain. Add tomato sauce, corn with juice, and salt and pepper to taste. Pour mixture in an 8 inch greased casserole dish.
Mix egg and milk together; add corn bread mix and mix well.
Spread on top of meat mixture in casserole dish.
Bake at 375° to 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: hidden valley ranch buffalo wings
directions: Mix together margarine, pepper sauce and vinegar.
Dip chicken pieces in margarine, sauce, and vinegar mixture.
Dredge in dry salad dressing mix.
Arrange on baking pan (cookie pan will do). Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn pieces and bake 15 minutes longer or until done.

title: homemade apple butter
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a granite pan, uncovered, for 3 hours at 300°.
Then put in jars and seal.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and knead.
Shape into small balls (do not roll), and place in greased pans.
Bake for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: delicious sweet pickles
directions: Drain pickles well in colander and slice about 1/4-inch thick. Return to the same jar a layer at a time, sprinkling sugar and spices over each layer.
Close jar tightly and seal with several layers of masking tape; sealing really well.
Turn upside down twice daily for two days.
Then, refrigerate and enjoy!

title: pineapple chess pie
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Drain pineapple.
Combine dry ingredients with margarine, vanilla, pineapple and milk.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: good morning casserole
directions: Line bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan with bread pieces. In large
mixing bowl combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over bread and refrigerate
4 to 5 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: beef bisquick bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease baking dish good.
Cook beef and onion in skillet until beef is brown.
Drain grease off.
Stir in soup, vegetables and milk.
Mix together the Bisquick and water in baking dish until moistened.
Spread evenly.
Add beef mixture over Bisquick batter.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Pour pie filling in a bowl and add strawberries, pineapple and oranges.
Chill overnight.
Add sliced bananas just before serving.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix gelatin and boiling water; add orange juice. Chill until it begins to thicken. Stir in sour cream and sherbet.
Beat until thick and foamy. Add pineapple and oranges. When set, sprinkle with coconut.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Cut up chicken breasts and brown in skillet. Add parmesan spaghetti sauce and cook about 20 minutes. Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: frozen vegetable casserole
directions: Thaw vegetables in microwave and put in a greased casserole. Combine soups with 1/4 can milk and pour over vegetables.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°; mix dry ingredients in a large bowl. Mix milk and 1/2 of pineapple and juice, egg whites and oil in a bowl or blender.
Combine the ingredients and mix; drain the second half of the pineapple and add to mixture.
Line the muffin pan with paper baking cups and fill with batter.
Bake for 17 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: scallop bake
directions: Cover scallops with cold water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Drain; reserve 1 cup liquid.
Slice scallops 1/4-inch thick.
Cook onion in butter until tender. Blend in flour and pepper.
Add reserved liquid and milk.
Cook and stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mushrooms, Parmesan cheese, parsley, pimento and scallops.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Top with potato chips.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: jamalya candy
directions: Melt the margarine in a pan.
Spread the coconut over this. Put the chocolate chips, milk and pecans over the coconut and bake until done (about 20 minutes).

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Pour into greased pie plate. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook (boil) chicken ahead of time until tender. Remove meat from bones (reserve broth).
Cut chicken into pieces and place in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese, seasoning and garlic salt or powder and spread in 9-inch greased pie pan.

title: snow cream
directions: Put milk in bowl.
Whip until thick.
Add sugar and vanilla; whip again.
Now fold in big pan of snow.

title: gi gi and mee ma rutland's hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add eggs, sweet milk and onion. It may not take the entire can of milk.
Have batter stiff enough that you can drop by small spoonfuls into hot Wesson oil where the fish have been fried.
(Use a deep pot or Fry Baby cooker.)
The hush puppies will pop up; turn over and cook on the other side. Drain on paper towels.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, Milnot and butter and let boil for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add chocolate bits and marshmallow cream.

title: knishes
directions: Saute onion and pepper until soft.
Brown ground beef and drain. Add to vegetables. Blend in soup mix until dissolved.
Mix in cheese. Cut crescent roll triangles in half.
Place teaspoon of filling on dough and roll until edges are sealed.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes on ungreased baking sheet.

title: raisin pumpkin or squash bread
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and egg.
Add pumpkin or squash.
Add remaining dry ingredients.
Add juice and raisins.

title: soda cracker pie
directions: Fold sugar into egg whites.
Add remaining ingredients to egg whites.
Pour in 8-inch buttered pie pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Refrigerate 2 hours.
Top with real whipped cream.

title: raspberry cream pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Chill several days ahead (it gets hotter).
Serve surrounded by assorted raw vegetables for dipping.

title: rhubarb dumplings
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients, bring to a boil and simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine cornstarch and water.
Stir into rhubarb. Boil 1 minute.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Blend into butter mixture.
Add lemon extract. Fold fruit and nuts into batter until thoroughly mixed.
Spoon mixture into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours. Cool cake thoroughly before removing from pan.

title: mimi's waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients but egg whites. Stir only until blended. Fold in egg whites.
Pour in hot waffle iron.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in 4-quart saucepan.
Stir until mixed. Cook on medium-high heat until a small amount forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Cook stirring constantly 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, peanut butter and vanilla. Beat until it begins to thicken.
Pour immediately into a greased 11 x 15-inch pan.
Smooth out.
When cool, cut into 35 squares.

title: jambalaya(dirty rice)
directions: Heat fat in 2-quart saucepan, add rice and fry to a golden brown on medium heat.
Add onion, celery and minced garlic and saute until wilted but not brown.
Add seasonings, chicken stock and ground meat.
Bring to a boil; turn switch to lowest heat and cover.
Cook for 30 minutes without lifting lid.

title: cherry salad
directions: Prepare Jell-O and add other ingredients.
Chill until set. Serve.

title: sun and fun dessert
directions: First Layer:
Cream butter and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Fold in sifted flour.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage breakfast loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, saute the sausage; cool.
In a bowl, combine the sausage, cheese, one egg, parsley, onion salt and garlic salt; mix well.
Unroll pizza dough; roll into a 12 x 8 inch rectangle.
Spread sausage mixture down the center of dough.
Bring dough over filling; pinch seams to seal. Place seam side down on a greased baking sheet; tuck ends under. Beat remaining egg; brush over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Let stand for 5 minutes before slicing.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix and bake according to directions.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Mix pineapple, blueberries and 1 cup of sugar.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over fruit. Drizzle evenly with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with pecans, then with 1/4 cup of sugar.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Wrap bacon around boned and skinned chicken breasts which have been cut in half.
Secure with skewers or toothpicks.
Place shredded dried beef in casserole and lay chicken and bacon rolls on top of beef.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.
Serves 6.

title: watermelon fire and ice salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Makes 3 cups.
Serve on sliced oranges or cheese-filled manicotti or with corn or potato chips.
Or top
1 cup dairy sour cream with 1 cup salsa and serve with chips.

title: feta cheese spread
directions: Mix Feta cheese, mayonnaise, spices, herbs and cream cheese in food processor.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups. Great on baked potatoes!

title: beefy vegetable soup
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in Dutch oven until beef is brown; drain.
Stir in Hamburger Helper sauce mix, water and other ingredients.

title: blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat 5 minutes until smooth.
Fold in blueberries.
Pour filling in pie shell. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bundt cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the first seven ingredients. Beat on low speed for 30 seconds, then beat on medium for 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased bundt pam.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes in a 350 degree oven.
(Mixture will be thick.)

title: baked chicken
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Dip and coat each piece with mayonnaise, then flour.
Salt and pepper each piece before or after coatings according to taste and preference.
Place coated chicken in baking pan.

title: savory pot roast
directions: Slow Cooker Directions:
In slow cooker mix soup, soup mix, potatoes, and carrots.
Add roast and turn to coat.
Cover and cook on low 8 to 9 hours or until roast and vegetables are done.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together.
Pour in a 10 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with the cracker crumbs mixed with the melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: hot hominy
directions: Beat soup.
Pour over hominy after adding chilies.
Put grated cheese on top. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes, then reduce to 325°. Bake 30 minutes more.

title: cranberry sauce cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and almond extract.
Cream again.
Sift together the flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Set aside.
Dry raisins on paper toweling.
Mix raisins with a tablespoon or two of the dry ingredients.
Add raisins to creamed mixture.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Add cranberry sauce, mixing well.
Pour into a greased 9-inch angel food pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven 1 hour or until it tests done.

title: italian pot roast
directions: Heat fat in heavy pan.
Add mushrooms and onions.
Saute over low heat until tender.
Remove from heat.
Rub meat with flour and brown on all sides.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in slow oven for several hours.
Serves 8.

title: south-of-the-border chicken sandwiches
directions: In small bowl, combine margarine, chili powder, onion powder, cumin, paprika and garlic powder; blend well.
Spread cut sides of buns with margarine mixture.

title: iowa corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes or until set.
Leave lid on the first half hour.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Frost while warm.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix all together; spread onto tortilla.
Roll up and place on platter.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Place in freezer overnight. Cut into slices while frozen.
Thaw about one hour before serving.

title: liverwurst pate
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Chill.
Shape into a ball by turning on piece of foil or wax paper which you slightly grease. Store in refrigerator until it is chilled enough to frost.

title: patsy's real chili
directions: In heavy pot or Dutch oven, fry bacon, then meat and brown. Add oregano, chili, cayenne, cumin, garlic and Tabasco; mix thoroughly.
Add tomatoes, peppers and enough liquid to cover ingredients, beginning with beer.
Simmer, uncovered, for around 3 1/2 to 4 hours, adding strong black coffee as necessary.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Put pineapple and juice in casserole. Mix flour, sugar and cheese. Spread over pineapple. Sprinkle Ritz crackers over that. Pour melted butter over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Combine beef, beans, seasoning mix and water in saucepan. Bring to a boil and simmer 10 to 15 minutes until liquid is gone. Pour tomato sauce into pie pan.
Dip both sides of 6 tortillas in sauce and layer around 9 x 13-inch baking dish to form crust. Spread beef mixture over tortillas.
Dip remaining tortillas in sauce and arrange on meat mixture.
Pour remaining sauce evenly over all and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. (Can be garnished with lettuce, olives, tomatoes, sour cream, etc.) Makes 6 servings; 3 1/2 proteins, 1 1/2 breads and 2/3 vegetable. (WW)

title: jigglers
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin.
Dissolve completely.
Pour mixture slowly into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Cut in any shape.
Use any flavors.
It is a wonderful healthy snack.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
In separate bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to butter mixture alternating with water.
Mix well.
Pour into greased cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake is done.

title: pumpkin cake with caramel sauce
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the first six ingredients.
In another bowl, beat eggs, pumpkin and oil until smooth; add to the dry ingredients.
Mix until well blended about 1 minute.
Pour into a greased 12 X 9 X 2 inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35-40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mexican wedding cookies
directions: Mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake in slow oven at 300°
for 20 minutes.
After cookies cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: corn meal pie
directions: Mix all together in a greased dish and bake at 350°.

title: easy sticky buns
directions: Butter Bundt pan.
Put raisins and nuts in.
Put in dough balls, melted butter, brown sugar and pudding mix.
Then mix up sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on.
Cover with foil and leave set out overnight.
Next morning bake at 350° for 30 minutes and serve.
Makes 12 servings.
Very good!

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and eggs well.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well.
Shape into small balls; roll in colored sugar and cinnamon, which have been mixed together.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.
These puff up and flatten out.

title: frankie baker's peach or apple pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in cream and vanilla.
Pour over fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: buttermilk scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a shallow dish, combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge potatoes in the flour mixture and place them in a shallow 2-quart baking dish.
In a small skillet, heat margarine over medium heat.
Add onion and saute for about 5 minutes or until tender.
Spoon onion over potatoes and pour buttermilk over top. Sprinkle paprika over potatoes and bake for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until the potatoes are tender.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Mix mustard and jelly together and cook on low heat until dissolved.
(A crock-pot is excellent for this dish.) Place the wieners into the mixture.
Cook for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Microwave chocolate and margarine in large, microwavable bowl on High 2 minutes or until margarine is melted.
Stir sugar into chocolate until well blended.
Mix in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour and walnuts until well blended.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass dish) for 30 to 35 minutes, until toothpick inserted in center comes out with fudgy crumbs.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pans.
Cut into squares.
Makes 24 fudgy brownies.

title: sour cream peach pie
directions: Place peaches pit side up in unbaked pie shell.
Combine other ingredients and pour over peaches.
Bake 15 minutes in a 400° oven. Reduce heat to 300° and bake 1 hour longer.

title: tropical mandarin bread
directions: Blend together oil and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in bananas and almond extract.
Cut oranges into pieces and add to banana mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients except graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well. Grease bottom and sides of an 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch (1 1/2-quart) loaf pan.
Sprinkle with graham cracker crumbs.
Shake out excess.
Pour batter into pan, spreading evenly.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: perfect pie crust(6 crusts)
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large bowl and mix well with fork.
Add shortening and mix until ingredients are crumbly.
In a small bowl, beat together water, vinegar and egg.
Combine the two mixtures, stirring until all ingredients are moistened.
Divide dough in 6 portions.
Shape each portion with hands into a flat, round patty, ready for rolling.
Wrap each in plastic wrap or wax paper and chill at least 1/2 hour (can freeze and thaw in refrigerator for later use).
No matter how much you handle this dough, it will always be flaky, tender and delicious.
Dough can be left in refrigerator up to 3 days.

title: tropical chicken salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, pineapple, mayo, sugar, orange and lime rind, ginger and lemon juice in food processor until smooth.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage and cook until brown; drain grease.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Place bread cubes on bottom.
Sprinkle sausage over bread.
Mix in bowl rest of ingredients and pour over sausage.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
